63
64SpellDestination::SpellDestination()
65{
66 _position.Relocate(0, 0, 0, 0);
67 _transportGUID.Clear();
68 _transportOffset.Relocate(0, 0, 0, 0);
69}
70
71SpellDestination::SpellDestination(float x, float y, float z, float orientation, uint32 mapId)
72{
73 _position.Relocate(x, y, z, orientation);
74 _transportGUID.Clear();
75 _position.m_mapId = mapId;
76 _transportOffset.Relocate(0, 0, 0, 0);
77}
78
79SpellDestination::SpellDestination(Position const& pos)
80{
81 _position.Relocate(pos);
82 _transportGUID.Clear();
83 _transportOffset.Relocate(0, 0, 0, 0);
84}
85
86SpellDestination::SpellDestination(WorldObject const& wObj)
87{
88 _transportGUID = wObj.GetTransGUID();
89 _transportOffset.Relocate(wObj.GetTransOffsetX(), wObj.GetTransOffsetY(), wObj.GetTransOffsetZ(), wObj.GetTransOffsetO());
90 _position.Relocate(wObj);
91}
92
93void SpellDestination::Relocate(Position const& pos)
94{
95 if (!_transportGUID.IsEmpty())
96 {
97 Position offset;
98 _position.GetPositionOffsetTo(pos, offset);
99 _transportOffset.RelocateOffset(offset);
100 }
101 _position.Relocate(pos);
102}
103
104void SpellDestination::RelocateOffset(Position const& offset)
105{
106 if (!_transportGUID.IsEmpty())
107 _transportOffset.RelocateOffset(offset);
108
109 _position.RelocateOffset(offset);
110}
111
112SpellCastTargets::SpellCastTargets() : m_targetMask(0), m_objectTarget(nullptr), m_itemTarget(nullptr),
113 m_itemTargetEntry(0), m_pitch(0.0f), m_speed(0.0f)
114{
115}
116
117SpellCastTargets::SpellCastTargets(Unit* caster, WorldPackets::Spells::SpellCastRequest const& spellCastRequest) :
118 m_targetMask(spellCastRequest.Target.Flags), m_objectTarget(nullptr), m_itemTarget(nullptr),
119 m_objectTargetGUID(spellCastRequest.Target.Unit), m_itemTargetGUID(spellCastRequest.Target.Item),
120 m_itemTargetEntry(0), m_pitch(0.0f), m_speed(0.0f), m_strTarget(spellCastRequest.Target.Name)
121{
122 if (spellCastRequest.Target.SrcLocation)
123 {
124 m_src._transportGUID = spellCastRequest.Target.SrcLocation->Transport;
125 Position* pos;
126 if (!m_src._transportGUID.IsEmpty())
127 pos = &m_src._transportOffset;
128 else
129 pos = &m_src._position;
130
131 pos->Relocate(spellCastRequest.Target.SrcLocation->Location);
132 if (spellCastRequest.Target.Orientation)
133 pos->SetOrientation(*spellCastRequest.Target.Orientation);
134 }
135
136 if (spellCastRequest.Target.DstLocation)
137 {
138 m_dst._transportGUID = spellCastRequest.Target.DstLocation->Transport;
139 Position* pos;
140 if (!m_dst._transportGUID.IsEmpty())
141 pos = &m_dst._transportOffset;
142 else
143 pos = &m_dst._position;
144
145 pos->Relocate(spellCastRequest.Target.DstLocation->Location);
146 if (spellCastRequest.Target.Orientation)
147 pos->SetOrientation(*spellCastRequest.Target.Orientation);
148 }
149
150 SetPitch(spellCastRequest.MissileTrajectory.Pitch);
151 SetSpeed(spellCastRequest.MissileTrajectory.Speed);
152
153 Update(caster);
154}
155
156SpellCastTargets::~SpellCastTargets() { }
157
158void SpellCastTargets::Write(WorldPackets::Spells::SpellTargetData& data)
159{
160 data.Flags = m_targetMask;
161
162 if (m_targetMask & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ALLY | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_ENEMY | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MINIPET))
163 data.Unit = m_objectTargetGUID;
164
165 if (m_targetMask & (TARGET_FLAG_ITEM | TARGET_FLAG_TRADE_ITEM) && m_itemTarget)
166 data.Item = m_itemTarget->GetGUID();
167
168 if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION)
169 {
170 data.SrcLocation = boost::in_place();
171 data.SrcLocation->Transport = m_src._transportGUID; // relative position guid here - transport for example
172 if (!m_src._transportGUID.IsEmpty())
173 data.SrcLocation->Location = m_src._transportOffset;
174 else
175 data.SrcLocation->Location = m_src._position;
176 }
177
178 if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
179 {
180 data.DstLocation = boost::in_place();
181 data.DstLocation->Transport = m_dst._transportGUID; // relative position guid here - transport for example
182 if (!m_dst._transportGUID.IsEmpty())
183 data.DstLocation->Location = m_dst._transportOffset;
184 else
185 data.DstLocation->Location = m_dst._position;
186 }
187
188 if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_STRING)
189 data.Name = m_strTarget;
190}
191
192ObjectGuid SpellCastTargets::GetOrigUnitTargetGUID() const
193{
194 switch (m_origObjectTargetGUID.GetHigh())
195 {
196 case HighGuid::Player:
197 case HighGuid::Vehicle:
198 case HighGuid::Creature:
199 case HighGuid::Pet:
200 return m_origObjectTargetGUID;
201 default:
202 return ObjectGuid();
203 }
204}
205
206void SpellCastTargets::SetOrigUnitTarget(Unit* target)
207{
208 if (!target)
209 return;
210
211 m_origObjectTargetGUID = target->GetGUID();
212}

218
219 return ObjectGuid::Empty;

293{
294 m_objectTarget = NULL;

297}

299void SpellCastTargets::SetItemTarget(Item* item)
300{
301 if (!item)
302 return;
303

305 m_itemTargetGUID = item->GetGUID();
306 m_itemTargetEntry = item->GetEntry();
307 m_targetMask |= TARGET_FLAG_ITEM;
308}

310void SpellCastTargets::SetTradeItemTarget(Player* caster)
311{
312 m_itemTargetGUID = ObjectGuid::TradeItem;
313 m_itemTargetEntry = 0;
314 m_targetMask |= TARGET_FLAG_TRADE_ITEM;
315
316 Update(caster);
317}

324 m_itemTargetEntry = m_itemTarget->GetEntry();

423
424void SpellCastTargets::Update(Unit* caster)
425{
426 m_objectTarget = !m_objectTargetGUID.IsEmpty() ? ((m_objectTargetGUID == caster->GetGUID()) ? caster : ObjectAccessor::GetWorldObject(*caster, m_objectTargetGUID)) : NULL;
427
428 m_itemTarget = NULL;
429 if (caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
430 {
431 Player* player = caster->ToPlayer();
432 if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_ITEM)
433 m_itemTarget = player->GetItemByGuid(m_itemTargetGUID);
434 else if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_TRADE_ITEM)
435 {
436 if (m_itemTargetGUID == ObjectGuid::TradeItem)
437 if (TradeData* pTrade = player->GetTradeData())
438 m_itemTarget = pTrade->GetTraderData()->GetItem(TRADE_SLOT_NONTRADED);
439 }
440
441 if (m_itemTarget)
442 m_itemTargetEntry = m_itemTarget->GetEntry();
443 }
444
445 // update positions by transport move
446 if (HasSrc() && !m_src._transportGUID.IsEmpty())
447 {
448 if (WorldObject* transport = ObjectAccessor::GetWorldObject(*caster, m_src._transportGUID))
449 {
450 m_src._position.Relocate(transport);
451 m_src._position.RelocateOffset(m_src._transportOffset);
452 }
453 }
454
455 if (HasDst() && !m_dst._transportGUID.IsEmpty())
456 {
457 if (WorldObject* transport = ObjectAccessor::GetWorldObject(*caster, m_dst._transportGUID))
458 {
459 m_dst._position.Relocate(transport);
460 m_dst._position.RelocateOffset(m_dst._transportOffset);
461 }
462 }
463}
464
465void SpellCastTargets::OutDebug() const
466{
467 if (!m_targetMask)
468 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "No targets");
469
470 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "target mask: %u", m_targetMask);
471 if (m_targetMask & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_MASK))
472 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Object target: %s", m_objectTargetGUID.ToString().c_str());
473 if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_ITEM)
474 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Item target: %s", m_itemTargetGUID.ToString().c_str());
475 if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_TRADE_ITEM)
476 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Trade item target: %s", m_itemTargetGUID.ToString().c_str());
477 if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION)
478 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Source location: transport guid:%s trans offset: %s position: %s", m_src._transportGUID.ToString().c_str(), m_src._transportOffset.ToString().c_str(), m_src._position.ToString().c_str());
479 if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
480 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Destination location: transport guid:%s trans offset: %s position: %s", m_dst._transportGUID.ToString().c_str(), m_dst._transportOffset.ToString().c_str(), m_dst._position.ToString().c_str());
481 if (m_targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_STRING)
482 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "String: %s", m_strTarget.c_str());
483 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "speed: %f", m_speed);
484 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "pitch: %f", m_pitch);
485}
486
487SpellValue::SpellValue(Difficulty diff, SpellInfo const* proto)
488{
489 // todo 6.x
490 SpellEffectInfoVector effects = proto->GetEffectsForDifficulty(diff);
491 ASSERT(effects.size() <= MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS);
492 memset(EffectBasePoints, 0, sizeof(EffectBasePoints));
493 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : effects)
494 if (effect)
495 EffectBasePoints[effect->EffectIndex] = effect->BasePoints;
496
497 MaxAffectedTargets = proto->MaxAffectedTargets;
498 RadiusMod = 1.0f;
499 AuraStackAmount = 1;
500}
501
502Spell::Spell(Unit* caster, SpellInfo const* info, TriggerCastFlags triggerFlags, ObjectGuid originalCasterGUID, bool skipCheck) :
503m_spellInfo(info), m_caster((info->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR6_CAST_BY_CHARMER) && caster->GetCharmerOrOwner()) ? caster->GetCharmerOrOwner() : caster),
504m_spellValue(new SpellValue(caster->GetMap()->GetDifficultyID(), m_spellInfo)), m_preGeneratedPath(PathGenerator(m_caster))
505{
506 _effects = info->GetEffectsForDifficulty(caster->GetMap()->GetDifficultyID());
507
508 m_customError = SPELL_CUSTOM_ERROR_NONE;
509 m_skipCheck = skipCheck;
510 m_selfContainer = NULL;
511 m_referencedFromCurrentSpell = false;
512 m_executedCurrently = false;
513 m_needComboPoints = m_spellInfo->NeedsComboPoints();
514 m_comboPointGain = 0;
515 m_delayStart = 0;
516 m_delayAtDamageCount = 0;
517
518 m_applyMultiplierMask = 0;
519 m_auraScaleMask = 0;
520 memset(m_damageMultipliers, 0, sizeof(m_damageMultipliers));
521
522 // Get data for type of attack
523 switch (m_spellInfo->DmgClass)
524 {
525 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MELEE:
526 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_REQ_OFFHAND))
527 m_attackType = OFF_ATTACK;
528 else
529 m_attackType = BASE_ATTACK;
530 break;
531 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_RANGED:
532 m_attackType = m_spellInfo->IsRangedWeaponSpell() ? RANGED_ATTACK : BASE_ATTACK;
533 break;
534 default:
535 // Wands
536 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_AUTOREPEAT_FLAG))
537 m_attackType = RANGED_ATTACK;
538 else
539 m_attackType = BASE_ATTACK;
540 break;
541 }
542
543 m_spellSchoolMask = info->GetSchoolMask(); // Can be override for some spell (wand shoot for example)
544
545 if (m_attackType == RANGED_ATTACK)
546 // wand case
547 if ((m_caster->getClassMask() & CLASSMASK_WAND_USERS) != 0 && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
548 if (Item* pItem = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetWeaponForAttack(RANGED_ATTACK))
549 m_spellSchoolMask = SpellSchoolMask(1 << pItem->GetTemplate()->GetDamageType());
550
551 if (!originalCasterGUID.IsEmpty())
552 m_originalCasterGUID = originalCasterGUID;
553 else
554 m_originalCasterGUID = m_caster->GetGUID();
555
556 if (m_originalCasterGUID == m_caster->GetGUID())
557 m_originalCaster = m_caster;
558 else
559 {
560 m_originalCaster = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, m_originalCasterGUID);
561 if (m_originalCaster && !m_originalCaster->IsInWorld())
562 m_originalCaster = NULL;
563 }
564
565 m_spellState = SPELL_STATE_NULL;
566 _triggeredCastFlags = triggerFlags;
567 if (info->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR4_CAN_CAST_WHILE_CASTING))
568 _triggeredCastFlags = TriggerCastFlags(uint32(_triggeredCastFlags) | TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CAST_IN_PROGRESS | TRIGGERED_CAST_DIRECTLY);
569
570 m_CastItem = NULL;
571 m_castItemGUID.Clear();
572 m_castItemEntry = 0;
573 m_castItemLevel = -1;
574 m_castFlagsEx = 0;
575
576 unitTarget = NULL;
577 itemTarget = NULL;
578 gameObjTarget = NULL;
579 destTarget = NULL;
580 damage = 0;
581 variance = 0.0f;
582 effectHandleMode = SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_LAUNCH;
583 effectInfo = nullptr;
584 m_diminishLevel = DIMINISHING_LEVEL_1;
585 m_diminishGroup = DIMINISHING_NONE;
586 m_damage = 0;
587 m_healing = 0;
588 m_procAttacker = 0;
589 m_procVictim = 0;
590 m_procEx = 0;
591 focusObject = NULL;
592 m_cast_count = 0;
593 memset(m_misc.Raw.Data, 0, sizeof(m_misc.Raw.Data));
594 m_SpellVisual = m_spellInfo->GetSpellXSpellVisualId(caster->GetMap()->GetDifficultyID());
595 m_preCastSpell = 0;
596 m_triggeredByAuraSpell = NULL;
597 m_spellAura = NULL;
598
599 //Auto Shot & Shoot (wand)
600 m_autoRepeat = m_spellInfo->IsAutoRepeatRangedSpell();
601
602 m_runesState = 0;
603 m_casttime = 0; // setup to correct value in Spell::prepare, must not be used before.
604 m_timer = 0; // will set to castime in prepare
605 m_channeledDuration = 0; // will be setup in Spell::handle_immediate
606 m_immediateHandled = false;
607
608 m_channelTargetEffectMask = 0;
609
610 // Determine if spell can be reflected back to the caster
611 // Patch 1.2 notes: Spell Reflection no longer reflects abilities
612 m_canReflect = m_spellInfo->DmgClass == SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MAGIC && !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_ABILITY)
613 && !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR1_CANT_BE_REFLECTED) && !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_UNAFFECTED_BY_INVULNERABILITY)
614 && !m_spellInfo->IsPassive() && !m_spellInfo->IsPositive();
615
616 CleanupTargetList();
617 CleanupExecuteLogList();
618
619 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++i)
620 m_destTargets[i] = SpellDestination(*m_caster);
621}
622
623Spell::~Spell()
624{
625 // unload scripts
626 while (!m_loadedScripts.empty())
627 {
628 std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator itr = m_loadedScripts.begin();
629 (*itr)->_Unload();
630 delete (*itr);
631 m_loadedScripts.erase(itr);
632 }
633
634 if (m_referencedFromCurrentSpell && m_selfContainer && *m_selfContainer == this)
635 {
636 // Clean the reference to avoid later crash.
637 // If this error is repeating, we may have to add an ASSERT to better track down how we get into this case.
638 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "SPELL: deleting spell for spell ID %u. However, spell still referenced.", m_spellInfo->Id);
639 *m_selfContainer = NULL;
640 }
641
642 if (m_caster && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
643 ASSERT(m_caster->ToPlayer()->m_spellModTakingSpell != this);
644
645 delete m_spellValue;
646 CleanupExecuteLogList();
647}
648
649void Spell::InitExplicitTargets(SpellCastTargets const& targets)
650{
651 m_targets = targets;
652 m_targets.SetOrigUnitTarget(m_targets.GetUnitTarget());
653 // this function tries to correct spell explicit targets for spell
654 // client doesn't send explicit targets correctly sometimes - we need to fix such spells serverside
655 // this also makes sure that we correctly send explicit targets to client (removes redundant data)
656 uint32 neededTargets = m_spellInfo->GetExplicitTargetMask();
657
658 if (WorldObject* target = m_targets.GetObjectTarget())
659 {
660 // check if object target is valid with needed target flags
661 // for unit case allow corpse target mask because player with not released corpse is a unit target
662 if ((target->ToUnit() && !(neededTargets & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK)))
663 || (target->ToGameObject() && !(neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_MASK))
664 || (target->ToCorpse() && !(neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK)))
665 m_targets.RemoveObjectTarget();
666 }
667 else
668 {
669 // try to select correct unit target if not provided by client or by serverside cast
670 if (neededTargets & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK))
671 {
672 Unit* unit = NULL;
673 // try to use player selection as a target
674 if (Player* playerCaster = m_caster->ToPlayer())
675 {
676 // selection has to be found and to be valid target for the spell
677 if (Unit* selectedUnit = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, playerCaster->GetTarget()))
678 if (m_spellInfo->CheckExplicitTarget(m_caster, selectedUnit) == SPELL_CAST_OK)
679 unit = selectedUnit;
680 }
681 // try to use attacked unit as a target
682 else if ((m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT) && neededTargets & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ENEMY | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT))
683 unit = m_caster->GetVictim();
684
685 // didn't find anything - let's use self as target
686 if (!unit && neededTargets & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_RAID | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_PARTY | TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ALLY))
687 unit = m_caster;
688
689 m_targets.SetUnitTarget(unit);
690 }
691 }
692
693 // check if spell needs dst target
694 if (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_DEST_LOCATION)
695 {
696 // and target isn't set
697 if (!m_targets.HasDst())
698 {
699 // try to use unit target if provided
700 if (WorldObject* target = targets.GetObjectTarget())
701 m_targets.SetDst(*target);
702 // or use self if not available
703 else
704 m_targets.SetDst(*m_caster);
705 }
706 }
707 else
708 m_targets.RemoveDst();
709
710 if (neededTargets & TARGET_FLAG_SOURCE_LOCATION)
711 {
712 if (!targets.HasSrc())
713 m_targets.SetSrc(*m_caster);
714 }
715 else
716 m_targets.RemoveSrc();
717}
718
719void Spell::SelectExplicitTargets()
720{
721 // here go all explicit target changes made to explicit targets after spell prepare phase is finished
722 if (Unit* target = m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
723 {
724 // check for explicit target redirection, for Grounding Totem for example
725 if (m_spellInfo->GetExplicitTargetMask() & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_ENEMY
726 || (m_spellInfo->GetExplicitTargetMask() & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT && !m_caster->IsFriendlyTo(target)))
727 {
728 Unit* redirect;
729 switch (m_spellInfo->DmgClass)
730 {
731 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MAGIC:
732 redirect = m_caster->GetMagicHitRedirectTarget(target, m_spellInfo);
733 break;
734 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MELEE:
735 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_RANGED:
736 redirect = m_caster->GetMeleeHitRedirectTarget(target, m_spellInfo);
737 break;
738 default:
739 redirect = NULL;
740 break;
741 }
742 if (redirect && (redirect != target))
743 m_targets.SetUnitTarget(redirect);
744 }
745 }
746}
747
748void Spell::SelectSpellTargets()
749{
750 // select targets for cast phase
751 SelectExplicitTargets();
752
753 uint32 processedAreaEffectsMask = 0;
754
755 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
756 {
757 if (!effect)
758 continue;
759
760 // not call for empty effect.
761 // Also some spells use not used effect targets for store targets for dummy effect in triggered spells
762 if (!effect->IsEffect())
763 continue;
764
765 // set expected type of implicit targets to be sent to client
766 uint32 implicitTargetMask = GetTargetFlagMask(effect->TargetA.GetObjectType()) | GetTargetFlagMask(effect->TargetB.GetObjectType());
767 if (implicitTargetMask & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT)
768 m_targets.SetTargetFlag(TARGET_FLAG_UNIT);
769 if (implicitTargetMask & (TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT | TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM))
770 m_targets.SetTargetFlag(TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT);
771
772 SelectEffectImplicitTargets(SpellEffIndex(effect->EffectIndex), effect->TargetA, processedAreaEffectsMask);
773 SelectEffectImplicitTargets(SpellEffIndex(effect->EffectIndex), effect->TargetB, processedAreaEffectsMask);
774
775 // Select targets of effect based on effect type
776 // those are used when no valid target could be added for spell effect based on spell target type
777 // some spell effects use explicit target as a default target added to target map (like SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_SPELL)
778 // some spell effects add target to target map only when target type specified (like SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON)
779 // some spell effects don't add anything to target map (confirmed with sniffs) (like SPELL_EFFECT_DESTROY_ALL_TOTEMS)
780 SelectEffectTypeImplicitTargets(effect->EffectIndex);
781
782 if (m_targets.HasDst())
783 AddDestTarget(*m_targets.GetDst(), effect->EffectIndex);
784
785 if (m_spellInfo->IsChanneled())
786 {
787 uint32 mask = (1 << effect->EffectIndex);
788 for (std::vector<TargetInfo>::iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
789 {
790 if (ihit->effectMask & mask)
791 {
792 m_channelTargetEffectMask |= mask;
793 break;
794 }
795 }
796 }
797 else if (m_auraScaleMask)
798 {
799 bool checkLvl = !m_UniqueTargetInfo.empty();
800 for (std::vector<TargetInfo>::iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end();)
801 {
802 // remove targets which did not pass min level check
803 if (m_auraScaleMask && ihit->effectMask == m_auraScaleMask)
804 {
805 // Do not check for selfcast
806 if (!ihit->scaleAura && ihit->targetGUID != m_caster->GetGUID())
807 {
808 ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.erase(ihit);
809 continue;
810 }
811 }
812
813 ++ihit;
814 }
815
816 if (checkLvl && m_UniqueTargetInfo.empty())
817 {
818 SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_LOWLEVEL);
819 finish(false);
820 }
821 }
822 }
823
824 if (m_targets.HasDst())
825 {
826 if (m_targets.HasTraj())
827 {
828 float speed = m_targets.GetSpeedXY();
829 if (speed > 0.0f)
830 m_delayMoment = uint64(std::floor(m_targets.GetDist2d() / speed * 1000.0f));
831 }
832 else if (m_spellInfo->Speed > 0.0f)
833 {
834 float dist = m_caster->GetDistance(*m_targets.GetDstPos());
835 if (!m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR9_SPECIAL_DELAY_CALCULATION))
836 m_delayMoment = uint64(std::floor(dist / m_spellInfo->Speed * 1000.0f));
837 else
838 m_delayMoment = uint64(m_spellInfo->Speed * 1000.0f);
839 }
840 }
841}
842
843void Spell::SelectEffectImplicitTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType, uint32& processedEffectMask)
844{
845 if (!targetType.GetTarget())
846 return;
847
848 uint32 effectMask = 1 << effIndex;
849 // set the same target list for all effects
850 // some spells appear to need this, however this requires more research
851 switch (targetType.GetSelectionCategory())
852 {
853 case TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_NEARBY:
854 case TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_CONE:
855 case TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_AREA:
856 // targets for effect already selected
857 if (effectMask & processedEffectMask)
858 return;
859 if (SpellEffectInfo const* _effect = GetEffect(effIndex))
860 {
861 // choose which targets we can select at once
862 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
863 {
864 //for (uint32 j = effIndex + 1; j < MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS; ++j)
865 if (!effect || effect->EffectIndex <= uint32(effIndex))
866 continue;
867 if (effect->IsEffect() &&
868 _effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == effect->TargetA.GetTarget() &&
869 _effect->TargetB.GetTarget() == effect->TargetB.GetTarget() &&
870 _effect->ImplicitTargetConditions == effect->ImplicitTargetConditions &&
871 _effect->CalcRadius(m_caster) == effect->CalcRadius(m_caster) &&
872 CheckScriptEffectImplicitTargets(effIndex, effect->EffectIndex))
873 {
874 effectMask |= 1 << effect->EffectIndex;
875 }
876 }
877 }
878 processedEffectMask |= effectMask;
879 break;
880 default:
881 break;
882 }
883
884 switch (targetType.GetSelectionCategory())
885 {
886 case TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_CHANNEL:
887 SelectImplicitChannelTargets(effIndex, targetType);
888 break;
889 case TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_NEARBY:
890 SelectImplicitNearbyTargets(effIndex, targetType, effectMask);
891 break;
892 case TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_CONE:
893 SelectImplicitConeTargets(effIndex, targetType, effectMask);
894 break;
895 case TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_AREA:
896 SelectImplicitAreaTargets(effIndex, targetType, effectMask);
897 break;
898 case TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_DEFAULT:
899 switch (targetType.GetObjectType())
900 {
901 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_SRC:
902 switch (targetType.GetReferenceType())
903 {
904 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_CASTER:
905 m_targets.SetSrc(*m_caster);
906 break;
907 default:
908 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectEffectImplicitTargets: received not implemented select target reference type for TARGET_TYPE_OBJECT_SRC");
909 break;
910 }
911 break;
912 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_DEST:
913 switch (targetType.GetReferenceType())
914 {
915 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_CASTER:
916 SelectImplicitCasterDestTargets(effIndex, targetType);
917 break;
918 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_TARGET:
919 SelectImplicitTargetDestTargets(effIndex, targetType);
920 break;
921 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_DEST:
922 SelectImplicitDestDestTargets(effIndex, targetType);
923 break;
924 default:
925 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectEffectImplicitTargets: received not implemented select target reference type for TARGET_TYPE_OBJECT_DEST");
926 break;
927 }
928 break;
929 default:
930 switch (targetType.GetReferenceType())
931 {
932 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_CASTER:
933 SelectImplicitCasterObjectTargets(effIndex, targetType);
934 break;
935 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_TARGET:
936 SelectImplicitTargetObjectTargets(effIndex, targetType);
937 break;
938 default:
939 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectEffectImplicitTargets: received not implemented select target reference type for TARGET_TYPE_OBJECT");
940 break;
941 }
942 break;
943 }
944 break;
945 case TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_NYI:
946 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "SPELL: target type %u, found in spellID %u, effect %u is not implemented yet!", m_spellInfo->Id, effIndex, targetType.GetTarget());
947 break;
948 default:
949 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectEffectImplicitTargets: received not implemented select target category");
950 break;
951 }
952}
953
954void Spell::SelectImplicitChannelTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType)
955{
956 if (targetType.GetReferenceType() != TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_CASTER)
957 {
958 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectImplicitChannelTargets: received not implemented target reference type");
959 return;
960 }
961
962 Spell* channeledSpell = m_originalCaster->GetCurrentSpell(CURRENT_CHANNELED_SPELL);
963 if (!channeledSpell)
964 {
965 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell::SelectImplicitChannelTargets: cannot find channel spell for spell ID %u, effect %u", m_spellInfo->Id, effIndex);
966 return;
967 }
968 switch (targetType.GetTarget())
969 {
970 case TARGET_UNIT_CHANNEL_TARGET:
971 {
972 WorldObject* target = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, m_originalCaster->GetChannelObjectGuid());
973 CallScriptObjectTargetSelectHandlers(target, effIndex, targetType);
974 // unit target may be no longer avalible - teleported out of map for example
975 if (target && target->ToUnit())
976 AddUnitTarget(target->ToUnit(), 1 << effIndex);
977 else
978 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "SPELL: cannot find channel spell target for spell ID %u, effect %u", m_spellInfo->Id, effIndex);
979 break;
980 }
981 case TARGET_DEST_CHANNEL_TARGET:
982 if (channeledSpell->m_targets.HasDst())
983 m_targets.SetDst(channeledSpell->m_targets);
984 else if (WorldObject* target = ObjectAccessor::GetWorldObject(*m_caster, m_originalCaster->GetChannelObjectGuid()))
985 {
986 CallScriptObjectTargetSelectHandlers(target, effIndex, targetType);
987 if (target)
988 m_targets.SetDst(*target);
989 }
990 else
991 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "SPELL: cannot find channel spell destination for spell ID %u, effect %u", m_spellInfo->Id, effIndex);
992 break;
993 case TARGET_DEST_CHANNEL_CASTER:
994 m_targets.SetDst(*channeledSpell->GetCaster());
995 break;
996 default:
997 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectImplicitChannelTargets: received not implemented target type");
998 break;
999 }
1000}
1001
1002void Spell::SelectImplicitNearbyTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType, uint32 effMask)
1003{
1004 if (targetType.GetReferenceType() != TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_CASTER)
1005 {
1006 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectImplicitNearbyTargets: received not implemented target reference type");
1007 return;
1008 }
1009
1010 SpellEffectInfo const* effect = GetEffect(effIndex);
1011 if (!effect)
1012 return;
1013
1014 float range = 0.0f;
1015 switch (targetType.GetCheckType())
1016 {
1017 case TARGET_CHECK_ENEMY:
1018 range = m_spellInfo->GetMaxRange(false, m_caster, this);
1019 break;
1020 case TARGET_CHECK_ALLY:
1021 case TARGET_CHECK_PARTY:
1022 case TARGET_CHECK_RAID:
1023 case TARGET_CHECK_RAID_CLASS:
1024 range = m_spellInfo->GetMaxRange(true, m_caster, this);
1025 break;
1026 case TARGET_CHECK_ENTRY:
1027 case TARGET_CHECK_DEFAULT:
1028 range = m_spellInfo->GetMaxRange(m_spellInfo->IsPositive(), m_caster, this);
1029 break;
1030 default:
1031 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectImplicitNearbyTargets: received not implemented selection check type");
1032 break;
1033 }
1034
1035 ConditionContainer* condList = effect->ImplicitTargetConditions;
1036
1037 // handle emergency case - try to use other provided targets if no conditions provided
1038 if (targetType.GetCheckType() == TARGET_CHECK_ENTRY && (!condList || condList->empty()))
1039 {
1040 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell::SelectImplicitNearbyTargets: no conditions entry for target with TARGET_CHECK_ENTRY of spell ID %u, effect %u - selecting default targets", m_spellInfo->Id, effIndex);
1041 switch (targetType.GetObjectType())
1042 {
1043 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ:
1044 if (m_spellInfo->RequiresSpellFocus)
1045 {
1046 if (focusObject)
1047 AddGOTarget(focusObject, effMask);
1048 return;
1049 }
1050 break;
1051 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_DEST:
1052 if (m_spellInfo->RequiresSpellFocus)
1053 {
1054 if (focusObject)
1055 m_targets.SetDst(*focusObject);
1056 return;
1057 }
1058 break;
1059 default:
1060 break;
1061 }
1062 }
1063
1064 WorldObject* target = SearchNearbyTarget(range, targetType.GetObjectType(), targetType.GetCheckType(), condList);
1065 if (!target)
1066 {
1067 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell::SelectImplicitNearbyTargets: cannot find nearby target for spell ID %u, effect %u", m_spellInfo->Id, effIndex);
1068 return;
1069 }
1070
1071 CallScriptObjectTargetSelectHandlers(target, effIndex, targetType);
1072 if (!target)
1073 {
1074 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell::SelectImplicitNearbyTargets: OnObjectTargetSelect script hook for spell Id %u set NULL target, effect %u", m_spellInfo->Id, effIndex);
1075 return;
1076 }
1077
1078 switch (targetType.GetObjectType())
1079 {
1080 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT:
1081 {
1082 if (Unit* unit = target->ToUnit())
1083 AddUnitTarget(unit, effMask, true, false);
1084 else
1085 {
1086 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell::SelectImplicitNearbyTargets: OnObjectTargetSelect script hook for spell Id %u set object of wrong type, expected unit, got %s, effect %u", m_spellInfo->Id, target->GetGUID().GetTypeName(), effMask);
1087 return;
1088 }
1089 break;
1090 }
1091 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ:
1092 if (GameObject* gobjTarget = target->ToGameObject())
1093 AddGOTarget(gobjTarget, effMask);
1094 else
1095 {
1096 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell::SelectImplicitNearbyTargets: OnObjectTargetSelect script hook for spell Id %u set object of wrong type, expected gameobject, got %s, effect %u", m_spellInfo->Id, target->GetGUID().GetTypeName(), effMask);
1097 return;
1098 }
1099 break;
1100 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_DEST:
1101 m_targets.SetDst(*target);
1102 break;
1103 default:
1104 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectImplicitNearbyTargets: received not implemented target object type");
1105 break;
1106 }
1107
1108 SelectImplicitChainTargets(effIndex, targetType, target, effMask);
1109}
1110
1111void Spell::SelectImplicitConeTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType, uint32 effMask)
1112{
1113 if (targetType.GetReferenceType() != TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_CASTER)
1114 {
1115 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectImplicitConeTargets: received not implemented target reference type");
1116 return;
1117 }
1118 std::list<WorldObject*> targets;
1119 SpellTargetObjectTypes objectType = targetType.GetObjectType();
1120 SpellTargetCheckTypes selectionType = targetType.GetCheckType();
1121 SpellEffectInfo const* effect = GetEffect(effIndex);
1122 if (!effect)
1123 return;
1124 ConditionContainer* condList = effect->ImplicitTargetConditions;
1125 float coneAngle = float(M_PI) / 2;
1126 float radius = effect->CalcRadius(m_caster) * m_spellValue->RadiusMod;
1127
1128 if (uint32 containerTypeMask = GetSearcherTypeMask(objectType, condList))
1129 {
1130 Trinity::WorldObjectSpellConeTargetCheck check(coneAngle, radius, m_caster, m_spellInfo, selectionType, condList);
1131 Trinity::WorldObjectListSearcher<Trinity::WorldObjectSpellConeTargetCheck> searcher(m_caster, targets, check, containerTypeMask);
1132 SearchTargets<Trinity::WorldObjectListSearcher<Trinity::WorldObjectSpellConeTargetCheck> >(searcher, containerTypeMask, m_caster, m_caster, radius);
1133
1134 CallScriptObjectAreaTargetSelectHandlers(targets, effIndex, targetType);
1135
1136 if (!targets.empty())
1137 {
1138 // Other special target selection goes here
1139 if (uint32 maxTargets = m_spellValue->MaxAffectedTargets)
1140 Trinity::Containers::RandomResizeList(targets, maxTargets);
1141
1142 for (std::list<WorldObject*>::iterator itr = targets.begin(); itr != targets.end(); ++itr)
1143 {
1144 if (Unit* unit = (*itr)->ToUnit())
1145 AddUnitTarget(unit, effMask, false);
1146 else if (GameObject* gObjTarget = (*itr)->ToGameObject())
1147 AddGOTarget(gObjTarget, effMask);
1148 }
1149 }
1150 }
1151}
1152
1153void Spell::SelectImplicitAreaTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType, uint32 effMask)
1154{
1155 Unit* referer = NULL;
1156 switch (targetType.GetReferenceType())
1157 {
1158 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_SRC:
1159 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_DEST:
1160 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_CASTER:
1161 referer = m_caster;
1162 break;
1163 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_TARGET:
1164 referer = m_targets.GetUnitTarget();
1165 break;
1166 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_LAST:
1167 {
1168 // find last added target for this effect
1169 for (std::vector<TargetInfo>::reverse_iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.rbegin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.rend(); ++ihit)
1170 {
1171 if (ihit->effectMask & (1<<effIndex))
1172 {
1173 referer = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, ihit->targetGUID);
1174 break;
1175 }
1176 }
1177 break;
1178 }
1179 default:
1180 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectImplicitAreaTargets: received not implemented target reference type");
1181 return;
1182 }
1183
1184 if (!referer)
1185 return;
1186
1187 Position const* center = NULL;
1188 switch (targetType.GetReferenceType())
1189 {
1190 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_SRC:
1191 center = m_targets.GetSrcPos();
1192 break;
1193 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_DEST:
1194 center = m_targets.GetDstPos();
1195 break;
1196 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_CASTER:
1197 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_TARGET:
1198 case TARGET_REFERENCE_TYPE_LAST:
1199 center = referer;
1200 break;
1201 default:
1202 ASSERT(false && "Spell::SelectImplicitAreaTargets: received not implemented target reference type");
1203 return;
1204 }
1205
1206 std::list<WorldObject*> targets;
1207 SpellEffectInfo const* effect = GetEffect(effIndex);
1208 if (!effect)
1209 return;
1210 float radius = effect->CalcRadius(m_caster) * m_spellValue->RadiusMod;
1211 SearchAreaTargets(targets, radius, center, referer, targetType.GetObjectType(), targetType.GetCheckType(), effect->ImplicitTargetConditions);
1212
1213 CallScriptObjectAreaTargetSelectHandlers(targets, effIndex, targetType);
1214
1215 if (!targets.empty())
1216 {
1217 // Other special target selection goes here
1218 if (uint32 maxTargets = m_spellValue->MaxAffectedTargets)
1219 Trinity::Containers::RandomResizeList(targets, maxTargets);
1220
1221 for (std::list<WorldObject*>::iterator itr = targets.begin(); itr != targets.end(); ++itr)
1222 {
1223 if (Unit* unit = (*itr)->ToUnit())
1224 AddUnitTarget(unit, effMask, false, true, center);
1225 else if (GameObject* gObjTarget = (*itr)->ToGameObject())
1226 AddGOTarget(gObjTarget, effMask);
1227 }
1228 }
1229}
1230
1231void Spell::SelectImplicitCasterDestTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType)
1232{
1233 SpellDestination dest(*m_caster);
1234
1235 switch (targetType.GetTarget())
1236 {
1237 case TARGET_DEST_CASTER:
1238 break;
1239 case TARGET_DEST_HOME:
1240 if (Player* playerCaster = m_caster->ToPlayer())
1241 dest = SpellDestination(playerCaster->m_homebindX, playerCaster->m_homebindY, playerCaster->m_homebindZ, playerCaster->GetOrientation(), playerCaster->m_homebindMapId);
1242 break;
1243 case TARGET_DEST_DB:
1244 if (SpellTargetPosition const* st = sSpellMgr->GetSpellTargetPosition(m_spellInfo->Id, effIndex))
1245 {
1246 /// @todo fix this check
1247 if (HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_TELEPORT_UNITS) || HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_BIND))
1248 dest = SpellDestination(st->target_X, st->target_Y, st->target_Z, st->target_Orientation, (int32)st->target_mapId);
1249 else if (st->target_mapId == m_caster->GetMapId())
1250 dest = SpellDestination(st->target_X, st->target_Y, st->target_Z, st->target_Orientation);
1251 }
1252 else
1253 {
1254 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "SPELL: unknown target coordinates for spell ID %u", m_spellInfo->Id);
1255 if (WorldObject* target = m_targets.GetObjectTarget())
1256 dest = SpellDestination(*target);
1257 }
1258 break;
1259 case TARGET_DEST_CASTER_FISHING:
1260 {
1261 float minDist = m_spellInfo->GetMinRange(true);
1262 float maxDist = m_spellInfo->GetMaxRange(true);
1263 float dist = frand(minDist, maxDist);
1264 float x, y, z;
1265 float angle = float(rand_norm()) * static_cast<float>(M_PI * 35.0f / 180.0f) - static_cast<float>(M_PI * 17.5f / 180.0f);
1266 m_caster->GetClosePoint(x, y, z, DEFAULT_WORLD_OBJECT_SIZE, dist, angle);
1267
1268 float ground = m_caster->GetMap()->GetHeight(m_caster->GetPhaseMask(), x, y, z, true, 50.0f);
1269 float liquidLevel = VMAP_INVALID_HEIGHT_VALUE;
1270 LiquidData liquidData;
1271 if (m_caster->GetMap()->getLiquidStatus(x, y, z, MAP_ALL_LIQUIDS, &liquidData))
1272 liquidLevel = liquidData.level;
1273
1274 if (liquidLevel <= ground) // When there is no liquid Map::GetWaterOrGroundLevel returns ground level
1275 {
1276 SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_NOT_HERE);
1277 SendChannelUpdate(0);
1278 finish(false);
1279 return;
1280 }
1281
1282 if (ground + 0.75 > liquidLevel)
1283 {
1284 SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_TOO_SHALLOW);
1285 SendChannelUpdate(0);
1286 finish(false);
1287 return;
1288 }
1289
1290 dest = SpellDestination(x, y, liquidLevel, m_caster->GetOrientation());
1291 break;
1292 }
1293 default:
1294 {
1295 if (SpellEffectInfo const* effect = GetEffect(effIndex))
1296 {
1297 float dist;
1298 float angle = targetType.CalcDirectionAngle();
1299 float objSize = m_caster->GetObjectSize();
1300 if (targetType.GetTarget() == TARGET_DEST_CASTER_SUMMON)
1301 dist = PET_FOLLOW_DIST;
1302 else
1303 dist = effect->CalcRadius(m_caster);
1304
1305 if (dist < objSize)
1306 dist = objSize;
1307 else if (targetType.GetTarget() == TARGET_DEST_CASTER_RANDOM)
1308 dist = objSize + (dist - objSize) * float(rand_norm());
1309
1310 Position pos = dest._position;
1311 m_caster->MovePositionToFirstCollision(pos, dist, angle);
1312
1313 dest.Relocate(pos);
1314 }
1315 break;
1316 }
1317 }
1318
1319 CallScriptDestinationTargetSelectHandlers(dest, effIndex, targetType);
1320 m_targets.SetDst(dest);
1321}
1322
1323void Spell::SelectImplicitTargetDestTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType)
1324{
1325 ASSERT(m_targets.GetObjectTarget() && "Spell::SelectImplicitTargetDestTargets - no explicit object target available!");
1326 WorldObject* target = m_targets.GetObjectTarget();
1327
1328 SpellDestination dest(*target);
1329
1330 switch (targetType.GetTarget())
1331 {
1332 case TARGET_DEST_TARGET_ENEMY:
1333 case TARGET_DEST_TARGET_ANY:
1334 break;
1335 default:
1336 {
1337 if (SpellEffectInfo const* effect = GetEffect(effIndex))
1338 {
1339 float angle = targetType.CalcDirectionAngle();
1340 float objSize = target->GetObjectSize();
1341 float dist = effect->CalcRadius(m_caster);
1342 if (dist < objSize)
1343 dist = objSize;
1344 else if (targetType.GetTarget() == TARGET_DEST_TARGET_RANDOM)
1345 dist = objSize + (dist - objSize) * float(rand_norm());
1346
1347 Position pos = dest._position;
1348 target->MovePositionToFirstCollision(pos, dist, angle);
1349
1350 dest.Relocate(pos);
1351 }
1352 break;
1353 }
1354 }
1355
1356 CallScriptDestinationTargetSelectHandlers(dest, effIndex, targetType);
1357 m_targets.SetDst(dest);
1358}
1359
1360void Spell::SelectImplicitDestDestTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType)
1361{
1362 // set destination to caster if no dest provided
1363 // can only happen if previous destination target could not be set for some reason
1364 // (not found nearby target, or channel target for example
1365 // maybe we should abort the spell in such case?
1366 CheckDst();
1367
1368 SpellDestination dest(*m_targets.GetDst());
1369
1370 switch (targetType.GetTarget())
1371 {
1372 case TARGET_DEST_DYNOBJ_ENEMY:
1373 case TARGET_DEST_DYNOBJ_ALLY:
1374 case TARGET_DEST_DYNOBJ_NONE:
1375 case TARGET_DEST_DEST:
1376 return;
1377 case TARGET_DEST_TRAJ:
1378 SelectImplicitTrajTargets(effIndex);
1379 return;
1380 default:
1381 {
1382 if (SpellEffectInfo const* effect = GetEffect(effIndex))
1383 {
1384 float angle = targetType.CalcDirectionAngle();
1385 float dist = effect->CalcRadius(m_caster);
1386 if (targetType.GetTarget() == TARGET_DEST_DEST_RANDOM)
1387 dist *= float(rand_norm());
1388
1389 Position pos = dest._position;
1390 m_caster->MovePositionToFirstCollision(pos, dist, angle);
1391
1392 dest.Relocate(pos);
1393 }
1394 break;
1395 }
1396 }
1397
1398 CallScriptDestinationTargetSelectHandlers(dest, effIndex, targetType);
1399 m_targets.ModDst(dest);
1400}
1401
1402void Spell::SelectImplicitCasterObjectTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType)
1403{
1404 WorldObject* target = NULL;
1405 bool checkIfValid = true;
1406
1407 switch (targetType.GetTarget())
1408 {
1409 case TARGET_UNIT_CASTER:
1410 target = m_caster;
1411 checkIfValid = false;
1412 break;
1413 case TARGET_UNIT_MASTER:
1414 target = m_caster->GetCharmerOrOwner();
1415 break;
1416 case TARGET_UNIT_PET:
1417 target = m_caster->GetGuardianPet();
1418 break;
1419 case TARGET_UNIT_SUMMONER:
1420 if (m_caster->IsSummon())
1421 target = m_caster->ToTempSummon()->GetSummoner();
1422 break;
1423 case TARGET_UNIT_VEHICLE:
1424 target = m_caster->GetVehicleBase();
1425 break;
1426 case TARGET_UNIT_PASSENGER_0:
1427 case TARGET_UNIT_PASSENGER_1:
1428 case TARGET_UNIT_PASSENGER_2:
1429 case TARGET_UNIT_PASSENGER_3:
1430 case TARGET_UNIT_PASSENGER_4:
1431 case TARGET_UNIT_PASSENGER_5:
1432 case TARGET_UNIT_PASSENGER_6:
1433 case TARGET_UNIT_PASSENGER_7:
1434 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && m_caster->IsVehicle())
1435 target = m_caster->GetVehicleKit()->GetPassenger(targetType.GetTarget() - TARGET_UNIT_PASSENGER_0);
1436 break;
1437 default:
1438 break;
1439 }
1440
1441 CallScriptObjectTargetSelectHandlers(target, effIndex, targetType);
1442
1443 if (target && target->ToUnit())
1444 AddUnitTarget(target->ToUnit(), 1 << effIndex, checkIfValid);
1445}
1446
1447void Spell::SelectImplicitTargetObjectTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType)
1448{
1449 ASSERT((m_targets.GetObjectTarget() || m_targets.GetItemTarget()) && "Spell::SelectImplicitTargetObjectTargets - no explicit object or item target available!");
1450
1451 WorldObject* target = m_targets.GetObjectTarget();
1452
1453 CallScriptObjectTargetSelectHandlers(target, effIndex, targetType);
1454
1455 if (target)
1456 {
1457 if (Unit* unit = target->ToUnit())
1458 AddUnitTarget(unit, 1 << effIndex, true, false);
1459 else if (GameObject* gobj = target->ToGameObject())
1460 AddGOTarget(gobj, 1 << effIndex);
1461
1462 SelectImplicitChainTargets(effIndex, targetType, target, 1 << effIndex);
1463 }
1464 // Script hook can remove object target and we would wrongly land here
1465 else if (Item* item = m_targets.GetItemTarget())
1466 AddItemTarget(item, 1 << effIndex);
1467}
1468
1469void Spell::SelectImplicitChainTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType, WorldObject* target, uint32 effMask)
1470{
1471 SpellEffectInfo const* effect = GetEffect(effIndex);
1472 if (!effect)
1473 return;
1474
1475 uint32 maxTargets = effect->ChainTargets;
1476 if (Player* modOwner = m_caster->GetSpellModOwner())
1477 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_JUMP_TARGETS, maxTargets, this);
1478
1479 if (maxTargets > 1)
1480 {
1481 // mark damage multipliers as used
1482 for (SpellEffectInfo const* eff : GetEffects())
1483 if (eff && (effMask & (1 << eff->EffectIndex)))
1484 m_damageMultipliers[eff->EffectIndex] = 1.0f;
1485 m_applyMultiplierMask |= effMask;
1486
1487 std::list<WorldObject*> targets;
1488 SearchChainTargets(targets, maxTargets - 1, target, targetType.GetObjectType(), targetType.GetCheckType()
1489 , effect->ImplicitTargetConditions, targetType.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_TARGET_CHAINHEAL_ALLY);
1490
1491 // Chain primary target is added earlier
1492 CallScriptObjectAreaTargetSelectHandlers(targets, effIndex, targetType);
1493
1494 for (std::list<WorldObject*>::iterator itr = targets.begin(); itr != targets.end(); ++itr)
1495 if (Unit* unit = (*itr)->ToUnit())
1496 AddUnitTarget(unit, effMask, false);
1497 }
1498}
1499
1500float tangent(float x)
1501{
1502 x = std::tan(x);
1503 //if (x < std::numeric_limits<float>::max() && x > -std::numeric_limits<float>::max()) return x;
1504 //if (x >= std::numeric_limits<float>::max()) return std::numeric_limits<float>::max();
1505 //if (x <= -std::numeric_limits<float>::max()) return -std::numeric_limits<float>::max();
1506 if (x < 100000.0f && x > -100000.0f) return x;
1507 if (x >= 100000.0f) return 100000.0f;
1508 if (x <= 100000.0f) return -100000.0f;
1509 return 0.0f;
1510}
1511
1512#define DEBUG_TRAJ(a) //a
1513
1514void Spell::SelectImplicitTrajTargets(SpellEffIndex effIndex)
1515{
1516 if (!m_targets.HasTraj())
1517 return;
1518
1519 float dist2d = m_targets.GetDist2d();
1520 if (!dist2d)
1521 return;
1522
1523 float srcToDestDelta = m_targets.GetDstPos()->m_positionZ - m_targets.GetSrcPos()->m_positionZ;
1524
1525 std::list<WorldObject*> targets;
1526 Trinity::WorldObjectSpellTrajTargetCheck check(dist2d, m_targets.GetSrcPos(), m_caster, m_spellInfo);
1527 Trinity::WorldObjectListSearcher<Trinity::WorldObjectSpellTrajTargetCheck> searcher(m_caster, targets, check, GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_ALL);
1528 SearchTargets<Trinity::WorldObjectListSearcher<Trinity::WorldObjectSpellTrajTargetCheck> > (searcher, GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_ALL, m_caster, m_targets.GetSrcPos(), dist2d);
1529 if (targets.empty())
1530 return;
1531
1532 targets.sort(Trinity::ObjectDistanceOrderPred(m_caster));
1533
1534 float b = tangent(m_targets.GetPitch());
1535 float a = (srcToDestDelta - dist2d * b) / (dist2d * dist2d);
1536 if (a > -0.0001f)
1537 a = 0;
1538 DEBUG_TRAJ(TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Spell::SelectTrajTargets: a %f b %f", a, b);)
1539
1540 float bestDist = m_spellInfo->GetMaxRange(false);
1541
1542 std::list<WorldObject*>::const_iterator itr = targets.begin();
1543 for (; itr != targets.end(); ++itr)
1544 {
1545 if (!m_caster->HasInLine(*itr, 5.0f))
1546 continue;
1547
1548 if (m_spellInfo->CheckTarget(m_caster, *itr, true) != SPELL_CAST_OK)
1549 continue;
1550
1551 if (Unit* unit = (*itr)->ToUnit())
1552 {
1553 if (m_caster == *itr || m_caster->IsOnVehicle(unit) || unit->GetVehicle())
1554 continue;
1555
1556 if (Creature* creatureTarget = unit->ToCreature())
1557 {
1558 if (!(creatureTarget->GetCreatureTemplate()->type_flags & CREATURE_TYPEFLAGS_PROJECTILE_COLLISION))
1559 continue;
1560 }
1561 }
1562
1563 const float size = std::max((*itr)->GetObjectSize() * 0.7f, 1.0f); // 1/sqrt(3)
1564 /// @todo all calculation should be based on src instead of m_caster
1565 const float objDist2d = m_targets.GetSrcPos()->GetExactDist2d(*itr) * std::cos(m_targets.GetSrcPos()->GetRelativeAngle(*itr));
1566 const float dz = (*itr)->GetPositionZ() - m_targets.GetSrcPos()->m_positionZ;
1567
1568 DEBUG_TRAJ(TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Spell::SelectTrajTargets: check %u, dist between %f %f, height between %f %f.", (*itr)->GetEntry(), objDist2d - size, objDist2d + size, dz - size, dz + size);)
1569
1570 float dist = objDist2d - size;
1571 float height = dist * (a * dist + b);
1572 DEBUG_TRAJ(TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Spell::SelectTrajTargets: dist %f, height %f.", dist, height);)
1573 if (dist < bestDist && height < dz + size && height > dz - size)
1574 {
1575 bestDist = dist > 0 ? dist : 0;
1576 break;
1577 }
1578
1579#define CHECK_DIST {\
1580 DEBUG_TRAJ(TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Spell::SelectTrajTargets: dist %f, height %f.", dist, height);)\
1581 if (dist > bestDist)\
1582 continue;\
1583 if (dist < objDist2d + size && dist > objDist2d - size)\
1584 {\
1585 bestDist = dist;\
1586 break;\
1587 }\
1588 }
1589
1590 if (!a)
1591 {
1592 height = dz - size;
1593 dist = height / b;
1594 CHECK_DIST;
1595
1596 height = dz + size;
1597 dist = height / b;
1598 CHECK_DIST;
1599
1600 continue;
1601 }
1602
1603 height = dz - size;
1604 float sqrt1 = b * b + 4 * a * height;
1605 if (sqrt1 > 0)
1606 {
1607 sqrt1 = std::sqrt(sqrt1);
1608 dist = (sqrt1 - b) / (2 * a);
1609 CHECK_DIST;
1610 }
1611
1612 height = dz + size;
1613 float sqrt2 = b * b + 4 * a * height;
1614 if (sqrt2 > 0)
1615 {
1616 sqrt2 = std::sqrt(sqrt2);
1617 dist = (sqrt2 - b) / (2 * a);
1618 CHECK_DIST;
1619
1620 dist = (-sqrt2 - b) / (2 * a);
1621 CHECK_DIST;
1622 }
1623
1624 if (sqrt1 > 0)
1625 {
1626 dist = (-sqrt1 - b) / (2 * a);
1627 CHECK_DIST;
1628 }
1629 }
1630
1631 if (m_targets.GetSrcPos()->GetExactDist2d(m_targets.GetDstPos()) > bestDist)
1632 {
1633 float x = m_targets.GetSrcPos()->m_positionX + std::cos(m_caster->GetOrientation()) * bestDist;
1634 float y = m_targets.GetSrcPos()->m_positionY + std::sin(m_caster->GetOrientation()) * bestDist;
1635 float z = m_targets.GetSrcPos()->m_positionZ + bestDist * (a * bestDist + b);
1636
1637 if (itr != targets.end())
1638 {
1639 float distSq = (*itr)->GetExactDistSq(x, y, z);
1640 float sizeSq = (*itr)->GetObjectSize();
1641 sizeSq *= sizeSq;
1642 DEBUG_TRAJ(TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Initial %f %f %f %f %f", x, y, z, distSq, sizeSq);)
1643 if (distSq > sizeSq)
1644 {
1645 float factor = 1 - std::sqrt(sizeSq / distSq);
1646 x += factor * ((*itr)->GetPositionX() - x);
1647 y += factor * ((*itr)->GetPositionY() - y);
1648 z += factor * ((*itr)->GetPositionZ() - z);
1649
1650 distSq = (*itr)->GetExactDistSq(x, y, z);
1651 DEBUG_TRAJ(TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Initial %f %f %f %f %f", x, y, z, distSq, sizeSq);)
1652 }
1653 }
1654
1655 Position trajDst;
1656 trajDst.Relocate(x, y, z, m_caster->GetOrientation());
1657 SpellDestination dest(*m_targets.GetDst());
1658 dest.Relocate(trajDst);
1659
1660 CallScriptDestinationTargetSelectHandlers(dest, effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo(TARGET_DEST_TRAJ));
1661 m_targets.ModDst(dest);
1662 }
1663
1664 if (Vehicle* veh = m_caster->GetVehicleKit())
1665 veh->SetLastShootPos(*m_targets.GetDstPos());
1666}
1667
1668void Spell::SelectEffectTypeImplicitTargets(uint32 effIndex)
1669{
1670 // special case for SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_RAF_FRIEND and SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_PLAYER
1671 /// @todo this is a workaround - target shouldn't be stored in target map for those spells
1672 SpellEffectInfo const* effect = GetEffect(effIndex);
1673 if (!effect)
1674 return;
1675 switch (effect->Effect)
1676 {
1677 case SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_RAF_FRIEND:
1678 case SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_PLAYER:
1679 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && !m_caster->GetTarget().IsEmpty())
1680 {
1681 WorldObject* target = ObjectAccessor::FindPlayer(m_caster->GetTarget());
1682
1683 CallScriptObjectTargetSelectHandlers(target, SpellEffIndex(effIndex), SpellImplicitTargetInfo());
1684
1685 if (target && target->ToPlayer())
1686 AddUnitTarget(target->ToUnit(), 1 << effIndex, false);
1687 }
1688 return;
1689 default:
1690 break;
1691 }
1692
1693 // select spell implicit targets based on effect type
1694 if (!effect->GetImplicitTargetType())
1695 return;
1696
1697 uint32 targetMask = effect->GetMissingTargetMask();
1698
1699 if (!targetMask)
1700 return;
1701
1702 WorldObject* target = NULL;
1703
1704 switch (effect->GetImplicitTargetType())
1705 {
1706 // add explicit object target or self to the target map
1707 case EFFECT_IMPLICIT_TARGET_EXPLICIT:
1708 // player which not released his spirit is Unit, but target flag for it is TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK
1709 if (targetMask & (TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK | TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK))
1710 {
1711 if (Unit* unit = m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
1712 target = unit;
1713 else if (targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_CORPSE_MASK)
1714 {
1715 if (Corpse* corpseTarget = m_targets.GetCorpseTarget())
1716 {
1717 /// @todo this is a workaround - corpses should be added to spell target map too, but we can't do that so we add owner instead
1718 if (Player* owner = ObjectAccessor::FindPlayer(corpseTarget->GetOwnerGUID()))
1719 target = owner;
1720 }
1721 }
1722 else //if (targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK)
1723 target = m_caster;
1724 }
1725 if (targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_ITEM_MASK)
1726 {
1727 if (Item* item = m_targets.GetItemTarget())
1728 AddItemTarget(item, 1 << effIndex);
1729 return;
1730 }
1731 if (targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_GAMEOBJECT_MASK)
1732 target = m_targets.GetGOTarget();
1733 break;
1734 // add self to the target map
1735 case EFFECT_IMPLICIT_TARGET_CASTER:
1736 if (targetMask & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT_MASK)
1737 target = m_caster;
1738 break;
1739 default:
1740 break;
1741 }
1742
1743 CallScriptObjectTargetSelectHandlers(target, SpellEffIndex(effIndex), SpellImplicitTargetInfo());
1744
1745 if (target)
1746 {
1747 if (target->ToUnit())
1748 AddUnitTarget(target->ToUnit(), 1 << effIndex, false);
1749 else if (target->ToGameObject())
1750 AddGOTarget(target->ToGameObject(), 1 << effIndex);
1751 }
1752}
1753
1754uint32 Spell::GetSearcherTypeMask(SpellTargetObjectTypes objType, ConditionContainer* condList)
1755{
1756 // this function selects which containers need to be searched for spell target
1757 uint32 retMask = GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_ALL;
1758
1759 // filter searchers based on searched object type
1760 switch (objType)
1761 {
1762 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT:
1763 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT_AND_DEST:
1764 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_CORPSE:
1765 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_CORPSE_ENEMY:
1766 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_CORPSE_ALLY:
1767 retMask &= GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_PLAYER | GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_CORPSE | GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_CREATURE;
1768 break;
1769 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ:
1770 case TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_GOBJ_ITEM:
1771 retMask &= GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_GAMEOBJECT;
1772 break;
1773 default:
1774 break;
1775 }
1776 if (!m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_CAN_TARGET_DEAD))
1777 retMask &= ~GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_CORPSE;
1778 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_ONLY_TARGET_PLAYERS))
1779 retMask &= GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_CORPSE | GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_PLAYER;
1780 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_ONLY_TARGET_GHOSTS))
1781 retMask &= GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_PLAYER;
1782
1783 if (condList)
1784 retMask &= sConditionMgr->GetSearcherTypeMaskForConditionList(*condList);
1785 return retMask;
1786}
1787
1788template<class SEARCHER>
1789void Spell::SearchTargets(SEARCHER& searcher, uint32 containerMask, Unit* referer, Position const* pos, float radius)
1790{
1791 if (!containerMask)
1792 return;
1793
1794 // search world and grid for possible targets
1795 bool searchInGrid = (containerMask & (GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_CREATURE | GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_GAMEOBJECT)) != 0;
1796 bool searchInWorld = (containerMask & (GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_CREATURE | GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_PLAYER | GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_CORPSE)) != 0;
1797 if (searchInGrid || searchInWorld)
1798 {
1799 float x, y;
1800 x = pos->GetPositionX();
1801 y = pos->GetPositionY();
1802
1803 CellCoord p(Trinity::ComputeCellCoord(x, y));
1804 Cell cell(p);
1805 cell.SetNoCreate();
1806
1807 Map& map = *(referer->GetMap());
1808
1809 if (searchInWorld)
1810 {
1811 TypeContainerVisitor<SEARCHER, WorldTypeMapContainer> world_object_notifier(searcher);
1812 cell.Visit(p, world_object_notifier, map, radius, x, y);
1813 }
1814 if (searchInGrid)
1815 {
1816 TypeContainerVisitor<SEARCHER, GridTypeMapContainer > grid_object_notifier(searcher);
1817 cell.Visit(p, grid_object_notifier, map, radius, x, y);
1818 }
1819 }
1820}
1821
1822WorldObject* Spell::SearchNearbyTarget(float range, SpellTargetObjectTypes objectType, SpellTargetCheckTypes selectionType, ConditionContainer* condList)
1823{
1824 WorldObject* target = NULL;
1825 uint32 containerTypeMask = GetSearcherTypeMask(objectType, condList);
1826 if (!containerTypeMask)
1827 return NULL;
1828 Trinity::WorldObjectSpellNearbyTargetCheck check(range, m_caster, m_spellInfo, selectionType, condList);
1829 Trinity::WorldObjectLastSearcher<Trinity::WorldObjectSpellNearbyTargetCheck> searcher(m_caster, target, check, containerTypeMask);
1830 SearchTargets<Trinity::WorldObjectLastSearcher<Trinity::WorldObjectSpellNearbyTargetCheck> > (searcher, containerTypeMask, m_caster, m_caster, range);
1831 return target;
1832}
1833
1834void Spell::SearchAreaTargets(std::list<WorldObject*>& targets, float range, Position const* position, Unit* referer, SpellTargetObjectTypes objectType, SpellTargetCheckTypes selectionType, ConditionContainer* condList)
1835{
1836 uint32 containerTypeMask = GetSearcherTypeMask(objectType, condList);
1837 if (!containerTypeMask)
1838 return;
1839 Trinity::WorldObjectSpellAreaTargetCheck check(range, position, m_caster, referer, m_spellInfo, selectionType, condList);
1840 Trinity::WorldObjectListSearcher<Trinity::WorldObjectSpellAreaTargetCheck> searcher(m_caster, targets, check, containerTypeMask);
1841 SearchTargets<Trinity::WorldObjectListSearcher<Trinity::WorldObjectSpellAreaTargetCheck> > (searcher, containerTypeMask, m_caster, position, range);
1842}
1843
1844void Spell::SearchChainTargets(std::list<WorldObject*>& targets, uint32 chainTargets, WorldObject* target, SpellTargetObjectTypes objectType, SpellTargetCheckTypes selectType, ConditionContainer* condList, bool isChainHeal)
1845{
1846 // max dist for jump target selection
1847 float jumpRadius = 0.0f;
1848 switch (m_spellInfo->DmgClass)
1849 {
1850 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_RANGED:
1851 // 7.5y for multi shot
1852 jumpRadius = 7.5f;
1853 break;
1854 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MELEE:
1855 // 5y for swipe, cleave and similar
1856 jumpRadius = 5.0f;
1857 break;
1858 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_NONE:
1859 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MAGIC:
1860 // 12.5y for chain heal spell since 3.2 patch
1861 if (isChainHeal)
1862 jumpRadius = 12.5f;
1863 // 10y as default for magic chain spells
1864 else
1865 jumpRadius = 10.0f;
1866 break;
1867 }
1868
1869 if (Player* modOwner = m_caster->GetSpellModOwner())
1870 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_JUMP_DISTANCE, jumpRadius, this);
1871
1872 // chain lightning/heal spells and similar - allow to jump at larger distance and go out of los
1873 bool isBouncingFar = (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR4_AREA_TARGET_CHAIN)
1874 || m_spellInfo->DmgClass == SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_NONE
1875 || m_spellInfo->DmgClass == SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MAGIC);
1876
1877 // max dist which spell can reach
1878 float searchRadius = jumpRadius;
1879 if (isBouncingFar)
1880 searchRadius *= chainTargets;
1881
1882 std::list<WorldObject*> tempTargets;
1883 SearchAreaTargets(tempTargets, searchRadius, target, m_caster, objectType, selectType, condList);
1884 tempTargets.remove(target);
1885
1886 // remove targets which are always invalid for chain spells
1887 // for some spells allow only chain targets in front of caster (swipe for example)
1888 if (!isBouncingFar)
1889 {
1890 for (std::list<WorldObject*>::iterator itr = tempTargets.begin(); itr != tempTargets.end();)
1891 {
1892 std::list<WorldObject*>::iterator checkItr = itr++;
1893 if (!m_caster->HasInArc(static_cast<float>(M_PI), *checkItr))
1894 tempTargets.erase(checkItr);
1895 }
1896 }
1897
1898 while (chainTargets)
1899 {
1900 // try to get unit for next chain jump
1901 std::list<WorldObject*>::iterator foundItr = tempTargets.end();
1902 // get unit with highest hp deficit in dist
1903 if (isChainHeal)
1904 {
1905 uint32 maxHPDeficit = 0;
1906 for (std::list<WorldObject*>::iterator itr = tempTargets.begin(); itr != tempTargets.end(); ++itr)
1907 {
1908 if (Unit* unit = (*itr)->ToUnit())
1909 {
1910 uint32 deficit = unit->GetMaxHealth() - unit->GetHealth();
1911 if ((deficit > maxHPDeficit || foundItr == tempTargets.end()) && target->IsWithinDist(unit, jumpRadius) && target->IsWithinLOSInMap(unit))
1912 {
1913 foundItr = itr;
1914 maxHPDeficit = deficit;
1915 }
1916 }
1917 }
1918 }
1919 // get closest object
1920 else
1921 {
1922 for (std::list<WorldObject*>::iterator itr = tempTargets.begin(); itr != tempTargets.end(); ++itr)
1923 {
1924 if (foundItr == tempTargets.end())
1925 {
1926 if ((!isBouncingFar || target->IsWithinDist(*itr, jumpRadius)) && target->IsWithinLOSInMap(*itr))
1927 foundItr = itr;
1928 }
1929 else if (target->GetDistanceOrder(*itr, *foundItr) && target->IsWithinLOSInMap(*itr))
1930 foundItr = itr;
1931 }
1932 }
1933 // not found any valid target - chain ends
1934 if (foundItr == tempTargets.end())
1935 break;
1936 target = *foundItr;
1937 tempTargets.erase(foundItr);
1938 targets.push_back(target);
1939 --chainTargets;
1940 }
1941}
1942
1943GameObject* Spell::SearchSpellFocus()
1944{
1945 GameObject* focus = NULL;
1946 Trinity::GameObjectFocusCheck check(m_caster, m_spellInfo->RequiresSpellFocus);
1947 Trinity::GameObjectSearcher<Trinity::GameObjectFocusCheck> searcher(m_caster, focus, check);
1948 SearchTargets<Trinity::GameObjectSearcher<Trinity::GameObjectFocusCheck> > (searcher, GRID_MAP_TYPE_MASK_GAMEOBJECT, m_caster, m_caster, m_caster->GetVisibilityRange());
1949 return focus;
1950}
1951
1952void Spell::prepareDataForTriggerSystem(AuraEffect const* /*triggeredByAura*/)
1953{
1954 //==========================================================================================
1955 // Now fill data for trigger system, need know:
1956 // can spell trigger another or not (m_canTrigger)
1957 // Create base triggers flags for Attacker and Victim (m_procAttacker, m_procVictim and m_procEx)
1958 //==========================================================================================
1959
1960 m_procVictim = m_procAttacker = 0;
1961 // Get data for type of attack and fill base info for trigger
1962 switch (m_spellInfo->DmgClass)
1963 {
1964 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MELEE:
1965 m_procAttacker = PROC_FLAG_DONE_SPELL_MELEE_DMG_CLASS;
1966 if (m_attackType == OFF_ATTACK)
1967 m_procAttacker |= PROC_FLAG_DONE_OFFHAND_ATTACK;
1968 else
1969 m_procAttacker |= PROC_FLAG_DONE_MAINHAND_ATTACK;
1970 m_procVictim = PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_SPELL_MELEE_DMG_CLASS;
1971 break;
1972 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_RANGED:
1973 // Auto attack
1974 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_AUTOREPEAT_FLAG))
1975 {
1976 m_procAttacker = PROC_FLAG_DONE_RANGED_AUTO_ATTACK;
1977 m_procVictim = PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_RANGED_AUTO_ATTACK;
1978 }
1979 else // Ranged spell attack
1980 {
1981 m_procAttacker = PROC_FLAG_DONE_SPELL_RANGED_DMG_CLASS;
1982 m_procVictim = PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_SPELL_RANGED_DMG_CLASS;
1983 }
1984 break;
1985 default:
1986 if (m_spellInfo->EquippedItemClass == ITEM_CLASS_WEAPON &&
1987 m_spellInfo->EquippedItemSubClassMask & (1<<ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_WAND)
1988 && m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_AUTOREPEAT_FLAG)) // Wands auto attack
1989 {
1990 m_procAttacker = PROC_FLAG_DONE_RANGED_AUTO_ATTACK;
1991 m_procVictim = PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_RANGED_AUTO_ATTACK;
1992 }
1993 // For other spells trigger procflags are set in Spell::DoAllEffectOnTarget
1994 // Because spell positivity is dependant on target
1995 }
1996 m_procEx = PROC_EX_NONE;
1997
1998 // Hunter trap spells - activation proc for Lock and Load, Entrapment and Misdirection
1999 if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_HUNTER &&
2000 (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x18 || // Freezing and Frost Trap, Freezing Arrow
2001 m_spellInfo->Id == 57879 || // Snake Trap - done this way to avoid double proc
2002 m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags[2] & 0x00024000)) // Explosive and Immolation Trap
2003 {
2004 m_procAttacker |= PROC_FLAG_DONE_TRAP_ACTIVATION;
2005 }
2006
2007 /* Effects which are result of aura proc from triggered spell cannot proc
2008 to prevent chain proc of these spells */
2009
2010 // Hellfire Effect - trigger as DOT
2011 if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_WARLOCK && m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x00000040)
2012 {
2013 m_procAttacker = PROC_FLAG_DONE_PERIODIC;
2014 m_procVictim = PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_PERIODIC;
2015 }
2016
2017 // Ranged autorepeat attack is set as triggered spell - ignore it
2018 if (!(m_procAttacker & PROC_FLAG_DONE_RANGED_AUTO_ATTACK))
2019 {
2020 if (_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DISALLOW_PROC_EVENTS &&
2021 (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_TRIGGERED_CAN_TRIGGER_PROC) ||
2022 m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_TRIGGERED_CAN_TRIGGER_PROC_2)))
2023 m_procEx |= PROC_EX_INTERNAL_CANT_PROC;
2024 else if (_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DISALLOW_PROC_EVENTS)
2025 m_procEx |= PROC_EX_INTERNAL_TRIGGERED;
2026 }
2027 // Totem casts require spellfamilymask defined in spell_proc_event to proc
2028 if (m_originalCaster && m_caster != m_originalCaster && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && m_caster->IsTotem() && m_caster->IsControlledByPlayer())
2029 m_procEx |= PROC_EX_INTERNAL_REQ_FAMILY;
2030}
2031
2032void Spell::CleanupTargetList()
2033{
2034 m_UniqueTargetInfo.clear();
2035 m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.clear();
2036 m_UniqueItemInfo.clear();
2037 m_delayMoment = 0;
2038}
2039
2040void Spell::AddUnitTarget(Unit* target, uint32 effectMask, bool checkIfValid /*= true*/, bool implicit /*= true*/, Position const* losPosition /*= nullptr*/)
2041{
2042 uint32 validEffectMask = 0;
2043 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
2044 if (effect && (effectMask & (1 << effect->EffectIndex)) != 0 && CheckEffectTarget(target, effect, losPosition))
2045 validEffectMask |= 1 << effect->EffectIndex;
2046
2047 effectMask &= validEffectMask;
2048
2049 // no effects left
2050 if (!effectMask)
2051 return;
2052
2053 if (checkIfValid)
2054 if (m_spellInfo->CheckTarget(m_caster, target, implicit) != SPELL_CAST_OK)
2055 return;
2056
2057 // Check for effect immune skip if immuned
2058 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
2059 if (effect && target->IsImmunedToSpellEffect(m_spellInfo, effect->EffectIndex))
2060 effectMask &= ~(1 << effect->EffectIndex);
2061
2062 ObjectGuid targetGUID = target->GetGUID();
2063
2064 // Lookup target in already in list
2065 for (std::vector<TargetInfo>::iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
2066 {
2067 if (targetGUID == ihit->targetGUID) // Found in list
2068 {
2069 ihit->effectMask |= effectMask; // Immune effects removed from mask
2070 ihit->scaleAura = false;
2071 if (m_auraScaleMask && ihit->effectMask == m_auraScaleMask && m_caster != target)
2072 {
2073 SpellInfo const* auraSpell = m_spellInfo->GetFirstRankSpell();
2074 if (uint32(target->getLevel() + 10) >= auraSpell->SpellLevel)
2075 ihit->scaleAura = true;
2076 }
2077 return;
2078 }
2079 }
2080
2081 // This is new target calculate data for him
2082
2083 // Get spell hit result on target
2084 TargetInfo targetInfo;
2085 targetInfo.targetGUID = targetGUID; // Store target GUID
2086 targetInfo.effectMask = effectMask; // Store all effects not immune
2087 targetInfo.processed = false; // Effects not apply on target
2088 targetInfo.alive = target->IsAlive();
2089 targetInfo.damage = 0;
2090 targetInfo.crit = false;
2091 targetInfo.scaleAura = false;
2092 if (m_auraScaleMask && targetInfo.effectMask == m_auraScaleMask && m_caster != target)
2093 {
2094 SpellInfo const* auraSpell = m_spellInfo->GetFirstRankSpell();
2095 if (uint32(target->getLevel() + 10) >= auraSpell->SpellLevel)
2096 targetInfo.scaleAura = true;
2097 }
2098
2099 // Calculate hit result
2100 if (m_originalCaster)
2101 {
2102 targetInfo.missCondition = m_originalCaster->SpellHitResult(target, m_spellInfo, m_canReflect);
2103 if (m_skipCheck && targetInfo.missCondition != SPELL_MISS_IMMUNE)
2104 targetInfo.missCondition = SPELL_MISS_NONE;
2105 }
2106 else
2107 targetInfo.missCondition = SPELL_MISS_EVADE; //SPELL_MISS_NONE;
2108
2109 // Spell have speed - need calculate incoming time
2110 // Incoming time is zero for self casts. At least I think so.
2111 if (m_spellInfo->Speed > 0.0f && m_caster != target)
2112 {
2113 // calculate spell incoming interval
2114 /// @todo this is a hack
2115 float dist = m_caster->GetDistance(target->GetPositionX(), target->GetPositionY(), target->GetPositionZ());
2116
2117 if (dist < 5.0f)
2118 dist = 5.0f;
2119
2120 if (!m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR9_SPECIAL_DELAY_CALCULATION))
2121 targetInfo.timeDelay = uint64(std::floor(dist / m_spellInfo->Speed * 1000.0f));
2122 else
2123 targetInfo.timeDelay = uint64(m_spellInfo->Speed * 1000.0f);
2124
2125 // Calculate minimum incoming time
2126 if (m_delayMoment == 0 || m_delayMoment > targetInfo.timeDelay)
2127 m_delayMoment = targetInfo.timeDelay;
2128 }
2129 else
2130 targetInfo.timeDelay = 0LL;
2131
2132 // If target reflect spell back to caster
2133 if (targetInfo.missCondition == SPELL_MISS_REFLECT)
2134 {
2135 // Calculate reflected spell result on caster
2136 targetInfo.reflectResult = m_caster->SpellHitResult(m_caster, m_spellInfo, m_canReflect);
2137
2138 if (targetInfo.reflectResult == SPELL_MISS_REFLECT) // Impossible reflect again, so simply deflect spell
2139 targetInfo.reflectResult = SPELL_MISS_PARRY;
2140
2141 // Increase time interval for reflected spells by 1.5
2142 targetInfo.timeDelay += targetInfo.timeDelay >> 1;
2143 }
2144 else
2145 targetInfo.reflectResult = SPELL_MISS_NONE;
2146
2147 // Add target to list
2148 m_UniqueTargetInfo.push_back(targetInfo);
2149}
2150
2151void Spell::AddGOTarget(GameObject* go, uint32 effectMask)
2152{
2153 uint32 validEffectMask = 0;
2154 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
2155 if (effect && (effectMask & (1 << effect->EffectIndex)) != 0 && CheckEffectTarget(go, effect))
2156 validEffectMask |= 1 << effect->EffectIndex;
2157
2158 effectMask &= validEffectMask;
2159
2160 // no effects left
2161 if (!effectMask)
2162 return;
2163
2164 ObjectGuid targetGUID = go->GetGUID();
2165
2166 // Lookup target in already in list
2167 for (std::vector<GOTargetInfo>::iterator ihit = m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
2168 {
2169 if (targetGUID == ihit->targetGUID) // Found in list
2170 {
2171 ihit->effectMask |= effectMask; // Add only effect mask
2172 return;
2173 }
2174 }
2175
2176 // This is new target calculate data for him
2177
2178 GOTargetInfo target;
2179 target.targetGUID = targetGUID;
2180 target.effectMask = effectMask;
2181 target.processed = false; // Effects not apply on target
2182
2183 // Spell have speed - need calculate incoming time
2184 if (m_spellInfo->Speed > 0.0f)
2185 {
2186 // calculate spell incoming interval
2187 float dist = m_caster->GetDistance(go->GetPositionX(), go->GetPositionY(), go->GetPositionZ());
2188 if (dist < 5.0f)
2189 dist = 5.0f;
2190
2191 if (!m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR9_SPECIAL_DELAY_CALCULATION))
2192 target.timeDelay = uint64(floor(dist / m_spellInfo->Speed * 1000.0f));
2193 else
2194 target.timeDelay = uint64(m_spellInfo->Speed * 1000.0f);
2195
2196 if (m_delayMoment == 0 || m_delayMoment > target.timeDelay)
2197 m_delayMoment = target.timeDelay;
2198 }
2199 else
2200 target.timeDelay = 0LL;
2201
2202 // Add target to list
2203 m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.push_back(target);
2204}

2206void Spell::AddItemTarget(Item* item, uint32 effectMask)
2207{
2208 uint32 validEffectMask = 0;
2209 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
2210 if (effect && (effectMask & (1 << effect->EffectIndex)) != 0 && CheckEffectTarget(item, effect))
2211 validEffectMask |= 1 << effect->EffectIndex;
2212
2213 effectMask &= validEffectMask;
2214
2215 // no effects left
2216 if (!effectMask)
2217 return;
2218
2219 // Lookup target in already in list
2220 for (std::vector<ItemTargetInfo>::iterator ihit = m_UniqueItemInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueItemInfo.end(); ++ihit)
2221 {
2222 if (item == ihit->item) // Found in list
2223 {
2224 ihit->effectMask |= effectMask; // Add only effect mask
2225 return;
2226 }
2227 }
2228
2229 // This is new target add data
2230
2231 ItemTargetInfo target;
2232 target.item = item;
2233 target.effectMask = effectMask;
2234
2235 m_UniqueItemInfo.push_back(target);
2236}
