2238void Spell::AddDestTarget(SpellDestination const& dest, uint32 effIndex)
2239{
2240 m_destTargets[effIndex] = dest;
2241}
2242
2243void Spell::DoAllEffectOnTarget(TargetInfo* target)
2244{
2245 if (!target || target->processed)
2246 return;
2247
2248 target->processed = true; // Target checked in apply effects procedure
2249
2250 // Get mask of effects for target
2251 uint32 mask = target->effectMask;
2252
2253 Unit* unit = m_caster->GetGUID() == target->targetGUID ? m_caster : ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, target->targetGUID);
2254 if (!unit && target->targetGUID.IsPlayer()) // only players may be targeted across maps
2255 {
2256 uint8 farMask = 0;
2257 // create far target mask
2258 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
2259 if (effect && effect->IsFarUnitTargetEffect())
2260 if ((1 << effect->EffectIndex) & mask)
2261 farMask |= (1 << effect->EffectIndex);
2262
2263 if (!farMask)
2264 return;
2265
2266 // find unit in world
2267 unit = ObjectAccessor::FindPlayer(target->targetGUID);
2268 if (!unit)
2269 return;
2270
2271 // do far effects on the unit
2272 // can't use default call because of threading, do stuff as fast as possible
2273 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
2274 if (effect && (farMask & (1 << effect->EffectIndex)))
2275 HandleEffects(unit, NULL, NULL, effect->EffectIndex, SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_HIT_TARGET);
2276 return;
2277 }
2278
2279 if (!unit)
2280 return;
2281
2282 if (unit->IsAlive() != target->alive)
2283 return;
2284
2285 if (getState() == SPELL_STATE_DELAYED && !m_spellInfo->IsPositive() && (getMSTime() - target->timeDelay) <= unit->m_lastSanctuaryTime)
2286 return; // No missinfo in that case
2287
2288 // Get original caster (if exist) and calculate damage/healing from him data
2289 Unit* caster = m_originalCaster ? m_originalCaster : m_caster;
2290
2291 // Skip if m_originalCaster not avaiable
2292 if (!caster)
2293 return;
2294
2295 SpellMissInfo missInfo = target->missCondition;
2296
2297 // Need init unitTarget by default unit (can changed in code on reflect)
2298 // Or on missInfo != SPELL_MISS_NONE unitTarget undefined (but need in trigger subsystem)
2299 unitTarget = unit;
2300
2301 // Reset damage/healing counter
2302 m_damage = target->damage;
2303 m_healing = -target->damage;
2304
2305 // Fill base trigger info
2306 uint32 procAttacker = m_procAttacker;
2307 uint32 procVictim = m_procVictim;
2308 uint32 procEx = m_procEx;
2309
2310 m_spellAura = NULL; // Set aura to null for every target-make sure that pointer is not used for unit without aura applied
2311
2312 //Spells with this flag cannot trigger if effect is cast on self
2313 bool canEffectTrigger = !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_CANT_TRIGGER_PROC) && unitTarget->CanProc() && (CanExecuteTriggersOnHit(mask) || missInfo == SPELL_MISS_IMMUNE || missInfo == SPELL_MISS_IMMUNE2);
2314 Unit* spellHitTarget = NULL;
2315
2316 if (missInfo == SPELL_MISS_NONE) // In case spell hit target, do all effect on that target
2317 spellHitTarget = unit;
2318 else if (missInfo == SPELL_MISS_REFLECT) // In case spell reflect from target, do all effect on caster (if hit)
2319 {
2320 if (target->reflectResult == SPELL_MISS_NONE) // If reflected spell hit caster -> do all effect on him
2321 {
2322 spellHitTarget = m_caster;
2323 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT)
2324 m_caster->ToCreature()->LowerPlayerDamageReq(target->damage);
2325 }
2326 }
2327
2328 if (spellHitTarget)
2329 {
2330 SpellMissInfo missInfo2 = DoSpellHitOnUnit(spellHitTarget, mask, target->scaleAura);
2331 if (missInfo2 != SPELL_MISS_NONE)
2332 {
2333 if (missInfo2 != SPELL_MISS_MISS)
2334 m_caster->SendSpellMiss(unit, m_spellInfo->Id, missInfo2);
2335 m_damage = 0;
2336 spellHitTarget = NULL;
2337 }
2338 }
2339
2340 // Do not take combo points on dodge and miss
2341 if (missInfo != SPELL_MISS_NONE && m_needComboPoints &&
2342 m_targets.GetUnitTargetGUID() == target->targetGUID)
2343 {
2344 m_needComboPoints = false;
2345 // Restore spell mods for a miss/dodge/parry Cold Blood
2346 /// @todo check how broad this rule should be
2347 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && (missInfo == SPELL_MISS_MISS ||
2348 missInfo == SPELL_MISS_DODGE || missInfo == SPELL_MISS_PARRY))
2349 m_caster->ToPlayer()->RestoreSpellMods(this, 14177);
2350 }
2351
2352 // Trigger info was not filled in spell::preparedatafortriggersystem - we do it now
2353 if (canEffectTrigger && !procAttacker && !procVictim)
2354 {
2355 bool positive = true;
2356 if (m_damage > 0)
2357 positive = false;
2358 else if (!m_healing)
2359 positive = m_spellInfo->IsPositive();
2360
2361 switch (m_spellInfo->DmgClass)
2362 {
2363 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MAGIC:
2364 if (positive)
2365 {
2366 procAttacker |= PROC_FLAG_DONE_SPELL_MAGIC_DMG_CLASS_POS;
2367 procVictim |= PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_SPELL_MAGIC_DMG_CLASS_POS;
2368 }
2369 else
2370 {
2371 procAttacker |= PROC_FLAG_DONE_SPELL_MAGIC_DMG_CLASS_NEG;
2372 procVictim |= PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_SPELL_MAGIC_DMG_CLASS_NEG;
2373 }
2374 break;
2375 case SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_NONE:
2376 if (positive)
2377 {
2378 procAttacker |= PROC_FLAG_DONE_SPELL_NONE_DMG_CLASS_POS;
2379 procVictim |= PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_SPELL_NONE_DMG_CLASS_POS;
2380 }
2381 else
2382 {
2383 procAttacker |= PROC_FLAG_DONE_SPELL_NONE_DMG_CLASS_NEG;
2384 procVictim |= PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_SPELL_NONE_DMG_CLASS_NEG;
2385 }
2386 break;
2387 }
2388 }
2389 CallScriptOnHitHandlers();
2390
2391 // All calculated do it!
2392 // Do healing and triggers
2393 if (m_healing > 0)
2394 {
2395 bool crit = target->crit;
2396 uint32 addhealth = m_healing;
2397 if (crit)
2398 {
2399 procEx |= PROC_EX_CRITICAL_HIT;
2400 addhealth = caster->SpellCriticalHealingBonus(m_spellInfo, addhealth, NULL);
2401 }
2402 else
2403 procEx |= PROC_EX_NORMAL_HIT;
2404
2405 int32 gain = caster->HealBySpell(unitTarget, m_spellInfo, addhealth, crit);
2406 unitTarget->getHostileRefManager().threatAssist(caster, float(gain) * 0.5f, m_spellInfo);
2407 m_healing = gain;
2408
2409 // Do triggers for unit (reflect triggers passed on hit phase for correct drop charge)
2410 if (canEffectTrigger && missInfo != SPELL_MISS_REFLECT)
2411 caster->ProcDamageAndSpell(unitTarget, procAttacker, procVictim, procEx, addhealth, m_attackType, m_spellInfo, m_triggeredByAuraSpell);
2412 }
2413 // Do damage and triggers
2414 else if (m_damage > 0)
2415 {
2416 // Fill base damage struct (unitTarget - is real spell target)
2417 SpellNonMeleeDamage damageInfo(caster, unitTarget, m_spellInfo->Id, m_spellSchoolMask);
2418
2419 // Add bonuses and fill damageInfo struct
2420 caster->CalculateSpellDamageTaken(&damageInfo, m_damage, m_spellInfo, m_attackType, target->crit);
2421 caster->DealDamageMods(damageInfo.target, damageInfo.damage, &damageInfo.absorb);
2422
2423 procEx |= createProcExtendMask(&damageInfo, missInfo);
2424 procVictim |= PROC_FLAG_TAKEN_DAMAGE;
2425
2426 // Do triggers for unit (reflect triggers passed on hit phase for correct drop charge)
2427 if (canEffectTrigger && missInfo != SPELL_MISS_REFLECT)
2428 {
2429 caster->ProcDamageAndSpell(unitTarget, procAttacker, procVictim, procEx, damageInfo.damage, m_attackType, m_spellInfo, m_triggeredByAuraSpell);
2430 if (caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_STOP_ATTACK_TARGET)) == 0 &&
2431 (m_spellInfo->DmgClass == SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_MELEE || m_spellInfo->DmgClass == SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_RANGED))
2432 caster->ToPlayer()->CastItemCombatSpell(unitTarget, m_attackType, procVictim, procEx);
2433 }
2434
2435 m_damage = damageInfo.damage;
2436
2437 caster->DealSpellDamage(&damageInfo, true);
2438
2439 // Send log damage message to client
2440 caster->SendSpellNonMeleeDamageLog(&damageInfo);
2441 }
2442 // Passive spell hits/misses or active spells only misses (only triggers)
2443 else
2444 {
2445 // Fill base damage struct (unitTarget - is real spell target)
2446 SpellNonMeleeDamage damageInfo(caster, unitTarget, m_spellInfo->Id, m_spellSchoolMask);
2447 procEx |= createProcExtendMask(&damageInfo, missInfo);
2448 // Do triggers for unit (reflect triggers passed on hit phase for correct drop charge)
2449 if (canEffectTrigger && missInfo != SPELL_MISS_REFLECT)
2450 caster->ProcDamageAndSpell(unit, procAttacker, procVictim, procEx, 0, m_attackType, m_spellInfo, m_triggeredByAuraSpell);
2451
2452 // Failed Pickpocket, reveal rogue
2453 if (missInfo == SPELL_MISS_RESIST && m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CU_PICKPOCKET) && unitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT)
2454 {
2455 m_caster->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_TALK);
2456 if (unitTarget->ToCreature()->IsAIEnabled)
2457 unitTarget->ToCreature()->AI()->AttackStart(m_caster);
2458 }
2459 }
2460
2461 if (missInfo != SPELL_MISS_EVADE && !m_caster->IsFriendlyTo(unit) && (!m_spellInfo->IsPositive() || HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_DISPEL)))
2462 {
2463 m_caster->CombatStart(unit, !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_NO_INITIAL_AGGRO));
2464
2465 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CU_AURA_CC))
2466 if (!unit->IsStandState())
2467 unit->SetStandState(UNIT_STAND_STATE_STAND);
2468 }
2469
2470 if (spellHitTarget)
2471 {
2472 //AI functions
2473 if (spellHitTarget->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT)
2474 if (spellHitTarget->ToCreature()->IsAIEnabled)
2475 spellHitTarget->ToCreature()->AI()->SpellHit(m_caster, m_spellInfo);
2476
2477 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && m_caster->ToCreature()->IsAIEnabled)
2478 m_caster->ToCreature()->AI()->SpellHitTarget(spellHitTarget, m_spellInfo);
2479
2480 // Needs to be called after dealing damage/healing to not remove breaking on damage auras
2481 DoTriggersOnSpellHit(spellHitTarget, mask);
2482
2483 // if target is fallged for pvp also flag caster if a player
2484 if (unit->IsPvP() && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
2485 m_caster->ToPlayer()->UpdatePvP(true);
2486
2487 CallScriptAfterHitHandlers();
2488 }
2489}
2490
2491SpellMissInfo Spell::DoSpellHitOnUnit(Unit* unit, uint32 effectMask, bool scaleAura)
2492{
2493 if (!unit || !effectMask)
2494 return SPELL_MISS_EVADE;
2495
2496 // For delayed spells immunity may be applied between missile launch and hit - check immunity for that case
2497 if (m_spellInfo->Speed && (unit->IsImmunedToDamage(m_spellInfo) || unit->IsImmunedToSpell(m_spellInfo)))
2498 return SPELL_MISS_IMMUNE;
2499
2500 // disable effects to which unit is immune
2501 SpellMissInfo returnVal = SPELL_MISS_IMMUNE;
2502 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
2503 if (effect && (effectMask & (1 << effect->EffectIndex)))
2504 if (unit->IsImmunedToSpellEffect(m_spellInfo, effect->EffectIndex))
2505 effectMask &= ~(1 << effect->EffectIndex);
2506
2507 if (!effectMask)
2508 return returnVal;
2509
2510 PrepareScriptHitHandlers();
2511 CallScriptBeforeHitHandlers();
2512
2513 if (Player* player = unit->ToPlayer())
2514 {
2515 player->StartTimedAchievement(ACHIEVEMENT_TIMED_TYPE_SPELL_TARGET, m_spellInfo->Id);
2516 player->UpdateAchievementCriteria(ACHIEVEMENT_CRITERIA_TYPE_BE_SPELL_TARGET, m_spellInfo->Id, 0, 0, m_caster);
2517 player->UpdateAchievementCriteria(ACHIEVEMENT_CRITERIA_TYPE_BE_SPELL_TARGET2, m_spellInfo->Id);
2518 }
2519
2520 if (Player* player = m_caster->ToPlayer())
2521 {
2522 player->StartTimedAchievement(ACHIEVEMENT_TIMED_TYPE_SPELL_CASTER, m_spellInfo->Id);
2523 player->UpdateAchievementCriteria(ACHIEVEMENT_CRITERIA_TYPE_CAST_SPELL2, m_spellInfo->Id, 0, 0, unit);
2524 }
2525
2526 if (m_caster != unit)
2527 {
2528 // Recheck UNIT_FLAG_NON_ATTACKABLE for delayed spells
2529 if (m_spellInfo->Speed > 0.0f && unit->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS, UNIT_FLAG_NON_ATTACKABLE) && unit->GetCharmerOrOwnerGUID() != m_caster->GetGUID())
2530 return SPELL_MISS_EVADE;
2531
2532 if (m_caster->_IsValidAttackTarget(unit, m_spellInfo))
2533 {
2534 unit->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_HITBYSPELL);
2535 /// @todo This is a hack. But we do not know what types of stealth should be interrupted by CC
2536 if ((m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CU_AURA_CC)) && unit->IsControlledByPlayer())
2537 unit->RemoveAurasByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_STEALTH);
2538 }
2539 else if (m_caster->IsFriendlyTo(unit))
2540 {
2541 // for delayed spells ignore negative spells (after duel end) for friendly targets
2542 /// @todo this cause soul transfer bugged
2543 // 63881 - Malady of the Mind jump spell (Yogg-Saron)
2544 if (m_spellInfo->Speed > 0.0f && unit->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && !m_spellInfo->IsPositive() && m_spellInfo->Id != 63881)
2545 return SPELL_MISS_EVADE;
2546
2547 // assisting case, healing and resurrection
2548 if (unit->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_ATTACK_PLAYER))
2549 {
2550 m_caster->SetContestedPvP();
2551 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
2552 m_caster->ToPlayer()->UpdatePvP(true);
2553 }
2554 if (unit->IsInCombat() && !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_NO_INITIAL_AGGRO))
2555 {
2556 m_caster->SetInCombatState(unit->GetCombatTimer() > 0, unit);
2557 unit->getHostileRefManager().threatAssist(m_caster, 0.0f);
2558 }
2559 }
2560 }
2561
2562 uint8 aura_effmask = 0;
2563 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
2564 if (effect && (effectMask & (1 << effect->EffectIndex) && effect->IsUnitOwnedAuraEffect()))
2565 aura_effmask |= 1 << effect->EffectIndex;
2566
2567 // Get Data Needed for Diminishing Returns, some effects may have multiple auras, so this must be done on spell hit, not aura add
2568 m_diminishGroup = GetDiminishingReturnsGroupForSpell(m_spellInfo);
2569 if (m_diminishGroup && aura_effmask)
2570 {
2571 m_diminishLevel = unit->GetDiminishing(m_diminishGroup);
2572 DiminishingReturnsType type = GetDiminishingReturnsGroupType(m_diminishGroup);
2573 // Increase Diminishing on unit, current informations for actually casts will use values above
2574 if ((type == DRTYPE_PLAYER &&
2575 (unit->GetCharmerOrOwnerPlayerOrPlayerItself() || (unit->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && unit->ToCreature()->GetCreatureTemplate()->flags_extra & CREATURE_FLAG_EXTRA_ALL_DIMINISH))) ||
2576 type == DRTYPE_ALL)
2577 unit->IncrDiminishing(m_diminishGroup);
2578 }
2579
2580 if (aura_effmask)
2581 {
2582 // Select rank for aura with level requirements only in specific cases
2583 // Unit has to be target only of aura effect, both caster and target have to be players, target has to be other than unit target
2584 SpellInfo const* aurSpellInfo = m_spellInfo;
2585 int32 basePoints[MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS];
2586 if (scaleAura)
2587 {
2588 aurSpellInfo = m_spellInfo->GetAuraRankForLevel(unitTarget->getLevel());
2589 ASSERT(aurSpellInfo);
2590 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : aurSpellInfo->GetEffectsForDifficulty(0))
2591 {
2592 basePoints[effect->EffectIndex] = effect->BasePoints;
2593 if (SpellEffectInfo const* myEffect = GetEffect(effect->EffectIndex))
2594 {
2595 if (myEffect->Effect != effect->Effect)
2596 {
2597 aurSpellInfo = m_spellInfo;
2598 break;
2599 }
2600 }
2601 }
2602 }
2603
2604 if (m_originalCaster)
2605 {
2606 bool refresh = false;
2607 m_spellAura = Aura::TryRefreshStackOrCreate(aurSpellInfo, effectMask, unit,
2608 m_originalCaster, (aurSpellInfo == m_spellInfo) ? m_spellValue->EffectBasePoints : basePoints,
2609 m_CastItem, ObjectGuid::Empty, &refresh, m_castItemLevel);
2610 if (m_spellAura)
2611 {
2612 // Set aura stack amount to desired value
2613 if (m_spellValue->AuraStackAmount > 1)
2614 {
2615 if (!refresh)
2616 m_spellAura->SetStackAmount(m_spellValue->AuraStackAmount);
2617 else
2618 m_spellAura->ModStackAmount(m_spellValue->AuraStackAmount);
2619 }
2620
2621 // Now Reduce spell duration using data received at spell hit
2622 int32 duration = m_spellAura->GetMaxDuration();
2623 int32 limitduration = m_diminishGroup ? GetDiminishingReturnsLimitDuration(aurSpellInfo) : 0;
2624 float diminishMod = unit->ApplyDiminishingToDuration(m_diminishGroup, duration, m_originalCaster, m_diminishLevel, limitduration);
2625
2626 // unit is immune to aura if it was diminished to 0 duration
2627 if (diminishMod == 0.0f)
2628 {
2629 m_spellAura->Remove();
2630 bool found = false;
2631 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
2632 if (effect && (effectMask & (1 << effect->EffectIndex) && effect->Effect != SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA))
2633 found = true;
2634 if (!found)
2635 return SPELL_MISS_IMMUNE;
2636 }
2637 else
2638 {
2639 ((UnitAura*)m_spellAura)->SetDiminishGroup(m_diminishGroup);
2640
2641 bool positive = m_spellAura->GetSpellInfo()->IsPositive();
2642 if (AuraApplication* aurApp = m_spellAura->GetApplicationOfTarget(m_originalCaster->GetGUID()))
2643 positive = aurApp->IsPositive();
2644
2645 duration = m_originalCaster->ModSpellDuration(aurSpellInfo, unit, duration, positive, effectMask);
2646
2647 if (duration > 0)
2648 {
2649 // Haste modifies duration of channeled spells
2650 if (m_spellInfo->IsChanneled())
2651 m_originalCaster->ModSpellCastTime(aurSpellInfo, duration, this);
2652 else if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_HASTE_AFFECT_DURATION))
2653 {
2654 int32 origDuration = duration;
2655 duration = 0;
2656 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
2657 if (effect)
2658 if (AuraEffect const* eff = m_spellAura->GetEffect(effect->EffectIndex))
2659 if (int32 period = eff->GetPeriod()) // period is hastened by UNIT_MOD_CAST_SPEED
2660 duration = std::max(std::max(origDuration / period, 1) * period, duration);
2661
2662 // if there is no periodic effect
2663 if (!duration)
2664 duration = int32(origDuration * m_originalCaster->GetFloatValue(UNIT_MOD_CAST_SPEED));
2665 }
2666 }
2667
2668 if (duration != m_spellAura->GetMaxDuration())
2669 {
2670 m_spellAura->SetMaxDuration(duration);
2671 m_spellAura->SetDuration(duration);
2672 }
2673 m_spellAura->_RegisterForTargets();
2674 }
2675 }
2676 }
2677 }
2678
2679 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
2680 if (effect && (effectMask & (1 << effect->EffectIndex)))
2681 HandleEffects(unit, NULL, NULL, effect->EffectIndex, SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_HIT_TARGET);
2682
2683 return SPELL_MISS_NONE;
2684}
2685
2686void Spell::DoTriggersOnSpellHit(Unit* unit, uint8 effMask)
2687{
2688 // Apply additional spell effects to target
2689 /// @todo move this code to scripts
2690 if (m_preCastSpell)
2691 {
2692 // Paladin immunity shields
2693 if (m_preCastSpell == 61988)
2694 {
2695 // Cast Forbearance
2696 m_caster->CastSpell(unit, 25771, true);
2697 // Cast Avenging Wrath Marker
2698 unit->CastSpell(unit, 61987, true);
2699 }
2700
2701 // Avenging Wrath
2702 if (m_preCastSpell == 61987)
2703 // Cast the serverside immunity shield marker
2704 m_caster->CastSpell(unit, 61988, true);
2705
2706 if (sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(m_preCastSpell))
2707 // Blizz seems to just apply aura without bothering to cast
2708 m_caster->AddAura(m_preCastSpell, unit);
2709 }
2710
2711 // handle SPELL_AURA_ADD_TARGET_TRIGGER auras
2712 // this is executed after spell proc spells on target hit
2713 // spells are triggered for each hit spell target
2714 // info confirmed with retail sniffs of permafrost and shadow weaving
2715 if (!m_hitTriggerSpells.empty())
2716 {
2717 int _duration = 0;
2718 for (HitTriggerSpellList::const_iterator i = m_hitTriggerSpells.begin(); i != m_hitTriggerSpells.end(); ++i)
2719 {
2720 if (CanExecuteTriggersOnHit(effMask, i->triggeredByAura) && roll_chance_i(i->chance))
2721 {
2722 m_caster->CastSpell(unit, i->triggeredSpell, TriggerCastFlags(TRIGGERED_FULL_MASK & ~TRIGGERED_IGNORE_TARGET_CHECK));
2723 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell %d triggered spell %d by SPELL_AURA_ADD_TARGET_TRIGGER aura", m_spellInfo->Id, i->triggeredSpell->Id);
2724
2725 // SPELL_AURA_ADD_TARGET_TRIGGER auras shouldn't trigger auras without duration
2726 // set duration of current aura to the triggered spell
2727 if (i->triggeredSpell->GetDuration() == -1)
2728 {
2729 if (Aura* triggeredAur = unit->GetAura(i->triggeredSpell->Id, m_caster->GetGUID()))
2730 {
2731 // get duration from aura-only once
2732 if (!_duration)
2733 {
2734 Aura* aur = unit->GetAura(m_spellInfo->Id, m_caster->GetGUID());
2735 _duration = aur ? aur->GetDuration() : -1;
2736 }
2737 triggeredAur->SetDuration(_duration);
2738 }
2739 }
2740 }
2741 }
2742 }
2743
2744 // trigger linked auras remove/apply
2745 /// @todo remove/cleanup this, as this table is not documented and people are doing stupid things with it
2746 if (std::vector<int32> const* spellTriggered = sSpellMgr->GetSpellLinked(m_spellInfo->Id + SPELL_LINK_HIT))
2747 {
2748 for (std::vector<int32>::const_iterator i = spellTriggered->begin(); i != spellTriggered->end(); ++i)
2749 {
2750 if (*i < 0)
2751 unit->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(-(*i));
2752 else
2753 unit->CastSpell(unit, *i, true, nullptr, nullptr, m_caster->GetGUID());
2754 }
2755 }
2756}
2757
2758void Spell::DoAllEffectOnTarget(GOTargetInfo* target)
2759{
2760 if (target->processed) // Check target
2761 return;
2762 target->processed = true; // Target checked in apply effects procedure
2763
2764 uint32 effectMask = target->effectMask;
2765 if (!effectMask)
2766 return;
2767
2768 GameObject* go = m_caster->GetMap()->GetGameObject(target->targetGUID);
2769 if (!go)
2770 return;
2771
2772 PrepareScriptHitHandlers();
2773 CallScriptBeforeHitHandlers();
2774
2775 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
2776 if (effect && (effectMask & (1 << effect->EffectIndex)))
2777 HandleEffects(NULL, NULL, go, effect->EffectIndex, SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_HIT_TARGET);
2778
2779 CallScriptOnHitHandlers();
2780 CallScriptAfterHitHandlers();
2781}
2782
2783void Spell::DoAllEffectOnTarget(ItemTargetInfo* target)
2784{
2785 uint32 effectMask = target->effectMask;
2786 if (!target->item || !effectMask)
2787 return;
2788
2789 PrepareScriptHitHandlers();
2790 CallScriptBeforeHitHandlers();
2791
2792 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
2793 if (effect && (effectMask & (1 << effect->EffectIndex)))
2794 HandleEffects(NULL, target->item, NULL, effect->EffectIndex, SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_HIT_TARGET);
2795
2796 CallScriptOnHitHandlers();
2797
2798 CallScriptAfterHitHandlers();
2799}
2800
2801bool Spell::UpdateChanneledTargetList()
2802{
2803 // Not need check return true
2804 if (m_channelTargetEffectMask == 0)
2805 return true;
2806
2807 uint32 channelTargetEffectMask = m_channelTargetEffectMask;
2808 uint32 channelAuraMask = 0;
2809 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
2810 if (effect && effect->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA)
2811 channelAuraMask |= 1 << effect->EffectIndex;
2812
2813 channelAuraMask &= channelTargetEffectMask;
2814
2815 float range = 0;
2816 if (channelAuraMask)
2817 {
2818 range = m_spellInfo->GetMaxRange(m_spellInfo->IsPositive());
2819 if (Player* modOwner = m_caster->GetSpellModOwner())
2820 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_RANGE, range, this);
2821 }
2822
2823 for (std::vector<TargetInfo>::iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
2824 {
2825 if (ihit->missCondition == SPELL_MISS_NONE && (channelTargetEffectMask & ihit->effectMask))
2826 {
2827 Unit* unit = m_caster->GetGUID() == ihit->targetGUID ? m_caster : ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, ihit->targetGUID);
2828
2829 if (!unit)
2830 continue;
2831
2832 if (IsValidDeadOrAliveTarget(unit))
2833 {
2834 if (channelAuraMask & ihit->effectMask)
2835 {
2836 if (AuraApplication * aurApp = unit->GetAuraApplication(m_spellInfo->Id, m_originalCasterGUID))
2837 {
2838 if (m_caster != unit && !m_caster->IsWithinDistInMap(unit, range))
2839 {
2840 ihit->effectMask &= ~aurApp->GetEffectMask();
2841 unit->RemoveAura(aurApp);
2842 continue;
2843 }
2844 }
2845 else // aura is dispelled
2846 continue;
2847 }
2848
2849 channelTargetEffectMask &= ~ihit->effectMask; // remove from need alive mask effect that have alive target
2850 }
2851 }
2852 }
2853
2854 // is all effects from m_needAliveTargetMask have alive targets
2855 return channelTargetEffectMask == 0;
2856}
2857
2858void Spell::prepare(SpellCastTargets const* targets, AuraEffect const* triggeredByAura)
2859{
2860 if (m_CastItem)
2861 {
2862 m_castItemGUID = m_CastItem->GetGUID();
2863 m_castItemEntry = m_CastItem->GetEntry();
2864
2865 if (Player* owner = m_CastItem->GetOwner())
2866 m_castItemLevel = int32(m_CastItem->GetItemLevel(owner));
2867 else if (m_CastItem->GetOwnerGUID() == m_caster->GetGUID())
2868 m_castItemLevel = int32(m_CastItem->GetItemLevel(m_caster->ToPlayer()));
2869 else
2870 {
2871 SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM);
2872 finish(false);
2873 return;
2874 }
2875 }
2876
2877 InitExplicitTargets(*targets);
2878
2879 // Fill aura scaling information
2880 if (m_caster->IsControlledByPlayer() && !m_spellInfo->IsPassive() && m_spellInfo->SpellLevel && !m_spellInfo->IsChanneled() && !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_AURA_SCALING))
2881 {
2882 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
2883 {
2884 if (effect && effect->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA)
2885 {
2886 // Change aura with ranks only if basepoints are taken from spellInfo and aura is positive
2887 if (m_spellInfo->IsPositiveEffect(effect->EffectIndex))
2888 {
2889 m_auraScaleMask |= (1 << effect->EffectIndex);
2890 if (m_spellValue->EffectBasePoints[effect->EffectIndex] != effect->BasePoints)
2891 {
2892 m_auraScaleMask = 0;
2893 break;
2894 }
2895 }
2896 }
2897 }
2898 }
2899
2900 m_spellState = SPELL_STATE_PREPARING;
2901
2902 if (triggeredByAura)
2903 {
2904 m_triggeredByAuraSpell = triggeredByAura->GetSpellInfo();
2905 m_castItemLevel = triggeredByAura->GetBase()->GetCastItemLevel();
2906 }
2907
2908 // create and add update event for this spell
2909 SpellEvent* Event = new SpellEvent(this);
2910 m_caster->m_Events.AddEvent(Event, m_caster->m_Events.CalculateTime(1));
2911
2912 //Prevent casting at cast another spell (ServerSide check)
2913 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CAST_IN_PROGRESS) && m_caster->IsNonMeleeSpellCast(false, true, true) && m_cast_count)
2914 {
2915 SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_SPELL_IN_PROGRESS);
2916 finish(false);
2917 return;
2918 }
2919
2920 if (DisableMgr::IsDisabledFor(DISABLE_TYPE_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id, m_caster))
2921 {
2922 SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_SPELL_UNAVAILABLE);
2923 finish(false);
2924 return;
2925 }
2926 LoadScripts();
2927
2928 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
2929 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, true);
2930 // Fill cost data (not use power for item casts
2931 if (!m_CastItem)
2932 m_powerCost = m_spellInfo->CalcPowerCost(m_caster, m_spellSchoolMask);
2933 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
2934 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, false);
2935
2936 // Set combo point requirement
2937 if ((_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_COMBO_POINTS) || m_CastItem || !m_caster->m_movedPlayer)
2938 m_needComboPoints = false;
2939
2940 SpellCastResult result = CheckCast(true);
2941 // target is checked in too many locations and with different results to handle each of them
2942 // handle just the general SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS result which is the default result for most DBC target checks
2943 if (_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_TARGET_CHECK && result == SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS)
2944 result = SPELL_CAST_OK;
2945 if (result != SPELL_CAST_OK && !IsAutoRepeat()) //always cast autorepeat dummy for triggering
2946 {
2947 // Periodic auras should be interrupted when aura triggers a spell which can't be cast
2948 // for example bladestorm aura should be removed on disarm as of patch 3.3.5
2949 // channeled periodic spells should be affected by this (arcane missiles, penance, etc)
2950 // a possible alternative sollution for those would be validating aura target on unit state change
2951 if (triggeredByAura && triggeredByAura->IsPeriodic() && !triggeredByAura->GetBase()->IsPassive())
2952 {
2953 SendChannelUpdate(0);
2954 triggeredByAura->GetBase()->SetDuration(0);
2955 }
2956
2957 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
2958 {
2959 m_caster->ToPlayer()->RestoreSpellMods(this);
2960 // cleanup after mod system
2961 // triggered spell pointer can be not removed in some cases
2962 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, false);
2963 }
2964
2965 SendCastResult(result);
2966
2967 finish(false);
2968 return;
2969 }
2970
2971 // Prepare data for triggers
2972 prepareDataForTriggerSystem(triggeredByAura);
2973
2974 if (Player* player = m_caster->ToPlayer())
2975 {
2976 if (!player->GetCommandStatus(CHEAT_CASTTIME))
2977 {
2978 player->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, true);
2979 // calculate cast time (calculated after first CheckCast check to prevent charge counting for first CheckCast fail)
2980 m_casttime = m_spellInfo->CalcCastTime(player->getLevel(), this);
2981 player->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, false);
2982 }
2983 else
2984 m_casttime = 0; // Set cast time to 0 if .cheat casttime is enabled.
2985 }
2986 else
2987 m_casttime = m_spellInfo->CalcCastTime(m_caster->getLevel(), this);
2988
2989 // don't allow channeled spells / spells with cast time to be cast while moving
2990 // (even if they are interrupted on moving, spells with almost immediate effect get to have their effect processed before movement interrupter kicks in)
2991 // don't cancel spells which are affected by a SPELL_AURA_CAST_WHILE_WALKING effect
2992 if (((m_spellInfo->IsChanneled() || m_casttime) && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && m_caster->isMoving() &&
2993 m_spellInfo->InterruptFlags & SPELL_INTERRUPT_FLAG_MOVEMENT) && !m_caster->HasAuraTypeWithAffectMask(SPELL_AURA_CAST_WHILE_WALKING, m_spellInfo))
2994 {
2995 SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_MOVING);
2996 finish(false);
2997 return;
2998 }
2999
3000 // set timer base at cast time
3001 ReSetTimer();
3002
3003 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell::prepare: spell id %u source %u caster %d customCastFlags %u mask %u", m_spellInfo->Id, m_caster->GetEntry(), m_originalCaster ? m_originalCaster->GetEntry() : -1, _triggeredCastFlags, m_targets.GetTargetMask());
3004
3005 //Containers for channeled spells have to be set
3006 /// @todoApply this to all cast spells if needed
3007 // Why check duration? 29350: channelled triggers channelled
3008 if ((_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_CAST_DIRECTLY) && (!m_spellInfo->IsChanneled() || !m_spellInfo->GetMaxDuration()))
3009 cast(true);
3010 else
3011 {
3012 // stealth must be removed at cast starting (at show channel bar)
3013 // skip triggered spell (item equip spell casting and other not explicit character casts/item uses)
3014 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAGS) && m_spellInfo->IsBreakingStealth())
3015 {
3016 m_caster->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_CAST);
3017 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
3018 if (effect && effect->GetUsedTargetObjectType() == TARGET_OBJECT_TYPE_UNIT)
3019 {
3020 m_caster->RemoveAurasWithInterruptFlags(AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_SPELL_ATTACK);
3021 break;
3022 }
3023 }
3024
3025 m_caster->SetCurrentCastSpell(this);
3026 SendSpellStart();
3027
3028 // set target for proper facing
3029 if ((m_casttime || m_spellInfo->IsChanneled()) && !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_SET_FACING))
3030 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && m_targets.GetObjectTarget() && m_caster != m_targets.GetObjectTarget())
3031 m_caster->ToCreature()->FocusTarget(this, m_targets.GetObjectTarget());
3032
3033 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_GCD))
3034 TriggerGlobalCooldown();
3035
3036 //item: first cast may destroy item and second cast causes crash
3037 if (!m_casttime && !m_spellInfo->StartRecoveryTime && !m_castItemGUID && GetCurrentContainer() == CURRENT_GENERIC_SPELL)
3038 cast(true);
3039 }
3040}
3041
3042void Spell::cancel()
3043{
3044 if (m_spellState == SPELL_STATE_FINISHED)
3045 return;
3046
3047 uint32 oldState = m_spellState;
3048 m_spellState = SPELL_STATE_FINISHED;
3049
3050 m_autoRepeat = false;
3051 switch (oldState)
3052 {
3053 case SPELL_STATE_PREPARING:
3054 CancelGlobalCooldown();
3055 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3056 m_caster->ToPlayer()->RestoreSpellMods(this);
3057 // no break
3058 case SPELL_STATE_DELAYED:
3059 SendInterrupted(0);
3060 SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_INTERRUPTED);
3061 break;
3062
3063 case SPELL_STATE_CASTING:
3064 for (std::vector<TargetInfo>::const_iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
3065 if ((*ihit).missCondition == SPELL_MISS_NONE)
3066 if (Unit* unit = m_caster->GetGUID() == ihit->targetGUID ? m_caster : ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, ihit->targetGUID))
3067 unit->RemoveOwnedAura(m_spellInfo->Id, m_originalCasterGUID, 0, AURA_REMOVE_BY_CANCEL);
3068
3069 SendChannelUpdate(0);
3070 SendInterrupted(0);
3071 SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_INTERRUPTED);
3072
3073 // spell is canceled-take mods and clear list
3074 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3075 m_caster->ToPlayer()->RemoveSpellMods(this);
3076
3077 m_appliedMods.clear();
3078 break;
3079
3080 default:
3081 break;
3082 }
3083
3084 SetReferencedFromCurrent(false);
3085 if (m_selfContainer && *m_selfContainer == this)
3086 *m_selfContainer = NULL;
3087
3088 m_caster->RemoveDynObject(m_spellInfo->Id);
3089 if (m_spellInfo->IsChanneled()) // if not channeled then the object for the current cast wasn't summoned yet
3090 m_caster->RemoveGameObject(m_spellInfo->Id, true);
3091
3092 //set state back so finish will be processed
3093 m_spellState = oldState;
3094
3095 finish(false);
3096}
3097
3098void Spell::cast(bool skipCheck)
3099{
3100 // update pointers base at GUIDs to prevent access to non-existed already object
3101 if (!UpdatePointers())
3102 {
3103 // cancel the spell if UpdatePointers() returned false, something wrong happened there
3104 cancel();
3105 return;
3106 }
3107
3108 // cancel at lost explicit target during cast
3109 if (!m_targets.GetObjectTargetGUID().IsEmpty() && !m_targets.GetObjectTarget())
3110 {
3111 cancel();
3112 return;
3113 }
3114
3115 if (Player* playerCaster = m_caster->ToPlayer())
3116 {
3117 // now that we've done the basic check, now run the scripts
3118 // should be done before the spell is actually executed
3119 sScriptMgr->OnPlayerSpellCast(playerCaster, this, skipCheck);
3120
3121 // As of 3.0.2 pets begin attacking their owner's target immediately
3122 // Let any pets know we've attacked something. Check DmgClass for harmful spells only
3123 // This prevents spells such as Hunter's Mark from triggering pet attack
3124 if (this->GetSpellInfo()->DmgClass != SPELL_DAMAGE_CLASS_NONE)
3125 if (Pet* playerPet = playerCaster->GetPet())
3126 if (playerPet->IsAlive() && playerPet->isControlled() && (m_targets.GetTargetMask() & TARGET_FLAG_UNIT))
3127 playerPet->AI()->OwnerAttacked(m_targets.GetUnitTarget());
3128 }
3129
3130 SetExecutedCurrently(true);
3131
3132 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_SET_FACING))
3133 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && m_targets.GetObjectTarget() && m_caster != m_targets.GetObjectTarget())
3134 m_caster->SetInFront(m_targets.GetObjectTarget());
3135
3136 // Should this be done for original caster?
3137 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3138 {
3139 // Set spell which will drop charges for triggered cast spells
3140 // if not successfully cast, will be remove in finish(false)
3141 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, true);
3142 }
3143
3144 CallScriptBeforeCastHandlers();
3145
3146 // skip check if done already (for instant cast spells for example)
3147 if (!skipCheck)
3148 {
3149 SpellCastResult castResult = CheckCast(false);
3150 if (castResult != SPELL_CAST_OK)
3151 {
3152 SendCastResult(castResult);
3153 SendInterrupted(0);
3154 //restore spell mods
3155 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3156 {
3157 m_caster->ToPlayer()->RestoreSpellMods(this);
3158 // cleanup after mod system
3159 // triggered spell pointer can be not removed in some cases
3160 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, false);
3161 }
3162 finish(false);
3163 SetExecutedCurrently(false);
3164 return;
3165 }
3166
3167 // additional check after cast bar completes (must not be in CheckCast)
3168 // if trade not complete then remember it in trade data
3169 if (m_targets.GetTargetMask() & TARGET_FLAG_TRADE_ITEM)
3170 {
3171 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3172 {
3173 if (TradeData* my_trade = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetTradeData())
3174 {
3175 if (!my_trade->IsInAcceptProcess())
3176 {
3177 // Spell will be cast after completing the trade. Silently ignore at this place
3178 my_trade->SetSpell(m_spellInfo->Id, m_CastItem);
3179 SendCastResult(SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT);
3180 SendInterrupted(0);
3181 m_caster->ToPlayer()->RestoreSpellMods(this);
3182 // cleanup after mod system
3183 // triggered spell pointer can be not removed in some cases
3184 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, false);
3185 finish(false);
3186 SetExecutedCurrently(false);
3187 return;
3188 }
3189 }
3190 }
3191 }
3192 }
3193
3194 SelectSpellTargets();
3195
3196 // Spell may be finished after target map check
3197 if (m_spellState == SPELL_STATE_FINISHED)
3198 {
3199 SendInterrupted(0);
3200 //restore spell mods
3201 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3202 {
3203 m_caster->ToPlayer()->RestoreSpellMods(this);
3204 // cleanup after mod system
3205 // triggered spell pointer can be not removed in some cases
3206 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, false);
3207 }
3208 finish(false);
3209 SetExecutedCurrently(false);
3210 return;
3211 }
3212
3213 PrepareTriggersExecutedOnHit();
3214
3215 CallScriptOnCastHandlers();
3216
3217 // traded items have trade slot instead of guid in m_itemTargetGUID
3218 // set to real guid to be sent later to the client
3219 m_targets.UpdateTradeSlotItem();
3220
3221 if (Player* player = m_caster->ToPlayer())
3222 {
3223 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CAST_ITEM) && m_CastItem)
3224 {
3225 player->StartTimedAchievement(ACHIEVEMENT_TIMED_TYPE_ITEM, m_CastItem->GetEntry());
3226 player->UpdateAchievementCriteria(ACHIEVEMENT_CRITERIA_TYPE_USE_ITEM, m_CastItem->GetEntry());
3227 }
3228
3229 player->UpdateAchievementCriteria(ACHIEVEMENT_CRITERIA_TYPE_CAST_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id);
3230 }
3231
3232 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_POWER_AND_REAGENT_COST))
3233 {
3234 // Powers have to be taken before SendSpellGo
3235 TakePower();
3236 TakeReagents(); // we must remove reagents before HandleEffects to allow place crafted item in same slot
3237 }
3238 else if (Item* targetItem = m_targets.GetItemTarget())
3239 {
3240 /// Not own traded item (in trader trade slot) req. reagents including triggered spell case
3241 if (targetItem->GetOwnerGUID() != m_caster->GetGUID())
3242 TakeReagents();
3243 }
3244
3245 // CAST SPELL
3246 SendSpellCooldown();
3247
3248 PrepareScriptHitHandlers();
3249
3250 HandleLaunchPhase();
3251
3252 // we must send smsg_spell_go packet before m_castItem delete in TakeCastItem()...
3253 SendSpellGo();
3254
3255 // Okay, everything is prepared. Now we need to distinguish between immediate and evented delayed spells
3256 if ((m_spellInfo->Speed > 0.0f && !m_spellInfo->IsChanneled()) || m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR4_UNK4))
3257 {
3258 // Remove used for cast item if need (it can be already NULL after TakeReagents call
3259 // in case delayed spell remove item at cast delay start
3260 TakeCastItem();
3261
3262 // Okay, maps created, now prepare flags
3263 m_immediateHandled = false;
3264 m_spellState = SPELL_STATE_DELAYED;
3265 SetDelayStart(0);
3266
3267 if (m_caster->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_CASTING) && !m_caster->IsNonMeleeSpellCast(false, false, true))
3268 m_caster->ClearUnitState(UNIT_STATE_CASTING);
3269 }
3270 else
3271 {
3272 // Immediate spell, no big deal
3273 handle_immediate();
3274 }
3275
3276 CallScriptAfterCastHandlers();
3277
3278 if (const std::vector<int32> *spell_triggered = sSpellMgr->GetSpellLinked(m_spellInfo->Id))
3279 {
3280 for (std::vector<int32>::const_iterator i = spell_triggered->begin(); i != spell_triggered->end(); ++i)
3281 if (*i < 0)
3282 m_caster->RemoveAurasDueToSpell(-(*i));
3283 else
3284 m_caster->CastSpell(m_targets.GetUnitTarget() ? m_targets.GetUnitTarget() : m_caster, *i, true);
3285 }
3286
3287 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3288 {
3289 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, false);
3290
3291 //Clear spell cooldowns after every spell is cast if .cheat cooldown is enabled.
3292 if (m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetCommandStatus(CHEAT_COOLDOWN))
3293 {
3294 m_caster->GetSpellHistory()->ResetCooldown(m_spellInfo->Id, true);
3295 m_caster->GetSpellHistory()->RestoreCharge(m_spellInfo->ChargeCategoryEntry);
3296 }
3297 }
3298
3299 SetExecutedCurrently(false);
3300}
3301
3302void Spell::handle_immediate()
3303{
3304 // start channeling if applicable
3305 if (m_spellInfo->IsChanneled())
3306 {
3307 int32 duration = m_spellInfo->GetDuration();
3308 if (duration > 0)
3309 {
3310 // First mod_duration then haste - see Missile Barrage
3311 // Apply duration mod
3312 if (Player* modOwner = m_caster->GetSpellModOwner())
3313 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_DURATION, duration);
3314
3315 // Apply haste mods
3316 m_caster->ModSpellCastTime(m_spellInfo, duration, this);
3317
3318 m_spellState = SPELL_STATE_CASTING;
3319 m_caster->AddInterruptMask(m_spellInfo->ChannelInterruptFlags);
3320 m_channeledDuration = duration;
3321 SendChannelStart(duration);
3322 }
3323 else if (duration == -1)
3324 {
3325 m_spellState = SPELL_STATE_CASTING;
3326 m_caster->AddInterruptMask(m_spellInfo->ChannelInterruptFlags);
3327 SendChannelStart(duration);
3328 }
3329 }
3330
3331 PrepareTargetProcessing();
3332
3333 // process immediate effects (items, ground, etc.) also initialize some variables
3334 _handle_immediate_phase();
3335
3336 for (std::vector<TargetInfo>::iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
3337 DoAllEffectOnTarget(&(*ihit));
3338
3339 for (std::vector<GOTargetInfo>::iterator ihit = m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
3340 DoAllEffectOnTarget(&(*ihit));
3341
3342 FinishTargetProcessing();
3343
3344 // spell is finished, perform some last features of the spell here
3345 _handle_finish_phase();
3346
3347 // Remove used for cast item if need (it can be already NULL after TakeReagents call
3348 TakeCastItem();
3349
3350 if (m_spellState != SPELL_STATE_CASTING)
3351 finish(true); // successfully finish spell cast (not last in case autorepeat or channel spell)
3352}
3353
3354uint64 Spell::handle_delayed(uint64 t_offset)
3355{
3356 if (!UpdatePointers())
3357 {
3358 // finish the spell if UpdatePointers() returned false, something wrong happened there
3359 finish(false);
3360 return 0;
3361 }
3362
3363 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3364 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, true);
3365
3366 uint64 next_time = 0;
3367
3368 PrepareTargetProcessing();
3369
3370 if (!m_immediateHandled)
3371 {
3372 _handle_immediate_phase();
3373 m_immediateHandled = true;
3374 }
3375
3376 bool single_missile = (m_targets.HasDst());
3377
3378 // now recheck units targeting correctness (need before any effects apply to prevent adding immunity at first effect not allow apply second spell effect and similar cases)
3379 for (std::vector<TargetInfo>::iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
3380 {
3381 if (ihit->processed == false)
3382 {
3383 if (single_missile || ihit->timeDelay <= t_offset)
3384 {
3385 ihit->timeDelay = t_offset;
3386 DoAllEffectOnTarget(&(*ihit));
3387 }
3388 else if (next_time == 0 || ihit->timeDelay < next_time)
3389 next_time = ihit->timeDelay;
3390 }
3391 }
3392
3393 // now recheck gameobject targeting correctness
3394 for (std::vector<GOTargetInfo>::iterator ighit = m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.begin(); ighit != m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.end(); ++ighit)
3395 {
3396 if (ighit->processed == false)
3397 {
3398 if (single_missile || ighit->timeDelay <= t_offset)
3399 DoAllEffectOnTarget(&(*ighit));
3400 else if (next_time == 0 || ighit->timeDelay < next_time)
3401 next_time = ighit->timeDelay;
3402 }
3403 }
3404
3405 FinishTargetProcessing();
3406
3407 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3408 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, false);
3409
3410 // All targets passed - need finish phase
3411 if (next_time == 0)
3412 {
3413 // spell is finished, perform some last features of the spell here
3414 _handle_finish_phase();
3415
3416 finish(true); // successfully finish spell cast
3417
3418 // return zero, spell is finished now
3419 return 0;
3420 }
3421 else
3422 {
3423 // spell is unfinished, return next execution time
3424 return next_time;
3425 }
3426}
3427
3428void Spell::_handle_immediate_phase()
3429{
3430 m_spellAura = NULL;
3431 // initialize Diminishing Returns Data
3432 m_diminishLevel = DIMINISHING_LEVEL_1;
3433 m_diminishGroup = DIMINISHING_NONE;
3434
3435 // handle some immediate features of the spell here
3436 HandleThreatSpells();
3437
3438 PrepareScriptHitHandlers();
3439
3440 // handle effects with SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_HIT mode
3441 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
3442 {
3443 // don't do anything for empty effect
3444 if (!effect || !effect->IsEffect())
3445 continue;
3446
3447 // call effect handlers to handle destination hit
3448 HandleEffects(NULL, NULL, NULL, effect->EffectIndex, SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_HIT);
3449 }
3450
3451 // process items
3452 for (std::vector<ItemTargetInfo>::iterator ihit = m_UniqueItemInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueItemInfo.end(); ++ihit)
3453 DoAllEffectOnTarget(&(*ihit));
3454
3455 if (!m_originalCaster)
3456 return;
3457 // Handle procs on cast
3458 /// @todo finish new proc system:P
3459 if (m_UniqueTargetInfo.empty() && m_targets.HasDst())
3460 {
3461 uint32 procAttacker = m_procAttacker;
3462 if (!procAttacker)
3463 procAttacker |= PROC_FLAG_DONE_SPELL_MAGIC_DMG_CLASS_POS;
3464
3465 // Proc the spells that have DEST target
3466 m_originalCaster->ProcDamageAndSpell(NULL, procAttacker, 0, m_procEx | PROC_EX_NORMAL_HIT, 0, BASE_ATTACK, m_spellInfo, m_triggeredByAuraSpell);
3467 }
3468}
3469
3470void Spell::_handle_finish_phase()
3471{
3472 if (m_caster->m_movedPlayer)
3473 {
3474 // Take for real after all targets are processed
3475 if (m_needComboPoints)
3476 m_caster->m_movedPlayer->ClearComboPoints();
3477
3478 // Real add combo points from effects
3479 if (m_comboPointGain)
3480 m_caster->m_movedPlayer->GainSpellComboPoints(m_comboPointGain);
3481 }
3482
3483 if (m_caster->m_extraAttacks && HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_ADD_EXTRA_ATTACKS))
3484 {
3485 if (Unit* victim = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, m_targets.GetOrigUnitTargetGUID()))
3486 m_caster->HandleProcExtraAttackFor(victim);
3487 else
3488 m_caster->m_extraAttacks = 0;
3489 }
3490
3491 /// @todo trigger proc phase finish here
3492}
3493
3494void Spell::SendSpellCooldown()
3495{
3496 if (m_CastItem)
3497 m_caster->GetSpellHistory()->HandleCooldowns(m_spellInfo, m_CastItem, this);
3498 else
3499 m_caster->GetSpellHistory()->HandleCooldowns(m_spellInfo, m_castItemEntry, this);
3500}
3501
3502void Spell::update(uint32 difftime)
3503{
3504 // update pointers based at it's GUIDs
3505 if (!UpdatePointers())
3506 {
3507 // cancel the spell if UpdatePointers() returned false, something wrong happened there
3508 cancel();
3509 return;
3510 }
3511
3512 if (!m_targets.GetUnitTargetGUID().IsEmpty() && !m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
3513 {
3514 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell %u is cancelled due to removal of target.", m_spellInfo->Id);
3515 cancel();
3516 return;
3517 }
3518
3519 // check if the player caster has moved before the spell finished
3520 // with the exception of spells affected with SPELL_AURA_CAST_WHILE_WALKING effect
3521 SpellEffectInfo const* effect = GetEffect(EFFECT_0);
3522 if ((m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && m_timer != 0) &&
3523 m_caster->isMoving() && (m_spellInfo->InterruptFlags & SPELL_INTERRUPT_FLAG_MOVEMENT) &&
3524 ((effect && effect->Effect != SPELL_EFFECT_STUCK) || !m_caster->HasUnitMovementFlag(MOVEMENTFLAG_FALLING_FAR)) &&
3525 !m_caster->HasAuraTypeWithAffectMask(SPELL_AURA_CAST_WHILE_WALKING, m_spellInfo))
3526 {
3527 // don't cancel for melee, autorepeat, triggered and instant spells
3528 if (!IsNextMeleeSwingSpell() && !IsAutoRepeat() && !IsTriggered())
3529 cancel();
3530 }
3531
3532 switch (m_spellState)
3533 {
3534 case SPELL_STATE_PREPARING:
3535 {
3536 if (m_timer > 0)
3537 {
3538 if (difftime >= (uint32)m_timer)
3539 m_timer = 0;
3540 else
3541 m_timer -= difftime;
3542 }
3543
3544 if (m_timer == 0 && !IsNextMeleeSwingSpell() && !IsAutoRepeat())
3545 // don't CheckCast for instant spells - done in spell::prepare, skip duplicate checks, needed for range checks for example
3546 cast(!m_casttime);
3547 break;
3548 }
3549 case SPELL_STATE_CASTING:
3550 {
3551 if (m_timer)
3552 {
3553 // check if there are alive targets left
3554 if (!UpdateChanneledTargetList())
3555 {
3556 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Channeled spell %d is removed due to lack of targets", m_spellInfo->Id);
3557 SendChannelUpdate(0);
3558 finish();
3559 }
3560
3561 if (m_timer > 0)
3562 {
3563 if (difftime >= (uint32)m_timer)
3564 m_timer = 0;
3565 else
3566 m_timer -= difftime;
3567 }
3568 }
3569
3570 if (m_timer == 0)
3571 {
3572 SendChannelUpdate(0);
3573 finish();
3574 }
3575 break;
3576 }
3577 default:
3578 break;
3579 }
3580}
3581
3582void Spell::finish(bool ok)
3583{
3584 if (!m_caster)
3585 return;
3586
3587 if (m_spellState == SPELL_STATE_FINISHED)
3588 return;
3589 m_spellState = SPELL_STATE_FINISHED;
3590
3591 if (m_spellInfo->IsChanneled())
3592 m_caster->UpdateInterruptMask();
3593
3594 if (m_caster->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_CASTING) && !m_caster->IsNonMeleeSpellCast(false, false, true))
3595 m_caster->ClearUnitState(UNIT_STATE_CASTING);
3596
3597 // Unsummon summon as possessed creatures on spell cancel
3598 if (m_spellInfo->IsChanneled() && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3599 {
3600 if (Unit* charm = m_caster->GetCharm())
3601 if (charm->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT
3602 && charm->ToCreature()->HasUnitTypeMask(UNIT_MASK_PUPPET)
3603 && charm->GetUInt32Value(UNIT_CREATED_BY_SPELL) == m_spellInfo->Id)
3604 ((Puppet*)charm)->UnSummon();
3605 }
3606
3607 if (Creature* creatureCaster = m_caster->ToCreature())
3608 creatureCaster->ReleaseFocus(this);
3609
3610 if (!ok)
3611 return;
3612
3613 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && m_caster->IsSummon())
3614 {
3615 // Unsummon statue
3616 uint32 spell = m_caster->GetUInt32Value(UNIT_CREATED_BY_SPELL);
3617 SpellInfo const* spellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(spell);
3618 if (spellInfo && spellInfo->SpellIconID == 2056)
3619 {
3620 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Statue %s is unsummoned in spell %d finish", m_caster->GetGUID().ToString().c_str(), m_spellInfo->Id);
3621 m_caster->setDeathState(JUST_DIED);
3622 return;
3623 }
3624 }
3625
3626 if (IsAutoActionResetSpell())
3627 {
3628 bool found = false;
3629 Unit::AuraEffectList const& vIgnoreReset = m_caster->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_IGNORE_MELEE_RESET);
3630 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator i = vIgnoreReset.begin(); i != vIgnoreReset.end(); ++i)
3631 {
3632 if ((*i)->IsAffectingSpell(m_spellInfo))
3633 {
3634 found = true;
3635 break;
3636 }
3637 }
3638 if (!found && !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_NOT_RESET_AUTO_ACTIONS))
3639 {
3640 m_caster->resetAttackTimer(BASE_ATTACK);
3641 if (m_caster->haveOffhandWeapon())
3642 m_caster->resetAttackTimer(OFF_ATTACK);
3643 m_caster->resetAttackTimer(RANGED_ATTACK);
3644 }
3645 }
3646
3647 // potions disabled by client, send event "not in combat" if need
3648 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3649 {
3650 if (!m_triggeredByAuraSpell)
3651 m_caster->ToPlayer()->UpdatePotionCooldown(this);
3652
3653 // triggered spell pointer can be not set in some cases
3654 // this is needed for proper apply of triggered spell mods
3655 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, true);
3656
3657 // Take mods after trigger spell (needed for 14177 to affect 48664)
3658 // mods are taken only on succesfull cast and independantly from targets of the spell
3659 m_caster->ToPlayer()->RemoveSpellMods(this);
3660 m_caster->ToPlayer()->SetSpellModTakingSpell(this, false);
3661 }
3662
3663 // Stop Attack for some spells
3664 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_STOP_ATTACK_TARGET))
3665 m_caster->AttackStop();
3666}
3667
3668void Spell::SendCastResult(SpellCastResult result)
3669{
3670 if (result == SPELL_CAST_OK)
3671 return;
3672
3673 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
3674 return;
3675
3676 if (m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetSession()->PlayerLoading()) // don't send cast results at loading time
3677 return;
3678
3679 SendCastResult(m_caster->ToPlayer(), m_spellInfo, m_cast_count, result, m_customError, SMSG_CAST_FAILED, m_misc.Raw.Data);
3680}
3681
3682void Spell::SendPetCastResult(SpellCastResult result)
3683{
3684 if (result == SPELL_CAST_OK)
3685 return;
3686
3687 Unit* owner = m_caster->GetCharmerOrOwner();
3688 if (!owner || owner->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
3689 return;
3690
3691 SendCastResult(owner->ToPlayer(), m_spellInfo, m_cast_count, result, SPELL_CUSTOM_ERROR_NONE, SMSG_PET_CAST_FAILED, m_misc.Raw.Data);
3692}
3693
3694void Spell::SendCastResult(Player* caster, SpellInfo const* spellInfo, uint8 cast_count, SpellCastResult result, SpellCustomErrors customError /*= SPELL_CUSTOM_ERROR_NONE*/, OpcodeServer opcode /*= SMSG_CAST_FAILED*/, uint32* misc /*= nullptr*/)
3695{
3696 if (result == SPELL_CAST_OK)
3697 return;
3698
3699 WorldPackets::Spells::CastFailed packet(opcode);
3700 packet.CastID = cast_count;
3701 packet.SpellID = spellInfo->Id;
3702 packet.Reason = result;
3703
3704 switch (result)
3705 {
3706 case SPELL_FAILED_NOT_READY:
3707 packet.FailedArg1 = 0; // unknown (value 1 update cooldowns on client flag)
3708 break;
3709 case SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_SPELL_FOCUS:
3710 packet.FailedArg1 = spellInfo->RequiresSpellFocus; // SpellFocusObject.dbc id
3711 break;
3712 case SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_AREA: // AreaTable.dbc id
3713 // hardcode areas limitation case
3714 switch (spellInfo->Id)
3715 {
3716 case 41617: // Cenarion Mana Salve
3717 case 41619: // Cenarion Healing Salve
3718 packet.FailedArg1 = 3905;
3719 break;
3720 case 41618: // Bottled Nethergon Energy
3721 case 41620: // Bottled Nethergon Vapor
3722 packet.FailedArg1 = 3842;
3723 break;
3724 case 45373: // Bloodberry Elixir
3725 packet.FailedArg1 = 4075;
3726 break;
3727 default: // default case (don't must be)
3728 packet.FailedArg1 = 0;
3729 break;
3730 }
3731 break;
3732 case SPELL_FAILED_TOTEMS:
3733 if (spellInfo->Totem[0])
3734 packet.FailedArg1 = spellInfo->Totem[0];
3735 if (spellInfo->Totem[1])
3736 packet.FailedArg2 = spellInfo->Totem[1];
3737 break;
3738 case SPELL_FAILED_TOTEM_CATEGORY:
3739 if (spellInfo->TotemCategory[0])
3740 packet.FailedArg1 = spellInfo->TotemCategory[0];
3741 if (spellInfo->TotemCategory[1])
3742 packet.FailedArg2 = spellInfo->TotemCategory[1];
3743 break;
3744 case SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM_CLASS:
3745 case SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM_CLASS_MAINHAND:
3746 case SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM_CLASS_OFFHAND:
3747 packet.FailedArg1 = spellInfo->EquippedItemClass;
3748 packet.FailedArg2 = spellInfo->EquippedItemSubClassMask;
3749 break;
3750 case SPELL_FAILED_TOO_MANY_OF_ITEM:
3751 {
3752 uint32 item = 0;
3753 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : spellInfo->GetEffectsForDifficulty(caster->GetMap()->GetDifficultyID()))
3754 if (effect->ItemType)
3755 item = effect->ItemType;
3756 ItemTemplate const* proto = sObjectMgr->GetItemTemplate(item);
3757 if (proto && proto->GetItemLimitCategory())
3758 packet.FailedArg1 = proto->GetItemLimitCategory();
3759 break;
3760 }
3761 case SPELL_FAILED_PREVENTED_BY_MECHANIC:
3762 packet.FailedArg1 = spellInfo->GetAllEffectsMechanicMask(); // SpellMechanic.dbc id
3763 break;
3764 case SPELL_FAILED_NEED_EXOTIC_AMMO:
3765 packet.FailedArg1 = spellInfo->EquippedItemSubClassMask; // seems correct...
3766 break;
3767 case SPELL_FAILED_NEED_MORE_ITEMS:
3768 packet.FailedArg1 = 0; // Item id
3769 packet.FailedArg2 = 0; // Item count?
3770 break;
3771 case SPELL_FAILED_MIN_SKILL:
3772 packet.FailedArg1 = 0; // SkillLine.dbc id
3773 packet.FailedArg2 = 0; // required skill value
3774 break;
3775 case SPELL_FAILED_FISHING_TOO_LOW:
3776 packet.FailedArg1 = 0; // required fishing skill
3777 break;
3778 case SPELL_FAILED_CUSTOM_ERROR:
3779 packet.FailedArg1 = customError;
3780 break;
3781 case SPELL_FAILED_SILENCED:
3782 packet.FailedArg1 = 0; // Unknown
3783 break;
3784 case SPELL_FAILED_REAGENTS:
3785 {
3786 uint32 missingItem = 0;
3787 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_REAGENTS; i++)
3788 {
3789 if (spellInfo->Reagent[i] <= 0)
3790 continue;
3791
3792 uint32 itemid = spellInfo->Reagent[i];
3793 uint32 itemcount = spellInfo->ReagentCount[i];
3794
3795 if (!caster->HasItemCount(itemid, itemcount))
3796 {
3797 missingItem = itemid;
3798 break;
3799 }
3800 }
3801
3802 packet.FailedArg1 = missingItem; // first missing item
3803 break;
3804 }
3805 case SPELL_FAILED_CANT_UNTALENT:
3806 {
3807 if (misc)
3808 if (TalentEntry const* talent = sTalentStore.LookupEntry(misc[0]))
3809 packet.FailedArg1 = talent->SpellID;
3810 break;
3811 }
3812 // TODO: SPELL_FAILED_NOT_STANDING
3813 default:
3814 break;
3815 }
3816
3817 caster->GetSession()->SendPacket(packet.Write());
3818}
3819
3820void Spell::SendSpellStart()
3821{
3822 if (!IsNeedSendToClient())
3823 return;
3824
3825 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Sending SMSG_SPELL_START id=%u", m_spellInfo->Id);
3826
3827 uint32 castFlags = CAST_FLAG_HAS_TRAJECTORY;
3828 uint32 schoolImmunityMask = m_caster->GetSchoolImmunityMask();
3829 uint32 mechanicImmunityMask = m_caster->GetMechanicImmunityMask();
3830 if (schoolImmunityMask || mechanicImmunityMask)
3831 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_IMMUNITY;
3832
3833 if ((IsTriggered() && !m_spellInfo->IsAutoRepeatRangedSpell()) || m_triggeredByAuraSpell)
3834 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_PENDING;
3835
3836 if ((m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER ||
3837 (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && m_caster->IsPet()))
3838 && std::find_if(m_powerCost.begin(), m_powerCost.end(), [](SpellInfo::CostData const& cost) { return cost.Power != POWER_HEALTH; }) != m_powerCost.end())
3839 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_POWER_LEFT_SELF;
3840
3841 if (m_spellInfo->RuneCostID &&
3842 std::find_if(m_powerCost.begin(), m_powerCost.end(), [](SpellInfo::CostData const& cost) { return cost.Power == POWER_RUNES; }) != m_powerCost.end())
3843 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_NO_GCD; // not needed, but Blizzard sends it
3844
3845 WorldPackets::Spells::SpellStart packet;
3846 WorldPackets::Spells::SpellCastData& castData = packet.Cast;
3847
3848 if (m_CastItem)
3849 castData.CasterGUID = m_CastItem->GetGUID();
3850 else
3851 castData.CasterGUID = m_caster->GetGUID();
3852
3853 castData.CasterUnit = m_caster->GetGUID();
3854 castData.CastID = m_cast_count; // pending spell cast?
3855 castData.SpellID = m_spellInfo->Id;
3856 castData.SpellXSpellVisualID = m_SpellVisual;
3857 castData.CastFlags = castFlags;
3858 castData.CastFlagsEx = m_castFlagsEx;
3859 castData.CastTime = m_casttime;
3860
3861 m_targets.Write(castData.Target);
3862
3863 if (castFlags & CAST_FLAG_POWER_LEFT_SELF)
3864 {
3865 for (SpellInfo::CostData const& cost : m_powerCost)
3866 {
3867 WorldPackets::Spells::SpellPowerData powerData;
3868 powerData.Type = cost.Power;
3869 powerData.Cost = m_caster->GetPower(cost.Power);
3870 castData.RemainingPower.push_back(powerData);
3871 }
3872 }
3873
3874 if (castFlags & CAST_FLAG_RUNE_LIST) // rune cooldowns list
3875 {
3876 castData.RemainingRunes = boost::in_place();
3877
3878 //TODO: There is a crash caused by a spell with CAST_FLAG_RUNE_LIST casted by a creature
3879 //The creature is the mover of a player, so HandleCastSpellOpcode uses it as the caster
3880 if (Player* player = m_caster->ToPlayer())
3881 {
3882 castData.RemainingRunes->Start = m_runesState; // runes state before
3883 castData.RemainingRunes->Count = player->GetRunesState(); // runes state after
3884 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_RUNES; ++i)
3885 {
3886 // float casts ensure the division is performed on floats as we need float result
3887 float baseCd = float(player->GetRuneBaseCooldown(i));
3888 castData.RemainingRunes->Cooldowns.push_back((baseCd - float(player->GetRuneCooldown(i))) / baseCd * 255); // rune cooldown passed
3889 }
3890 }
3891 else
3892 {
3893 castData.RemainingRunes->Start = 0;
3894 castData.RemainingRunes->Count = 0;
3895 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_RUNES; ++i)
3896 castData.RemainingRunes->Cooldowns.push_back(0);
3897 }
3898 }
3899
3900 /** @todo implement spell ammo packet data
3901 if (castFlags & CAST_FLAG_PROJECTILE)
3902 {
3903 castData.Ammo.DisplayID = 0;
3904 castData.Ammo.InventoryType = 0;
3905 }**/
3906
3907 if (castFlags & CAST_FLAG_IMMUNITY)
3908 {
3909 castData.Immunities.School = schoolImmunityMask;
3910 castData.Immunities.Value = mechanicImmunityMask;
3911 }
3912
3913 /** @todo implement heal prediction packet data
3914 if (castFlags & CAST_FLAG_HEAL_PREDICTION)
3915 {
3916 castData.Predict.BeconGUID = ??
3917 castData.Predict.Points = 0;
3918 castData.Predict.Type = 0;
3919 }**/
3920
3921 m_caster->SendMessageToSet(packet.Write(), true);
3922}
3923
3924void Spell::SendSpellGo()
3925{
3926 // not send invisible spell casting
3927 if (!IsNeedSendToClient())
3928 return;
3929
3930 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Sending SMSG_SPELL_GO id=%u", m_spellInfo->Id);
3931
3932 uint32 castFlags = CAST_FLAG_UNKNOWN_9;
3933
3934 // triggered spells with spell visual != 0
3935 if ((IsTriggered() && !m_spellInfo->IsAutoRepeatRangedSpell()) || m_triggeredByAuraSpell)
3936 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_PENDING;
3937
3938 if ((m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER ||
3939 (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && m_caster->IsPet()))
3940 && std::find_if(m_powerCost.begin(), m_powerCost.end(), [](SpellInfo::CostData const& cost) { return cost.Power != POWER_HEALTH; }) != m_powerCost.end())
3941 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_POWER_LEFT_SELF; // should only be sent to self, but the current messaging doesn't make that possible
3942
3943 if ((m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
3944 && (m_caster->getClass() == CLASS_DEATH_KNIGHT)
3945 && m_spellInfo->RuneCostID
3946 && std::find_if(m_powerCost.begin(), m_powerCost.end(), [](SpellInfo::CostData const& cost) { return cost.Power == POWER_RUNES; }) != m_powerCost.end()
3947 && !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_POWER_AND_REAGENT_COST))
3948 {
3949 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_NO_GCD; // not needed, but Blizzard sends it
3950 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_RUNE_LIST; // rune cooldowns list
3951 }
3952
3953 if (HasEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_ACTIVATE_RUNE))
3954 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_RUNE_LIST; // rune cooldowns list
3955
3956 if (m_targets.HasTraj())
3957 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_ADJUST_MISSILE;
3958
3959 if (!m_spellInfo->StartRecoveryTime)
3960 castFlags |= CAST_FLAG_NO_GCD;
3961
3962 WorldPackets::Spells::SpellGo packet;
3963 WorldPackets::Spells::SpellCastData& castData = packet.Cast;
3964
3965 if (m_CastItem)
3966 castData.CasterGUID = m_CastItem->GetGUID();
3967 else
3968 castData.CasterGUID = m_caster->GetGUID();
3969
3970 castData.CasterUnit = m_caster->GetGUID();
3971 castData.CastID = m_cast_count; // pending spell cast?
3972 castData.SpellID = m_spellInfo->Id;
3973 castData.SpellXSpellVisualID = m_SpellVisual;
3974 castData.CastFlags = castFlags;
3975 castData.CastFlagsEx = m_castFlagsEx;
3976 castData.CastTime = getMSTime();
3977
3978 UpdateSpellCastDataTargets(castData);
3979
3980 m_targets.Write(castData.Target);
3981
3982 if (castFlags & CAST_FLAG_POWER_LEFT_SELF)
3983 {
3984 for (SpellInfo::CostData const& cost : m_powerCost)
3985 {
3986 WorldPackets::Spells::SpellPowerData powerData;
3987 powerData.Type = cost.Power;
3988 powerData.Cost = m_caster->GetPower(cost.Power);
3989 castData.RemainingPower.push_back(powerData);
3990 }
3991 }
3992
3993 if (castFlags & CAST_FLAG_RUNE_LIST) // rune cooldowns list
3994 {
3995 castData.RemainingRunes = boost::in_place();
3996
3997 //TODO: There is a crash caused by a spell with CAST_FLAG_RUNE_LIST casted by a creature
3998 //The creature is the mover of a player, so HandleCastSpellOpcode uses it as the caster
3999 if (Player* player = m_caster->ToPlayer())
4000 {
4001 castData.RemainingRunes->Start = m_runesState; // runes state before
4002 castData.RemainingRunes->Count = player->GetRunesState(); // runes state after
4003 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_RUNES; ++i)
4004 {
4005 // float casts ensure the division is performed on floats as we need float result
4006 float baseCd = float(player->GetRuneBaseCooldown(i));
4007 castData.RemainingRunes->Cooldowns.push_back((baseCd - float(player->GetRuneCooldown(i))) / baseCd * 255); // rune cooldown passed
4008 }
4009 }
4010 else
4011 {
4012 castData.RemainingRunes->Start = 0;
4013 castData.RemainingRunes->Count = 0;
4014 for (uint8 i = 0; i < MAX_RUNES; ++i)
4015 castData.RemainingRunes->Cooldowns.push_back(0);
4016 }
4017 }
4018
4019 if (castFlags & CAST_FLAG_ADJUST_MISSILE)
4020 {
4021 castData.MissileTrajectory.TravelTime = m_delayMoment;
4022 castData.MissileTrajectory.Pitch = m_targets.GetPitch();
4023 }
4024
4025 m_caster->SendMessageToSet(packet.Write(), true);
4026}
4027
4028/// Writes miss and hit targets for a SMSG_SPELL_GO packet
4029void Spell::UpdateSpellCastDataTargets(WorldPackets::Spells::SpellCastData& data)
4030{
4031 // This function also fill data for channeled spells:
4032 // m_needAliveTargetMask req for stop channeling if one target die
4033 for (TargetInfo& targetInfo : m_UniqueTargetInfo)
4034 {
4035 if (targetInfo.effectMask == 0) // No effect apply - all immune add state
4036 // possibly SPELL_MISS_IMMUNE2 for this??
4037 targetInfo.missCondition = SPELL_MISS_IMMUNE2;
4038
4039 if (targetInfo.missCondition == SPELL_MISS_NONE) // hits
4040 {
4041 data.HitTargets.push_back(targetInfo.targetGUID);
4042
4043 m_channelTargetEffectMask |= targetInfo.effectMask;
4044 }
4045 else // misses
4046 {
4047 data.MissTargets.push_back(targetInfo.targetGUID);
4048
4049 WorldPackets::Spells::SpellMissStatus missStatus;
4050 missStatus.Reason = targetInfo.missCondition;
4051 if (targetInfo.missCondition == SPELL_MISS_REFLECT)
4052 missStatus.ReflectStatus = targetInfo.reflectResult;
4053
4054 data.MissStatus.push_back(missStatus);
4055 }
4056 }
4057
4058 for (GOTargetInfo const& targetInfo : m_UniqueGOTargetInfo)
4059 data.HitTargets.push_back(targetInfo.targetGUID); // Always hits
4060
4061 // Reset m_needAliveTargetMask for non channeled spell
4062 if (!m_spellInfo->IsChanneled())
4063 m_channelTargetEffectMask = 0;
4064}
4065
4066void Spell::SendSpellExecuteLog()
4067{
4068 WorldPackets::CombatLog::SpellExecuteLog spellExecuteLog;
4069
4070 spellExecuteLog.Caster = m_caster->GetGUID();
4071 spellExecuteLog.SpellID = m_spellInfo->Id;
4072
4073 if (_powerDrainTargets->empty() && _extraAttacksTargets->empty() &&
4074 _durabilityDamageTargets->empty() && _genericVictimTargets->empty() &&
4075 _tradeSkillTargets->empty() && _feedPetTargets->empty())
4076 return;
4077
4078 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
4079 {
4080 WorldPackets::CombatLog::SpellExecuteLog::SpellLogEffect spellLogEffect;
4081 if (!effect)
4082 continue;
4083
4084 spellLogEffect.Effect = effect->Effect;
4085
4086 for (SpellLogEffectPowerDrainParams const& powerDrainParam : _powerDrainTargets[effect->EffectIndex])
4087 spellLogEffect.PowerDrainTargets.push_back(powerDrainParam);
4088
4089 for (SpellLogEffectExtraAttacksParams const& extraAttacksTarget : _extraAttacksTargets[effect->EffectIndex])
4090 spellLogEffect.ExtraAttacksTargets.push_back(extraAttacksTarget);
4091
4092 for (SpellLogEffectDurabilityDamageParams const& durabilityDamageTarget : _durabilityDamageTargets[effect->EffectIndex])
4093 spellLogEffect.DurabilityDamageTargets.push_back(durabilityDamageTarget);
4094
4095 for (SpellLogEffectGenericVictimParams const& genericVictimTarget : _genericVictimTargets[effect->EffectIndex])
4096 spellLogEffect.GenericVictimTargets.push_back(genericVictimTarget);
4097
4098 for (SpellLogEffectTradeSkillItemParams const& tradeSkillTarget : _tradeSkillTargets[effect->EffectIndex])
4099 spellLogEffect.TradeSkillTargets.push_back(tradeSkillTarget);
4100
4101 for (SpellLogEffectFeedPetParams const& feedPetTarget : _feedPetTargets[effect->EffectIndex])
4102 spellLogEffect.FeedPetTargets.push_back(feedPetTarget);
4103
4104 spellExecuteLog.Effects.push_back(spellLogEffect);
4105 }
4106
4107 m_caster->SendCombatLogMessage(&spellExecuteLog);
4108}

4224 failedPacket.Reason = result;

4228void Spell::SendChannelUpdate(uint32 time)
4229{
4230 if (time == 0)
4231 {
4232 m_caster->SetChannelObjectGuid(ObjectGuid::Empty);
4233 m_caster->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_CHANNEL_SPELL, 0);
4234 }

4237 spellChannelUpdate.CasterGUID = m_caster->GetGUID();

4240}

4242void Spell::SendChannelStart(uint32 duration)
4243{
4244 ObjectGuid channelTarget = m_targets.GetObjectTargetGUID();
4245 if (!channelTarget && !m_spellInfo->NeedsExplicitUnitTarget())
4246 if (m_UniqueTargetInfo.size() + m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.size() == 1) // this is for TARGET_SELECT_CATEGORY_NEARBY
4247 channelTarget = !m_UniqueTargetInfo.empty() ? m_UniqueTargetInfo.front().targetGUID : m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.front().targetGUID;
4248
4249 WorldPackets::Spells::SpellChannelStart spellChannelStart;
4250 spellChannelStart.CasterGUID = m_caster->GetGUID();
4251 spellChannelStart.SpellID = m_spellInfo->Id;
4252 spellChannelStart.ChannelDuration = duration;
4253 m_caster->SendMessageToSet(spellChannelStart.Write(), true);
4254
4255 uint32 schoolImmunityMask = m_caster->GetSchoolImmunityMask();
4256 uint32 mechanicImmunityMask = m_caster->GetMechanicImmunityMask();
4257
4258 if (schoolImmunityMask || mechanicImmunityMask)
4259 {
4260 spellChannelStart.InterruptImmunities = boost::in_place();
4261 spellChannelStart.InterruptImmunities->SchoolImmunities = schoolImmunityMask;
4262 spellChannelStart.InterruptImmunities->Immunities = mechanicImmunityMask;
4263 }
4264
4265 m_timer = duration;
4266 if (!channelTarget.IsEmpty())
4267 m_caster->SetChannelObjectGuid(channelTarget);
4268
4269 m_caster->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_CHANNEL_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id);
4270 m_caster->SetUInt32Value(UNIT_CHANNEL_SPELL_X_SPELL_VISUAL, m_spellInfo->GetSpellXSpellVisualId(m_caster->GetMap()->GetDifficultyID()));
4271}
4272
4273void Spell::SendResurrectRequest(Player* target)
4274{
4275 // get resurrector name for creature resurrections, otherwise packet will be not accepted
4276 // for player resurrections the name is looked up by guid
4277 std::string const sentName(m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER
4278 ? "" : m_caster->GetNameForLocaleIdx(target->GetSession()->GetSessionDbLocaleIndex()));
4279
4280 WorldPackets::Spells::ResurrectRequest resurrectRequest;
4281 resurrectRequest.ResurrectOffererGUID = m_caster->GetGUID();
4282 resurrectRequest.ResurrectOffererVirtualRealmAddress = GetVirtualRealmAddress();
4283
4284 if (Pet* pet = target->GetPet())
4285 {
4286 if (CharmInfo* charmInfo = pet->GetCharmInfo())
4287 resurrectRequest.PetNumber = charmInfo->GetPetNumber();
4288 }
4289
4290 resurrectRequest.SpellID = m_spellInfo->Id;
4291
4292 //packet.ReadBit("UseTimer"); /// @todo: 6.x Has to be implemented
4293 resurrectRequest.Sickness = m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER; // "you'll be afflicted with resurrection sickness"
4294
4295 resurrectRequest.Name = sentName;
4296
4297 target->GetSession()->SendPacket(resurrectRequest.Write());
4298}
4299
4300void Spell::TakeCastItem()
4301{
4302 if (!m_CastItem)
4303 return;
4304
4305 Player* player = m_caster->ToPlayer();
4306 if (!player)
4307 return;
4308
4309 // not remove cast item at triggered spell (equipping, weapon damage, etc)
4310 if (_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CAST_ITEM)
4311 return;
4312
4313 ItemTemplate const* proto = m_CastItem->GetTemplate();
4314
4315 if (!proto)
4316 {
4317 // This code is to avoid a crash
4318 // I'm not sure, if this is really an error, but I guess every item needs a prototype
4319 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Cast item has no item prototype %s", m_CastItem->GetGUID().ToString().c_str());
4320 return;
4321 }
4322
4323 bool expendable = false;
4324 bool withoutCharges = false;
4325
4326 for (uint8 i = 0; i < proto->Effects.size() && i < 5; ++i)
4327 {
4328 // item has limited charges
4329 if (proto->Effects[i]->Charges)
4330 {
4331 if (proto->Effects[i]->Charges < 0)
4332 expendable = true;
4333
4334 int32 charges = m_CastItem->GetSpellCharges(i);
4335
4336 // item has charges left
4337 if (charges)
4338 {
4339 (charges > 0) ? --charges : ++charges; // abs(charges) less at 1 after use
4340 if (proto->GetMaxStackSize() == 1)
4341 m_CastItem->SetSpellCharges(i, charges);
4342 m_CastItem->SetState(ITEM_CHANGED, player);
4343 }
4344
4345 // all charges used
4346 withoutCharges = (charges == 0);
4347 }
4348 }
4349
4350 if (expendable && withoutCharges)
4351 {
4352 uint32 count = 1;
4353 m_caster->ToPlayer()->DestroyItemCount(m_CastItem, count, true);
4354
4355 // prevent crash at access to deleted m_targets.GetItemTarget
4356 if (m_CastItem == m_targets.GetItemTarget())
4357 m_targets.SetItemTarget(NULL);
4358
4359 m_CastItem = NULL;
4360 m_castItemGUID.Clear();
4361 m_castItemEntry = 0;
4362 }
4363}
4364
4365void Spell::TakePower()
4366{
4367 if (m_CastItem || m_triggeredByAuraSpell)
4368 return;
4369
4370 //Don't take power if the spell is cast while .cheat power is enabled.
4371 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
4372 {
4373 if (m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetCommandStatus(CHEAT_POWER))
4374 return;
4375 }
4376
4377 for (SpellInfo::CostData& cost : m_powerCost)
4378 {
4379 Powers powerType = Powers(cost.Power);
4380 bool hit = true;
4381 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
4382 {
4383 if (powerType == POWER_RAGE || powerType == POWER_ENERGY || powerType == POWER_RUNES)
4384 {
4385 ObjectGuid targetGUID = m_targets.GetUnitTargetGUID();
4386 if (!targetGUID.IsEmpty())
4387 {
4388 for (std::vector<TargetInfo>::iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
4389 {
4390 if (ihit->targetGUID == targetGUID)
4391 {
4392 if (ihit->missCondition != SPELL_MISS_NONE)
4393 {
4394 hit = false;
4395 //lower spell cost on fail (by talent aura)
4396 if (Player* modOwner = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetSpellModOwner())
4397 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_SPELL_COST_REFUND_ON_FAIL, cost.Amount);
4398 }
4399 break;
4400 }
4401 }
4402 }
4403 }
4404 }
4405
4406 if (powerType == POWER_RUNES)
4407 {
4408 TakeRunePower(hit);
4409 continue;
4410 }
4411
4412 if (!cost.Amount)
4413 continue;
4414
4415 // health as power used
4416 if (powerType == POWER_HEALTH)
4417 {
4418 m_caster->ModifyHealth(-cost.Amount);
4419 continue;
4420 }
4421
4422 if (powerType >= MAX_POWERS)
4423 {
4424 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Spell::TakePower: Unknown power type '%d'", powerType);
4425 continue;
4426 }
4427
4428 if (hit)
4429 m_caster->ModifyPower(powerType, -cost.Amount);
4430 else
4431 m_caster->ModifyPower(powerType, -irand(0, cost.Amount / 4));
4432 }
4433}
4434
4435SpellCastResult Spell::CheckRuneCost(uint32 runeCostID)
4436{
4437 if (std::find_if(m_powerCost.begin(), m_powerCost.end(), [](SpellInfo::CostData const& cost) { return cost.Power == POWER_RUNES; }) == m_powerCost.end() || !runeCostID)
4438 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
4439
4440 Player* player = m_caster->ToPlayer();
4441 if (!player)
4442 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
4443
4444 if (player->getClass() != CLASS_DEATH_KNIGHT)
4445 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
4446
4447 SpellRuneCostEntry const* src = sSpellRuneCostStore.LookupEntry(runeCostID);
4448 if (!src)
4449 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
4450
4451 if (src->NoRuneCost())
4452 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
4453
4454 int32 runeCost[NUM_RUNE_TYPES]; // blood, frost, unholy, death
4455
4456 for (uint32 i = 0; i < NUM_RUNE_TYPES; ++i)
4457 {
4458 runeCost[i] = src->RuneCost[i];
4459 if (Player* modOwner = m_caster->GetSpellModOwner())
4460 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_COST, runeCost[i], this);
4461 }
4462
4463 runeCost[RUNE_DEATH] += MAX_RUNES;
4464
4465 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_RUNES; ++i)
4466 {
4467 RuneType rune = player->GetCurrentRune(i);
4468 if ((player->GetRuneCooldown(i) == 0) && (runeCost[rune] > 0))
4469 runeCost[rune]--;
4470 }
4471
4472 for (uint32 i = 0; i < RUNE_DEATH; ++i)
4473 if (runeCost[i] > 0)
4474 runeCost[RUNE_DEATH] += runeCost[i];
4475
4476 if (runeCost[RUNE_DEATH] > MAX_RUNES)
4477 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_POWER; // not sure if result code is correct
4478
4479 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
4480}
4481
4482void Spell::TakeRunePower(bool didHit)
4483{
4484 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER || m_caster->getClass() != CLASS_DEATH_KNIGHT)
4485 return;
4486
4487 SpellRuneCostEntry const* runeCostData = sSpellRuneCostStore.LookupEntry(m_spellInfo->RuneCostID);
4488 if (!runeCostData || (runeCostData->NoRuneCost() && runeCostData->NoRunicPowerGain()))
4489 return;
4490
4491 Player* player = m_caster->ToPlayer();
4492 m_runesState = player->GetRunesState(); // store previous state
4493
4494 int32 runeCost[NUM_RUNE_TYPES]; // blood, frost, unholy, death
4495
4496 for (uint32 i = 0; i < NUM_RUNE_TYPES; ++i)
4497 {
4498 runeCost[i] = runeCostData->RuneCost[i];
4499 if (Player* modOwner = m_caster->GetSpellModOwner())
4500 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_COST, runeCost[i], this);
4501 }
4502
4503 // Let's say we use a skill that requires a Frost rune. This is the order:
4504 // - Frost rune
4505 // - Death rune, originally a Frost rune
4506 // - Death rune, any kind
4507 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_RUNES; ++i)
4508 {
4509 RuneType rune = player->GetCurrentRune(i);
4510 if (!player->GetRuneCooldown(i) && runeCost[rune] > 0)
4511 {
4512 player->SetRuneCooldown(i, didHit ? player->GetRuneBaseCooldown(i) : uint32(RUNE_MISS_COOLDOWN), true);
4513 player->SetLastUsedRune(rune);
4514 runeCost[rune]--;
4515 }
4516 }
4517
4518 // Find a Death rune where the base rune matches the one we need
4519 runeCost[RUNE_DEATH] += runeCost[RUNE_BLOOD] + runeCost[RUNE_UNHOLY] + runeCost[RUNE_FROST];
4520 if (runeCost[RUNE_DEATH] > 0)
4521 {
4522 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_RUNES; ++i)
4523 {
4524 RuneType rune = player->GetCurrentRune(i);
4525 RuneType baseRune = player->GetBaseRune(i);
4526 if (!player->GetRuneCooldown(i) && rune == RUNE_DEATH && runeCost[baseRune] > 0)
4527 {
4528 player->SetRuneCooldown(i, didHit ? player->GetRuneBaseCooldown(i) : uint32(RUNE_MISS_COOLDOWN), true);
4529 player->SetLastUsedRune(rune);
4530 runeCost[baseRune]--;
4531 runeCost[rune]--;
4532
4533 // keep Death Rune type if missed
4534 if (didHit)
4535 player->RestoreBaseRune(i);
4536
4537 if (runeCost[RUNE_DEATH] == 0)
4538 break;
4539 }
4540 }
4541 }
4542
4543 // Grab any Death rune
4544 if (runeCost[RUNE_DEATH] > 0)
4545 {
4546 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_RUNES; ++i)
4547 {
4548 RuneType rune = player->GetCurrentRune(i);
4549 if (!player->GetRuneCooldown(i) && rune == RUNE_DEATH)
4550 {
4551 player->SetRuneCooldown(i, didHit ? player->GetRuneBaseCooldown(i) : uint32(RUNE_MISS_COOLDOWN), true);
4552 player->SetLastUsedRune(rune);
4553 runeCost[rune]--;
4554
4555 // keep Death Rune type if missed
4556 if (didHit)
4557 player->RestoreBaseRune(i);
4558
4559 if (runeCost[RUNE_DEATH] == 0)
4560 break;
4561 }
4562 }
4563 }
4564
4565 // you can gain some runic power when use runes
4566 if (didHit)
4567 if (int32 rp = int32(runeCostData->RunicPower * sWorld->getRate(RATE_POWER_RUNICPOWER_INCOME)))
4568 player->ModifyPower(POWER_RUNIC_POWER, int32(rp));
4569}
4570
4571void Spell::TakeReagents()
4572{
4573 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
4574 return;
4575
4576 ItemTemplate const* castItemTemplate = m_CastItem ? m_CastItem->GetTemplate() : NULL;
4577
4578 // do not take reagents for these item casts
4579 if (castItemTemplate && castItemTemplate->GetFlags() & ITEM_FLAG_TRIGGERED_CAST)
4580 return;
4581
4582 Player* p_caster = m_caster->ToPlayer();
4583 if (p_caster->CanNoReagentCast(m_spellInfo))
4584 return;
4585
4586 for (uint32 x = 0; x < MAX_SPELL_REAGENTS; ++x)
4587 {
4588 if (m_spellInfo->Reagent[x] <= 0)
4589 continue;
4590
4591 uint32 itemid = m_spellInfo->Reagent[x];
4592 uint32 itemcount = m_spellInfo->ReagentCount[x];
4593
