4594 // if CastItem is also spell reagent
4595 if (castItemTemplate && castItemTemplate->GetId() == itemid)
4596 {
4597 for (uint8 s = 0; s < castItemTemplate->Effects.size() && s < 5; ++s)
4598 {
4599 // CastItem will be used up and does not count as reagent
4600 int32 charges = m_CastItem->GetSpellCharges(s);
4601 if (castItemTemplate->Effects[s]->Charges < 0 && abs(charges) < 2)
4602 {
4603 ++itemcount;
4604 break;
4605 }
4606 }
4607
4608 m_CastItem = NULL;
4609 m_castItemGUID.Clear();
4610 m_castItemEntry = 0;
4611 }
4612
4613 // if GetItemTarget is also spell reagent
4614 if (m_targets.GetItemTargetEntry() == itemid)
4615 m_targets.SetItemTarget(NULL);
4616
4617 p_caster->DestroyItemCount(itemid, itemcount, true);
4618 }
4619}
4620
4621void Spell::HandleThreatSpells()
4622{
4623 if (m_UniqueTargetInfo.empty())
4624 return;
4625
4626 if ((m_spellInfo->AttributesEx & SPELL_ATTR1_NO_THREAT) ||
4627 (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_NO_INITIAL_AGGRO)))
4628 return;
4629
4630 float threat = 0.0f;
4631 if (SpellThreatEntry const* threatEntry = sSpellMgr->GetSpellThreatEntry(m_spellInfo->Id))
4632 {
4633 if (threatEntry->apPctMod != 0.0f)
4634 threat += threatEntry->apPctMod * m_caster->GetTotalAttackPowerValue(BASE_ATTACK);
4635
4636 threat += threatEntry->flatMod;
4637 }
4638 else if ((m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CU_NO_INITIAL_THREAT)) == 0)
4639 threat += m_spellInfo->SpellLevel;
4640
4641 // past this point only multiplicative effects occur
4642 if (threat == 0.0f)
4643 return;
4644
4645 // since 2.0.1 threat from positive effects also is distributed among all targets, so the overall caused threat is at most the defined bonus
4646 threat /= m_UniqueTargetInfo.size();
4647
4648 for (std::vector<TargetInfo>::iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
4649 {
4650 float threatToAdd = threat;
4651 if (ihit->missCondition != SPELL_MISS_NONE)
4652 threatToAdd = 0.0f;
4653
4654 Unit* target = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, ihit->targetGUID);
4655 if (!target)
4656 continue;
4657
4658 // positive spells distribute threat among all units that are in combat with target, like healing
4659 if (m_spellInfo->_IsPositiveSpell())
4660 target->getHostileRefManager().threatAssist(m_caster, threatToAdd, m_spellInfo);
4661 // for negative spells threat gets distributed among affected targets
4662 else
4663 {
4664 if (!target->CanHaveThreatList())
4665 continue;
4666
4667 target->AddThreat(m_caster, threatToAdd, m_spellInfo->GetSchoolMask(), m_spellInfo);
4668 }
4669 }
4670 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell %u, added an additional %f threat for %s %u target(s)", m_spellInfo->Id, threat, m_spellInfo->_IsPositiveSpell() ? "assisting" : "harming", uint32(m_UniqueTargetInfo.size()));
4671}
4672
4673void Spell::HandleEffects(Unit* pUnitTarget, Item* pItemTarget, GameObject* pGOTarget, uint32 i, SpellEffectHandleMode mode)
4674{
4675 effectHandleMode = mode;
4676 unitTarget = pUnitTarget;
4677 itemTarget = pItemTarget;
4678 gameObjTarget = pGOTarget;
4679 destTarget = &m_destTargets[i]._position;
4680
4681 effectInfo = GetEffect(i);
4682 if (!effectInfo)
4683 {
4684 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Spell: %u HandleEffects at EffectIndex: %u missing effect", m_spellInfo->Id, i);
4685 return;
4686 }
4687 uint32 eff = effectInfo->Effect;
4688
4689 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell: %u Effect: %u", m_spellInfo->Id, eff);
4690
4691 damage = CalculateDamage(i, unitTarget, &variance);
4692
4693 bool preventDefault = CallScriptEffectHandlers((SpellEffIndex)i, mode);
4694
4695 if (!preventDefault && eff < TOTAL_SPELL_EFFECTS)
4696 {
4697 (this->*SpellEffects[eff])((SpellEffIndex)i);
4698 }
4699}
4700
4701SpellCastResult Spell::CheckCast(bool strict)
4702{
4703 // check death state
4704 if (!m_caster->IsAlive() && !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_PASSIVE) && !((m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CASTABLE_WHILE_DEAD)) || (IsTriggered() && !m_triggeredByAuraSpell)))
4705 return SPELL_FAILED_CASTER_DEAD;
4706
4707 // check cooldowns to prevent cheating
4708 if (!m_spellInfo->IsPassive())
4709 {
4710 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
4711 {
4712 //can cast triggered (by aura only?) spells while have this flag
4713 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CASTER_AURASTATE) && m_caster->ToPlayer()->HasFlag(PLAYER_FLAGS, PLAYER_ALLOW_ONLY_ABILITY))
4714 return SPELL_FAILED_SPELL_IN_PROGRESS;
4715
4716 // check if we are using a potion in combat for the 2nd+ time. Cooldown is added only after caster gets out of combat
4717 if (m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetLastPotionId() && m_CastItem && (m_CastItem->IsPotion() || m_spellInfo->IsCooldownStartedOnEvent()))
4718 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_READY;
4719 }
4720
4721 if (!m_caster->GetSpellHistory()->IsReady(m_spellInfo, m_castItemEntry, IsIgnoringCooldowns()))
4722 {
4723 if (m_triggeredByAuraSpell)
4724 return SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
4725 else
4726 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_READY;
4727 }
4728 }
4729
4730 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR7_IS_CHEAT_SPELL) && !m_caster->HasFlag(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS_2, UNIT_FLAG2_ALLOW_CHEAT_SPELLS))
4731 {
4732 m_customError = SPELL_CUSTOM_ERROR_GM_ONLY;
4733 return SPELL_FAILED_CUSTOM_ERROR;
4734 }
4735
4736 // Check global cooldown
4737 if (strict && !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_GCD) && HasGlobalCooldown())
4738 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_READY;
4739
4740 // only triggered spells can be processed an ended battleground
4741 if (!IsTriggered() && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
4742 if (Battleground* bg = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetBattleground())
4743 if (bg->GetStatus() == STATUS_WAIT_LEAVE)
4744 return SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
4745
4746 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && VMAP::VMapFactory::createOrGetVMapManager()->isLineOfSightCalcEnabled())
4747 {
4748 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_OUTDOORS_ONLY) &&
4749 !m_caster->GetMap()->IsOutdoors(m_caster->GetPositionX(), m_caster->GetPositionY(), m_caster->GetPositionZ()))
4750 return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_OUTDOORS;
4751
4752 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_INDOORS_ONLY) &&
4753 m_caster->GetMap()->IsOutdoors(m_caster->GetPositionX(), m_caster->GetPositionY(), m_caster->GetPositionZ()))
4754 return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_INDOORS;
4755 }
4756
4757 // only check at first call, Stealth auras are already removed at second call
4758 // for now, ignore triggered spells
4759 if (strict && !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_SHAPESHIFT))
4760 {
4761 bool checkForm = true;
4762 // Ignore form req aura
4763 Unit::AuraEffectList const& ignore = m_caster->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_IGNORE_SHAPESHIFT);
4764 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator i = ignore.begin(); i != ignore.end(); ++i)
4765 {
4766 if (!(*i)->IsAffectingSpell(m_spellInfo))
4767 continue;
4768 checkForm = false;
4769 break;
4770 }
4771 if (checkForm)
4772 {
4773 // Cannot be used in this stance/form
4774 SpellCastResult shapeError = m_spellInfo->CheckShapeshift(m_caster->GetShapeshiftForm());
4775 if (shapeError != SPELL_CAST_OK)
4776 return shapeError;
4777
4778 if ((m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_ONLY_STEALTHED)) && !(m_caster->HasStealthAura()))
4779 return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_STEALTHED;
4780 }
4781 }
4782
4783 Unit::AuraEffectList const& blockSpells = m_caster->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_BLOCK_SPELL_FAMILY);
4784 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator blockItr = blockSpells.begin(); blockItr != blockSpells.end(); ++blockItr)
4785 if (uint32((*blockItr)->GetMiscValue()) == m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName)
4786 return SPELL_FAILED_SPELL_UNAVAILABLE;
4787
4788 bool reqCombat = true;
4789 Unit::AuraEffectList const& stateAuras = m_caster->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_ABILITY_IGNORE_AURASTATE);
4790 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator j = stateAuras.begin(); j != stateAuras.end(); ++j)
4791 {
4792 if ((*j)->IsAffectingSpell(m_spellInfo))
4793 {
4794 m_needComboPoints = false;
4795 if ((*j)->GetMiscValue() == 1)
4796 {
4797 reqCombat=false;
4798 break;
4799 }
4800 }
4801 }
4802
4803 // caster state requirements
4804 // not for triggered spells (needed by execute)
4805 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CASTER_AURASTATE))
4806 {
4807 if (m_spellInfo->CasterAuraState && !m_caster->HasAuraState(AuraStateType(m_spellInfo->CasterAuraState), m_spellInfo, m_caster))
4808 return SPELL_FAILED_CASTER_AURASTATE;
4809 if (m_spellInfo->ExcludeCasterAuraState && m_caster->HasAuraState(AuraStateType(m_spellInfo->ExcludeCasterAuraState), m_spellInfo, m_caster))
4810 return SPELL_FAILED_CASTER_AURASTATE;
4811
4812 // Note: spell 62473 requres casterAuraSpell = triggering spell
4813 if (m_spellInfo->CasterAuraSpell && !m_caster->HasAura(m_spellInfo->CasterAuraSpell))
4814 return SPELL_FAILED_CASTER_AURASTATE;
4815 if (m_spellInfo->ExcludeCasterAuraSpell && m_caster->HasAura(m_spellInfo->ExcludeCasterAuraSpell))
4816 return SPELL_FAILED_CASTER_AURASTATE;
4817
4818 if (reqCombat && m_caster->IsInCombat() && !m_spellInfo->CanBeUsedInCombat())
4819 return SPELL_FAILED_AFFECTING_COMBAT;
4820 }
4821
4822 // cancel autorepeat spells if cast start when moving
4823 // (not wand currently autorepeat cast delayed to moving stop anyway in spell update code)
4824 // Do not cancel spells which are affected by a SPELL_AURA_CAST_WHILE_WALKING effect
4825 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && m_caster->ToPlayer()->isMoving() && !m_caster->HasAuraTypeWithAffectMask(SPELL_AURA_CAST_WHILE_WALKING, m_spellInfo))
4826 {
4827 // skip stuck spell to allow use it in falling case and apply spell limitations at movement
4828 SpellEffectInfo const* effect = GetEffect(EFFECT_0);
4829 if ((!m_caster->HasUnitMovementFlag(MOVEMENTFLAG_FALLING_FAR) || (effect && effect->Effect != SPELL_EFFECT_STUCK)) &&
4830 (IsAutoRepeat() || (m_spellInfo->AuraInterruptFlags & AURA_INTERRUPT_FLAG_NOT_SEATED) != 0))
4831 return SPELL_FAILED_MOVING;
4832 }
4833
4834 // Check vehicle flags
4835 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CASTER_MOUNTED_OR_ON_VEHICLE))
4836 {
4837 SpellCastResult vehicleCheck = m_spellInfo->CheckVehicle(m_caster);
4838 if (vehicleCheck != SPELL_CAST_OK)
4839 return vehicleCheck;
4840 }
4841
4842 // check spell cast conditions from database
4843 {
4844 ConditionSourceInfo condInfo = ConditionSourceInfo(m_caster, m_targets.GetObjectTarget());
4845 if (!sConditionMgr->IsObjectMeetingNotGroupedConditions(CONDITION_SOURCE_TYPE_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id, condInfo))
4846 {
4847 // mLastFailedCondition can be NULL if there was an error processing the condition in Condition::Meets (i.e. wrong data for ConditionTarget or others)
4848 if (condInfo.mLastFailedCondition && condInfo.mLastFailedCondition->ErrorType)
4849 {
4850 if (condInfo.mLastFailedCondition->ErrorType == SPELL_FAILED_CUSTOM_ERROR)
4851 m_customError = SpellCustomErrors(condInfo.mLastFailedCondition->ErrorTextId);
4852 return SpellCastResult(condInfo.mLastFailedCondition->ErrorType);
4853 }
4854 if (!condInfo.mLastFailedCondition || !condInfo.mLastFailedCondition->ConditionTarget)
4855 return SPELL_FAILED_CASTER_AURASTATE;
4856 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
4857 }
4858 }
4859
4860 // Don't check explicit target for passive spells (workaround) (check should be skipped only for learn case)
4861 // those spells may have incorrect target entries or not filled at all (for example 15332)
4862 // such spells when learned are not targeting anyone using targeting system, they should apply directly to caster instead
4863 // also, such casts shouldn't be sent to client
4864 if (!((m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_PASSIVE)) && (!m_targets.GetUnitTarget() || m_targets.GetUnitTarget() == m_caster)))
4865 {
4866 // Check explicit target for m_originalCaster - todo: get rid of such workarounds
4867 SpellCastResult castResult = m_spellInfo->CheckExplicitTarget(m_originalCaster ? m_originalCaster : m_caster, m_targets.GetObjectTarget(), m_targets.GetItemTarget());
4868 if (castResult != SPELL_CAST_OK)
4869 return castResult;
4870 }
4871
4872 if (Unit* target = m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
4873 {
4874 SpellCastResult castResult = m_spellInfo->CheckTarget(m_caster, target, false);
4875 if (castResult != SPELL_CAST_OK)
4876 return castResult;
4877
4878 if (target != m_caster)
4879 {
4880 // Must be behind the target
4881 if ((m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CU_REQ_CASTER_BEHIND_TARGET)) && target->HasInArc(static_cast<float>(M_PI), m_caster))
4882 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_BEHIND;
4883
4884 // Target must be facing you
4885 if ((m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CU_REQ_TARGET_FACING_CASTER)) && !target->HasInArc(static_cast<float>(M_PI), m_caster))
4886 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_INFRONT;
4887
4888 if (m_caster->GetEntry() != WORLD_TRIGGER) // Ignore LOS for gameobjects casts (wrongly cast by a trigger)
4889 {
4890 WorldObject* losTarget = m_caster;
4891 if (IsTriggered() && m_triggeredByAuraSpell)
4892 if (DynamicObject* dynObj = m_caster->GetDynObject(m_triggeredByAuraSpell->Id))
4893 losTarget = dynObj;
4894
4895 if (!m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_CAN_TARGET_NOT_IN_LOS) && !DisableMgr::IsDisabledFor(DISABLE_TYPE_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id, NULL, SPELL_DISABLE_LOS) && !target->IsWithinLOSInMap(losTarget))
4896 return SPELL_FAILED_LINE_OF_SIGHT;
4897 }
4898 }
4899 }
4900
4901 // Check for line of sight for spells with dest
4902 if (m_targets.HasDst())
4903 {
4904 float x, y, z;
4905 m_targets.GetDstPos()->GetPosition(x, y, z);
4906
4907 if (!m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_CAN_TARGET_NOT_IN_LOS) && !DisableMgr::IsDisabledFor(DISABLE_TYPE_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id, NULL, SPELL_DISABLE_LOS) && !m_caster->IsWithinLOS(x, y, z))
4908 return SPELL_FAILED_LINE_OF_SIGHT;
4909 }
4910
4911 // check pet presence
4912 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
4913 {
4914 if (effect && effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_PET)
4915 {
4916 if (!m_caster->GetGuardianPet())
4917 {
4918 if (m_triggeredByAuraSpell) // not report pet not existence for triggered spells
4919 return SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
4920 else
4921 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_PET;
4922 }
4923 break;
4924 }
4925 }
4926
4927 // Spell cast only in battleground
4928 if ((m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_BATTLEGROUND)) && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
4929 if (!m_caster->ToPlayer()->InBattleground())
4930 return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_BATTLEGROUNDS;
4931
4932 // do not allow spells to be cast in arenas or rated battlegrounds
4933 if (Player* player = m_caster->ToPlayer())
4934 if (player->InArena()/* || player->InRatedBattleGround() NYI*/)
4935 {
4936 SpellCastResult castResult = CheckArenaAndRatedBattlegroundCastRules();
4937 if (castResult != SPELL_CAST_OK)
4938 return castResult;
4939 }
4940
4941 // zone check
4942 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT || !m_caster->ToPlayer()->IsGameMaster())
4943 {
4944 uint32 zone, area;
4945 m_caster->GetZoneAndAreaId(zone, area);
4946
4947 SpellCastResult locRes = m_spellInfo->CheckLocation(m_caster->GetMapId(), zone, area, m_caster->ToPlayer());
4948 if (locRes != SPELL_CAST_OK)
4949 return locRes;
4950 }
4951
4952 // not let players cast spells at mount (and let do it to creatures)
4953 if (m_caster->IsMounted() && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CASTER_MOUNTED_OR_ON_VEHICLE) &&
4954 !m_spellInfo->IsPassive() && !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CASTABLE_WHILE_MOUNTED))
4955 {
4956 if (m_caster->IsInFlight())
4957 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_ON_TAXI;
4958 else
4959 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_MOUNTED;
4960 }
4961
4962 // check spell focus object
4963 if (m_spellInfo->RequiresSpellFocus)
4964 {
4965 focusObject = SearchSpellFocus();
4966 if (!focusObject)
4967 return SPELL_FAILED_REQUIRES_SPELL_FOCUS;
4968 }
4969
4970 SpellCastResult castResult = SPELL_CAST_OK;
4971
4972 // always (except passive spells) check items (only player related checks)
4973 if (!m_spellInfo->IsPassive())
4974 {
4975 castResult = CheckItems();
4976 if (castResult != SPELL_CAST_OK)
4977 return castResult;
4978 }
4979
4980 // Triggered spells also have range check
4981 /// @todo determine if there is some flag to enable/disable the check
4982 castResult = CheckRange(strict);
4983 if (castResult != SPELL_CAST_OK)
4984 return castResult;
4985
4986 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_POWER_AND_REAGENT_COST))
4987 {
4988 castResult = CheckPower();
4989 if (castResult != SPELL_CAST_OK)
4990 return castResult;
4991 }
4992
4993 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CASTER_AURAS))
4994 {
4995 castResult = CheckCasterAuras();
4996 if (castResult != SPELL_CAST_OK)
4997 return castResult;
4998 }
4999
5000 // script hook
5001 castResult = CallScriptCheckCastHandlers();
5002 if (castResult != SPELL_CAST_OK)
5003 return castResult;
5004
5005 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
5006 {
5007 if (!effect)
5008 continue;
5009 // for effects of spells that have only one target
5010 switch (effect->Effect)
5011 {
5012 case SPELL_EFFECT_DUMMY:
5013 {
5014 if (m_spellInfo->Id == 19938) // Awaken Peon
5015 {
5016 Unit* unit = m_targets.GetUnitTarget();
5017 if (!unit || !unit->HasAura(17743))
5018 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5019 }
5020 else if (m_spellInfo->Id == 31789) // Righteous Defense
5021 {
5022 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5023 return SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
5024
5025 Unit* target = m_targets.GetUnitTarget();
5026 if (!target || !target->IsFriendlyTo(m_caster) || target->getAttackers().empty())
5027 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5028
5029 }
5030 break;
5031 }
5032 case SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_SPELL:
5033 {
5034 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5035 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5036
5037 if (effect->TargetA.GetTarget() != TARGET_UNIT_PET)
5038 break;
5039
5040 Pet* pet = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetPet();
5041
5042 if (!pet)
5043 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_PET;
5044
5045 SpellInfo const* learn_spellproto = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(effect->TriggerSpell);
5046
5047 if (!learn_spellproto)
5048 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_KNOWN;
5049
5050 if (m_spellInfo->SpellLevel > pet->getLevel())
5051 return SPELL_FAILED_LOWLEVEL;
5052
5053 break;
5054 }
5055 case SPELL_EFFECT_UNLOCK_GUILD_VAULT_TAB:
5056 {
5057 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5058 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5059 if (Guild* guild = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetGuild())
5060 if (guild->GetLeaderGUID() != m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetGUID())
5061 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_DO_THAT_RIGHT_NOW;
5062 break;
5063 }
5064 case SPELL_EFFECT_LEARN_PET_SPELL:
5065 {
5066 // check target only for unit target case
5067 if (Unit* unit = m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
5068 {
5069 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5070 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5071
5072 Pet* pet = unit->ToPet();
5073 if (!pet || pet->GetOwner() != m_caster)
5074 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5075
5076 SpellInfo const* learn_spellproto = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(effect->TriggerSpell);
5077
5078 if (!learn_spellproto)
5079 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_KNOWN;
5080
5081 if (m_spellInfo->SpellLevel > pet->getLevel())
5082 return SPELL_FAILED_LOWLEVEL;
5083 }
5084 break;
5085 }
5086 case SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_GLYPH:
5087 {
5088 uint32 glyphId = effect->MiscValue;
5089 if (GlyphPropertiesEntry const* gp = sGlyphPropertiesStore.LookupEntry(glyphId))
5090 if (m_caster->HasAura(gp->SpellID))
5091 return SPELL_FAILED_UNIQUE_GLYPH;
5092 break;
5093 }
5094 case SPELL_EFFECT_FEED_PET:
5095 {
5096 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5097 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5098
5099 Item* foodItem = m_targets.GetItemTarget();
5100 if (!foodItem)
5101 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5102
5103 Pet* pet = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetPet();
5104
5105 if (!pet)
5106 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_PET;
5107
5108 if (!pet->HaveInDiet(foodItem->GetTemplate()))
5109 return SPELL_FAILED_WRONG_PET_FOOD;
5110
5111 if (!pet->GetCurrentFoodBenefitLevel(foodItem->GetTemplate()->GetBaseItemLevel()))
5112 return SPELL_FAILED_FOOD_LOWLEVEL;
5113
5114 if (m_caster->IsInCombat() || pet->IsInCombat())
5115 return SPELL_FAILED_AFFECTING_COMBAT;
5116
5117 break;
5118 }
5119 case SPELL_EFFECT_POWER_BURN:
5120 case SPELL_EFFECT_POWER_DRAIN:
5121 {
5122 // Can be area effect, Check only for players and not check if target - caster (spell can have multiply drain/burn effects)
5123 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
5124 if (Unit* target = m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
5125 if (target != m_caster && target->getPowerType() != Powers(effect->MiscValue))
5126 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5127 break;
5128 }
5129 case SPELL_EFFECT_CHARGE:
5130 {
5131 if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_WARRIOR)
5132 {
5133 // Warbringer - can't be handled in proc system - should be done before checkcast root check and charge effect process
5134 if (strict && m_caster->IsScriptOverriden(m_spellInfo, 6953))
5135 m_caster->RemoveMovementImpairingAuras();
5136 }
5137
5138 if (m_caster->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_ROOT))
5139 return SPELL_FAILED_ROOTED;
5140
5141 if (GetSpellInfo()->NeedsExplicitUnitTarget())
5142 {
5143 Unit* target = m_targets.GetUnitTarget();
5144 if (!target)
5145 return SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
5146
5147 float objSize = target->GetObjectSize();
5148 float range = m_spellInfo->GetMaxRange(true, m_caster, this) * 1.5f + objSize; // can't be overly strict
5149
5150 m_preGeneratedPath.SetPathLengthLimit(range);
5151 // first try with raycast, if it fails fall back to normal path
5152 float targetObjectSize = std::min(target->GetObjectSize(), 4.0f);
5153 bool result = m_preGeneratedPath.CalculatePath(target->GetPositionX(), target->GetPositionY(), target->GetPositionZ() + targetObjectSize, false, true);
5154 if (m_preGeneratedPath.GetPathType() & PATHFIND_SHORT)
5155 return SPELL_FAILED_OUT_OF_RANGE;
5156 else if (!result || m_preGeneratedPath.GetPathType() & (PATHFIND_NOPATH | PATHFIND_INCOMPLETE))
5157 {
5158 result = m_preGeneratedPath.CalculatePath(target->GetPositionX(), target->GetPositionY(), target->GetPositionZ() + targetObjectSize, false, false);
5159 if (m_preGeneratedPath.GetPathType() & PATHFIND_SHORT)
5160 return SPELL_FAILED_OUT_OF_RANGE;
5161 else if (!result || m_preGeneratedPath.GetPathType() & (PATHFIND_NOPATH | PATHFIND_INCOMPLETE))
5162 return SPELL_FAILED_NOPATH;
5163 }
5164
5165 m_preGeneratedPath.ReducePathLenghtByDist(objSize); // move back
5166 }
5167 break;
5168 }
5169 case SPELL_EFFECT_SKINNING:
5170 {
5171 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER || !m_targets.GetUnitTarget() || m_targets.GetUnitTarget()->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_UNIT)
5172 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5173
5174 if (!(m_targets.GetUnitTarget()->GetUInt32Value(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS) & UNIT_FLAG_SKINNABLE))
5175 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_UNSKINNABLE;
5176
5177 Creature* creature = m_targets.GetUnitTarget()->ToCreature();
5178 if (!creature->IsCritter() && !creature->loot.isLooted())
5179 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NOT_LOOTED;
5180
5181 uint32 skill = creature->GetCreatureTemplate()->GetRequiredLootSkill();
5182
5183 int32 skillValue = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetSkillValue(skill);
5184 int32 TargetLevel = m_targets.GetUnitTarget()->getLevel();
5185 int32 ReqValue = (skillValue < 100 ? (TargetLevel-10) * 10 : TargetLevel * 5);
5186 if (ReqValue > skillValue)
5187 return SPELL_FAILED_LOW_CASTLEVEL;
5188
5189 // chance for fail at orange skinning attempt
5190 if ((m_selfContainer && (*m_selfContainer) == this) &&
5191 skillValue < sWorld->GetConfigMaxSkillValue() &&
5192 (ReqValue < 0 ? 0 : ReqValue) > irand(skillValue - 25, skillValue + 37))
5193 return SPELL_FAILED_TRY_AGAIN;
5194
5195 break;
5196 }
5197 case SPELL_EFFECT_OPEN_LOCK:
5198 {
5199 if (effect->TargetA.GetTarget() != TARGET_GAMEOBJECT_TARGET &&
5200 effect->TargetA.GetTarget() != TARGET_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM_TARGET)
5201 break;
5202
5203 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER // only players can open locks, gather etc.
5204 // we need a go target in case of TARGET_GAMEOBJECT_TARGET
5205 || (effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_GAMEOBJECT_TARGET && !m_targets.GetGOTarget()))
5206 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5207
5208 Item* pTempItem = NULL;
5209 if (m_targets.GetTargetMask() & TARGET_FLAG_TRADE_ITEM)
5210 {
5211 if (TradeData* pTrade = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetTradeData())
5212 pTempItem = pTrade->GetTraderData()->GetItem(TradeSlots(m_targets.GetItemTargetGUID().GetRawValue().at(0))); // at this point item target guid contains the trade slot
5213 }
5214 else if (m_targets.GetTargetMask() & TARGET_FLAG_ITEM)
5215 pTempItem = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetItemByGuid(m_targets.GetItemTargetGUID());
5216
5217 // we need a go target, or an openable item target in case of TARGET_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM_TARGET
5218 if (effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM_TARGET &&
5219 !m_targets.GetGOTarget() &&
5220 (!pTempItem || !pTempItem->GetTemplate()->GetLockID() || !pTempItem->IsLocked()))
5221 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5222
5223 if (m_spellInfo->Id != 1842 || (m_targets.GetGOTarget() &&
5224 m_targets.GetGOTarget()->GetGOInfo()->type != GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_TRAP))
5225 if (m_caster->ToPlayer()->InBattleground() && // In Battleground players can use only flags and banners
5226 !m_caster->ToPlayer()->CanUseBattlegroundObject(m_targets.GetGOTarget()))
5227 return SPELL_FAILED_TRY_AGAIN;
5228
5229 // get the lock entry
5230 uint32 lockId = 0;
5231 if (GameObject* go = m_targets.GetGOTarget())
5232 {
5233 lockId = go->GetGOInfo()->GetLockId();
5234 if (!lockId)
5235 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5236 }
5237 else if (Item* itm = m_targets.GetItemTarget())
5238 lockId = itm->GetTemplate()->GetLockID();
5239
5240 SkillType skillId = SKILL_NONE;
5241 int32 reqSkillValue = 0;
5242 int32 skillValue = 0;
5243
5244 // check lock compatibility
5245 SpellCastResult res = CanOpenLock(effect->EffectIndex, lockId, skillId, reqSkillValue, skillValue);
5246 if (res != SPELL_CAST_OK)
5247 return res;
5248
5249 // chance for fail at orange mining/herb/LockPicking gathering attempt
5250 // second check prevent fail at rechecks
5251 if (skillId != SKILL_NONE && (!m_selfContainer || ((*m_selfContainer) != this)))
5252 {
5253 bool canFailAtMax = skillId != SKILL_HERBALISM && skillId != SKILL_MINING;
5254
5255 // chance for failure in orange gather / lockpick (gathering skill can't fail at maxskill)
5256 if ((canFailAtMax || skillValue < sWorld->GetConfigMaxSkillValue()) && reqSkillValue > irand(skillValue - 25, skillValue + 37))
5257 return SPELL_FAILED_TRY_AGAIN;
5258 }
5259 break;
5260 }
5261 case SPELL_EFFECT_RESURRECT_PET:
5262 {
5263 Creature* pet = m_caster->GetGuardianPet();
5264
5265 if (pet && pet->IsAlive())
5266 return SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_HAVE_SUMMON;
5267
5268 break;
5269 }
5270 // This is generic summon effect
5271 case SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON:
5272 {
5273 SummonPropertiesEntry const* SummonProperties = sSummonPropertiesStore.LookupEntry(effect->MiscValueB);
5274 if (!SummonProperties)
5275 break;
5276 switch (SummonProperties->Category)
5277 {
5278 case SUMMON_CATEGORY_PET:
5279 if (!m_caster->GetPetGUID().IsEmpty())
5280 return SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_HAVE_SUMMON;
5281 // intentional missing break, check both GetPetGUID() and GetCharmGUID for SUMMON_CATEGORY_PET
5282 case SUMMON_CATEGORY_PUPPET:
5283 if (!m_caster->GetCharmGUID().IsEmpty())
5284 return SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_HAVE_CHARM;
5285 break;
5286 }
5287 break;
5288 }
5289 case SPELL_EFFECT_CREATE_TAMED_PET:
5290 {
5291 if (m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
5292 {
5293 if (m_targets.GetUnitTarget()->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5294 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5295 if (!m_targets.GetUnitTarget()->GetPetGUID().IsEmpty())
5296 return SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_HAVE_SUMMON;
5297 }
5298 break;
5299 }
5300 case SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_PET:
5301 {
5302 if (!m_caster->GetPetGUID().IsEmpty()) //let warlock do a replacement summon
5303 {
5304 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && m_caster->getClass() == CLASS_WARLOCK)
5305 {
5306 if (strict) //starting cast, trigger pet stun (cast by pet so it doesn't attack player)
5307 if (Pet* pet = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetPet())
5308 pet->CastSpell(pet, 32752, true, NULL, NULL, pet->GetGUID());
5309 }
5310 else
5311 return SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_HAVE_SUMMON;
5312 }
5313
5314 if (!m_caster->GetCharmGUID().IsEmpty())
5315 return SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_HAVE_CHARM;
5316 break;
5317 }
5318 case SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_PLAYER:
5319 {
5320 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5321 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5322 if (!m_caster->GetTarget())
5323 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5324
5325 Player* target = ObjectAccessor::FindPlayer(m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetTarget());
5326 if (!target || m_caster->ToPlayer() == target || (!target->IsInSameRaidWith(m_caster->ToPlayer()) && m_spellInfo->Id != 48955)) // refer-a-friend spell
5327 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5328
5329 // check if our map is dungeon
5330 MapEntry const* map = sMapStore.LookupEntry(m_caster->GetMapId());
5331 if (map->IsDungeon())
5332 {
5333 uint32 mapId = m_caster->GetMap()->GetId();
5334 Difficulty difficulty = m_caster->GetMap()->GetDifficultyID();
5335 if (map->IsRaid())
5336 if (InstancePlayerBind* targetBind = target->GetBoundInstance(mapId, difficulty))
5337 if (InstancePlayerBind* casterBind = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetBoundInstance(mapId, difficulty))
5338 if (targetBind->perm && targetBind->save != casterBind->save)
5339 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_LOCKED_TO_RAID_INSTANCE;
5340
5341 InstanceTemplate const* instance = sObjectMgr->GetInstanceTemplate(mapId);
5342 if (!instance)
5343 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_NOT_IN_INSTANCE;
5344 if (!target->Satisfy(sObjectMgr->GetAccessRequirement(mapId, difficulty), mapId))
5345 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5346 }
5347 break;
5348 }
5349 // RETURN HERE
5350 case SPELL_EFFECT_SUMMON_RAF_FRIEND:
5351 {
5352 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5353 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5354
5355 Player* playerCaster = m_caster->ToPlayer();
5356 //
5357 if (!(playerCaster->GetTarget()))
5358 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5359
5360 Player* target = playerCaster->GetSelectedPlayer();
5361
5362 if (!target ||
5363 !(target->GetSession()->GetRecruiterId() == playerCaster->GetSession()->GetAccountId() || target->GetSession()->GetAccountId() == playerCaster->GetSession()->GetRecruiterId()))
5364 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5365
5366 break;
5367 }
5368 case SPELL_EFFECT_LEAP:
5369 case SPELL_EFFECT_TELEPORT_UNITS_FACE_CASTER:
5370 {
5371 //Do not allow to cast it before BG starts.
5372 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
5373 if (Battleground const* bg = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetBattleground())
5374 if (bg->GetStatus() != STATUS_IN_PROGRESS)
5375 return SPELL_FAILED_TRY_AGAIN;
5376 break;
5377 }
5378 case SPELL_EFFECT_STEAL_BENEFICIAL_BUFF:
5379 {
5380 if (m_targets.GetUnitTarget() == m_caster)
5381 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5382 break;
5383 }
5384 case SPELL_EFFECT_LEAP_BACK:
5385 {
5386 if (m_caster->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_ROOT))
5387 {
5388 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
5389 return SPELL_FAILED_ROOTED;
5390 else
5391 return SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
5392 }
5393 break;
5394 }
5395 case SPELL_EFFECT_TALENT_SPEC_SELECT:
5396 {
5397 // can't change during already started arena/battleground
5398 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
5399 if (Battleground const* bg = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetBattleground())
5400 if (bg->GetStatus() == STATUS_IN_PROGRESS)
5401 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_IN_BATTLEGROUND;
5402 break;
5403 }
5404 case SPELL_EFFECT_REMOVE_TALENT:
5405 {
5406 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5407 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5408 TalentEntry const* talent = sTalentStore.LookupEntry(m_misc.TalentId);
5409 if (!talent)
5410 return SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
5411 if (m_caster->GetSpellHistory()->HasCooldown(talent->SpellID))
5412 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_UNTALENT;
5413 break;
5414 }
5415 default:
5416 break;
5417 }
5418 }
5419
5420 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
5421 {
5422 if (!effect)
5423 continue;
5424 switch (effect->ApplyAuraName)
5425 {
5426 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_POSSESS_PET:
5427 {
5428 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5429 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_PET;
5430
5431 Pet* pet = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetPet();
5432 if (!pet)
5433 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_PET;
5434
5435 if (!pet->GetCharmerGUID().IsEmpty())
5436 return SPELL_FAILED_CHARMED;
5437 break;
5438 }
5439 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_POSSESS:
5440 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_CHARM:
5441 case SPELL_AURA_AOE_CHARM:
5442 {
5443 if (!m_caster->GetCharmerGUID().IsEmpty())
5444 return SPELL_FAILED_CHARMED;
5445
5446 if (effect->ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_CHARM
5447 || effect->ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MOD_POSSESS)
5448 {
5449 if (!m_caster->GetPetGUID().IsEmpty())
5450 return SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_HAVE_SUMMON;
5451
5452 if (!m_caster->GetCharmGUID().IsEmpty())
5453 return SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_HAVE_CHARM;
5454 }
5455
5456 if (Unit* target = m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
5457 {
5458 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && target->IsVehicle())
5459 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_IMPLICIT_TARGETS;
5460
5461 if (target->IsMounted())
5462 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_CHARMED;
5463
5464 if (!target->GetCharmerGUID().IsEmpty())
5465 return SPELL_FAILED_CHARMED;
5466
5467 if (target->GetOwner() && target->GetOwner()->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
5468 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_IS_PLAYER_CONTROLLED;
5469
5470 int32 value = CalculateDamage(effect->EffectIndex, target);
5471 if (value && int32(target->getLevel()) > value)
5472 return SPELL_FAILED_HIGHLEVEL;
5473 }
5474
5475 break;
5476 }
5477 case SPELL_AURA_MOUNTED:
5478 {
5479 if (m_caster->IsInWater())
5480 return SPELL_FAILED_ONLY_ABOVEWATER;
5481
5482 // Ignore map check if spell have AreaId. AreaId already checked and this prevent special mount spells
5483 bool allowMount = !m_caster->GetMap()->IsDungeon() || m_caster->GetMap()->IsBattlegroundOrArena();
5484 InstanceTemplate const* it = sObjectMgr->GetInstanceTemplate(m_caster->GetMapId());
5485 if (it)
5486 allowMount = it->AllowMount;
5487 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && !allowMount && !m_spellInfo->RequiredAreasID)
5488 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_MOUNTS_ALLOWED;
5489
5490 if (m_caster->IsInDisallowedMountForm())
5491 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_SHAPESHIFT;
5492
5493 break;
5494 }
5495 case SPELL_AURA_RANGED_ATTACK_POWER_ATTACKER_BONUS:
5496 {
5497 if (!m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
5498 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_IMPLICIT_TARGETS;
5499
5500 // can be cast at non-friendly unit or own pet/charm
5501 if (m_caster->IsFriendlyTo(m_targets.GetUnitTarget()))
5502 return SPELL_FAILED_TARGET_FRIENDLY;
5503
5504 break;
5505 }
5506 case SPELL_AURA_FLY:
5507 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_INCREASE_MOUNTED_FLIGHT_SPEED:
5508 {
5509 // not allow cast fly spells if not have req. skills (all spells is self target)
5510 // allow always ghost flight spells
5511 if (m_originalCaster && m_originalCaster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER && m_originalCaster->IsAlive())
5512 {
5513 Battlefield* Bf = sBattlefieldMgr->GetBattlefieldToZoneId(m_originalCaster->GetZoneId());
5514 if (AreaTableEntry const* area = sAreaTableStore.LookupEntry(m_originalCaster->GetAreaId()))
5515 if (area->Flags[0] & AREA_FLAG_NO_FLY_ZONE || (Bf && !Bf->CanFlyIn()))
5516 return (_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DONT_REPORT_CAST_ERROR) ? SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT : SPELL_FAILED_NOT_HERE;
5517 }
5518 break;
5519 }
5520 case SPELL_AURA_PERIODIC_MANA_LEECH:
5521 {
5522 if (effect->IsTargetingArea())
5523 break;
5524
5525 if (!m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
5526 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_IMPLICIT_TARGETS;
5527
5528 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER || m_CastItem)
5529 break;
5530
5531 if (m_targets.GetUnitTarget()->getPowerType() != POWER_MANA)
5532 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5533
5534 break;
5535 }
5536 default:
5537 break;
5538 }
5539 }
5540
5541 // check trade slot case (last, for allow catch any another cast problems)
5542 if (m_targets.GetTargetMask() & TARGET_FLAG_TRADE_ITEM)
5543 {
5544 if (m_CastItem)
5545 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_ENCHANT_TRADE_WINDOW;
5546
5547 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
5548 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_TRADING;
5549
5550 TradeData* my_trade = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetTradeData();
5551
5552 if (!my_trade)
5553 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_TRADING;
5554
5555 if (m_targets.GetItemTargetGUID() != ObjectGuid::TradeItem)
5556 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
5557
5558 if (!IsTriggered())
5559 if (my_trade->GetSpell())
5560 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_ALREADY_ENCHANTED;
5561 }
5562
5563 // check if caster has at least 1 combo point for spells that require combo points
5564 if (m_needComboPoints)
5565 if (Player* plrCaster = m_caster->ToPlayer())
5566 if (!plrCaster->GetComboPoints())
5567 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_COMBO_POINTS;
5568
5569 // all ok
5570 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5571}
5572
5573SpellCastResult Spell::CheckPetCast(Unit* target)
5574{
5575 if (m_caster->HasUnitState(UNIT_STATE_CASTING) && !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_CAST_IN_PROGRESS)) //prevent spellcast interruption by another spellcast
5576 return SPELL_FAILED_SPELL_IN_PROGRESS;
5577
5578 // dead owner (pets still alive when owners ressed?)
5579 if (Unit* owner = m_caster->GetCharmerOrOwner())
5580 if (!owner->IsAlive())
5581 return SPELL_FAILED_CASTER_DEAD;
5582
5583 if (!target && m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
5584 target = m_targets.GetUnitTarget();
5585
5586 if (m_spellInfo->NeedsExplicitUnitTarget())
5587 {
5588 if (!target)
5589 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_IMPLICIT_TARGETS;
5590 m_targets.SetUnitTarget(target);
5591 }
5592
5593 // cooldown
5594 if (Creature* creatureCaster = m_caster->ToCreature())
5595 if (!creatureCaster->GetSpellHistory()->IsReady(m_spellInfo))
5596 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_READY;
5597
5598 // Check if spell is affected by GCD
5599 if (m_spellInfo->StartRecoveryCategory > 0)
5600 if (m_caster->GetCharmInfo() && m_caster->GetSpellHistory()->HasGlobalCooldown(m_spellInfo))
5601 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_READY;
5602
5603 return CheckCast(true);
5604}
5605
5606SpellCastResult Spell::CheckCasterAuras() const
5607{
5608 // spells totally immuned to caster auras (wsg flag drop, give marks etc)
5609 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR6_IGNORE_CASTER_AURAS))
5610 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5611
5612 uint8 school_immune = 0;
5613 uint32 mechanic_immune = 0;
5614 uint32 dispel_immune = 0;
5615
5616 // Check if the spell grants school or mechanic immunity.
5617 // We use bitmasks so the loop is done only once and not on every aura check below.
5618 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR1_DISPEL_AURAS_ON_IMMUNITY))
5619 {
5620 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
5621 {
5622 if (!effect)
5623 continue;
5624
5625 if (effect->ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_SCHOOL_IMMUNITY)
5626 school_immune |= uint32(effect->MiscValue);
5627 else if (effect->ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_MECHANIC_IMMUNITY)
5628 mechanic_immune |= 1 << uint32(effect->MiscValue);
5629 else if (effect->ApplyAuraName == SPELL_AURA_DISPEL_IMMUNITY)
5630 dispel_immune |= SpellInfo::GetDispelMask(DispelType(effect->MiscValue));
5631 }
5632 // immune movement impairment and loss of control
5633 if (m_spellInfo->Id == 42292 || m_spellInfo->Id == 59752 || m_spellInfo->Id == 19574)
5634 mechanic_immune = IMMUNE_TO_MOVEMENT_IMPAIRMENT_AND_LOSS_CONTROL_MASK;
5635 }
5636
5637 bool usableInStun = m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_USABLE_WHILE_STUNNED);
5638
5639 // Glyph of Pain Suppression
5640 // Allow Pain Suppression and Guardian Spirit to be cast while stunned
5641 // there is no other way to handle it
5642 if ((m_spellInfo->Id == 33206 || m_spellInfo->Id == 47788) && !m_caster->HasAura(63248))
5643 usableInStun = false;
5644
5645 // Check whether the cast should be prevented by any state you might have.
5646 SpellCastResult prevented_reason = SPELL_CAST_OK;
5647 // Have to check if there is a stun aura. Otherwise will have problems with ghost aura apply while logging out
5648 uint32 unitflag = m_caster->GetUInt32Value(UNIT_FIELD_FLAGS); // Get unit state
5649 if (unitflag & UNIT_FLAG_STUNNED)
5650 {
5651 // spell is usable while stunned, check if caster has only mechanic stun auras, another stun types must prevent cast spell
5652 if (usableInStun)
5653 {
5654 bool foundNotStun = false;
5655 Unit::AuraEffectList const& stunAuras = m_caster->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_MOD_STUN);
5656 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator i = stunAuras.begin(); i != stunAuras.end(); ++i)
5657 {
5658 if ((*i)->GetSpellInfo()->GetAllEffectsMechanicMask() && !((*i)->GetSpellInfo()->GetAllEffectsMechanicMask() & (1<<MECHANIC_STUN)))
5659 {
5660 foundNotStun = true;
5661 break;
5662 }
5663 }
5664 if (foundNotStun && m_spellInfo->Id != 22812)
5665 prevented_reason = SPELL_FAILED_STUNNED;
5666 }
5667 else
5668 prevented_reason = SPELL_FAILED_STUNNED;
5669 }
5670 else if (unitflag & UNIT_FLAG_CONFUSED && !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_USABLE_WHILE_CONFUSED))
5671 prevented_reason = SPELL_FAILED_CONFUSED;
5672 else if (unitflag & UNIT_FLAG_FLEEING && !m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_USABLE_WHILE_FEARED))
5673 prevented_reason = SPELL_FAILED_FLEEING;
5674 else if (unitflag & UNIT_FLAG_SILENCED && m_spellInfo->PreventionType == SPELL_PREVENTION_TYPE_SILENCE)
5675 prevented_reason = SPELL_FAILED_SILENCED;
5676 else if (unitflag & UNIT_FLAG_PACIFIED && m_spellInfo->PreventionType == SPELL_PREVENTION_TYPE_PACIFY)
5677 prevented_reason = SPELL_FAILED_PACIFIED;
5678
5679 // Attr must make flag drop spell totally immune from all effects
5680 if (prevented_reason != SPELL_CAST_OK)
5681 {
5682 if (school_immune || mechanic_immune || dispel_immune)
5683 {
5684 //Checking auras is needed now, because you are prevented by some state but the spell grants immunity.
5685 Unit::AuraApplicationMap const& auras = m_caster->GetAppliedAuras();
5686 for (Unit::AuraApplicationMap::const_iterator itr = auras.begin(); itr != auras.end(); ++itr)
5687 {
5688 Aura const* aura = itr->second->GetBase();
5689 SpellInfo const* auraInfo = aura->GetSpellInfo();
5690 if (auraInfo->GetAllEffectsMechanicMask() & mechanic_immune)
5691 continue;
5692 if (auraInfo->GetSchoolMask() & school_immune && !auraInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR1_UNAFFECTED_BY_SCHOOL_IMMUNE))
5693 continue;
5694 if (auraInfo->GetDispelMask() & dispel_immune)
5695 continue;
5696
5697 //Make a second check for spell failed so the right SPELL_FAILED message is returned.
5698 //That is needed when your casting is prevented by multiple states and you are only immune to some of them.
5699 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
5700 {
5701 if (!effect)
5702 continue;
5703
5704 if (AuraEffect* part = aura->GetEffect(effect->EffectIndex))
5705 {
5706 switch (part->GetAuraType())
5707 {
5708 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_STUN:
5709 if (!usableInStun || !(auraInfo->GetAllEffectsMechanicMask() & (1<<MECHANIC_STUN)))
5710 return SPELL_FAILED_STUNNED;
5711 break;
5712 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_CONFUSE:
5713 if (!m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_USABLE_WHILE_CONFUSED))
5714 return SPELL_FAILED_CONFUSED;
5715 break;
5716 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_FEAR:
5717 if (!m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR5_USABLE_WHILE_FEARED))
5718 return SPELL_FAILED_FLEEING;
5719 break;
5720 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_SILENCE:
5721 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_PACIFY:
5722 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_PACIFY_SILENCE:
5723 if (m_spellInfo->PreventionType == SPELL_PREVENTION_TYPE_PACIFY)
5724 return SPELL_FAILED_PACIFIED;
5725 else if (m_spellInfo->PreventionType == SPELL_PREVENTION_TYPE_SILENCE)
5726 return SPELL_FAILED_SILENCED;
5727 break;
5728 default: break;
5729 }
5730 }
5731 }
5732 }
5733 }
5734 // You are prevented from casting and the spell cast does not grant immunity. Return a failed error.
5735 else
5736 return prevented_reason;
5737 }
5738 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5739}
5740
5741SpellCastResult Spell::CheckArenaAndRatedBattlegroundCastRules()
5742{
5743 bool isRatedBattleground = false; // NYI
5744 bool isArena = !isRatedBattleground;
5745
5746 // check USABLE attributes
5747 // USABLE takes precedence over NOT_USABLE
5748 if (isRatedBattleground && m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR9_USABLE_IN_RATED_BATTLEGROUNDS))
5749 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5750
5751 if (isArena && m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR4_USABLE_IN_ARENA))
5752 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5753
5754 // check NOT_USABLE attributes
5755 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR4_NOT_USABLE_IN_ARENA_OR_RATED_BG))
5756 return isArena ? SPELL_FAILED_NOT_IN_ARENA : SPELL_FAILED_NOT_IN_RATED_BATTLEGROUND;
5757
5758 if (isArena && m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR9_NOT_USABLE_IN_ARENA))
5759 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_IN_ARENA;
5760
5761 // check cooldowns
5762 uint32 spellCooldown = m_spellInfo->GetRecoveryTime();
5763 if (isArena && spellCooldown > 10 * MINUTE * IN_MILLISECONDS) // not sure if still needed
5764 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_IN_ARENA;
5765
5766 if (isRatedBattleground && spellCooldown > 15 * MINUTE * IN_MILLISECONDS)
5767 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_IN_RATED_BATTLEGROUND;
5768
5769 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5770}
5771
5772bool Spell::CanAutoCast(Unit* target)
5773{
5774 ObjectGuid targetguid = target->GetGUID();
5775
5776 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
5777 {
5778 if (!effect)
5779 continue;
5780
5781 if (effect->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_APPLY_AURA)
5782 {
5783 if (m_spellInfo->StackAmount <= 1)
5784 {
5785 if (target->HasAuraEffect(m_spellInfo->Id, effect->EffectIndex))
5786 return false;
5787 }
5788 else
5789 {
5790 if (AuraEffect* aureff = target->GetAuraEffect(m_spellInfo->Id, effect->EffectIndex))
5791 if (aureff->GetBase()->GetStackAmount() >= m_spellInfo->StackAmount)
5792 return false;
5793 }
5794 }
5795 else if (effect->IsAreaAuraEffect())
5796 {
5797 if (target->HasAuraEffect(m_spellInfo->Id, effect->EffectIndex))
5798 return false;
5799 }
5800 }
5801
5802 SpellCastResult result = CheckPetCast(target);
5803
5804 if (result == SPELL_CAST_OK || result == SPELL_FAILED_UNIT_NOT_INFRONT)
5805 {
5806 SelectSpellTargets();
5807 //check if among target units, our WANTED target is as well (->only self cast spells return false)
5808 for (std::vector<TargetInfo>::iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
5809 if (ihit->targetGUID == targetguid)
5810 return true;
5811 }
5812 return false; //target invalid
5813}
5814
5815SpellCastResult Spell::CheckRange(bool strict)
5816{
5817 // Don't check for instant cast spells
5818 if (!strict && m_casttime == 0)
5819 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5820
5821 uint32 range_type = 0;
5822
5823 if (m_spellInfo->RangeEntry)
5824 {
5825 // check needed by 68766 51693 - both spells are cast on enemies and have 0 max range
5826 // these are triggered by other spells - possibly we should omit range check in that case?
5827 if (m_spellInfo->RangeEntry->ID == 1)
5828 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5829
5830 range_type = m_spellInfo->RangeEntry->Flags;
5831 }
5832
5833 Unit* target = m_targets.GetUnitTarget();
5834 float max_range = m_caster->GetSpellMaxRangeForTarget(target, m_spellInfo);
5835 float min_range = m_caster->GetSpellMinRangeForTarget(target, m_spellInfo);
5836
5837 if (Player* modOwner = m_caster->GetSpellModOwner())
5838 modOwner->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_RANGE, max_range, this);
5839
5840 if (target && target != m_caster)
5841 {
5842 if (range_type == SPELL_RANGE_MELEE)
5843 {
5844 // Because of lag, we can not check too strictly here.
5845 if (!m_caster->IsWithinMeleeRange(target, max_range))
5846 return !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DONT_REPORT_CAST_ERROR) ? SPELL_FAILED_OUT_OF_RANGE : SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
5847 }
5848 else if (!m_caster->IsWithinCombatRange(target, max_range))
5849 return !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DONT_REPORT_CAST_ERROR) ? SPELL_FAILED_OUT_OF_RANGE : SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT; //0x5A;
5850
5851 if (range_type == SPELL_RANGE_RANGED)
5852 {
5853 if (m_caster->IsWithinMeleeRange(target))
5854 return !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DONT_REPORT_CAST_ERROR) ? SPELL_FAILED_TOO_CLOSE : SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
5855 }
5856 else if (min_range && m_caster->IsWithinCombatRange(target, min_range)) // skip this check if min_range = 0
5857 return !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DONT_REPORT_CAST_ERROR) ? SPELL_FAILED_TOO_CLOSE : SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
5858
5859 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER &&
5860 (m_spellInfo->FacingCasterFlags & SPELL_FACING_FLAG_INFRONT) && !m_caster->HasInArc(static_cast<float>(M_PI), target))
5861 return !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DONT_REPORT_CAST_ERROR) ? SPELL_FAILED_UNIT_NOT_INFRONT : SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
5862 }
5863
5864 if (m_targets.HasDst() && !m_targets.HasTraj())
5865 {
5866 if (!m_caster->IsWithinDist3d(m_targets.GetDstPos(), max_range))
5867 return SPELL_FAILED_OUT_OF_RANGE;
5868 if (min_range && m_caster->IsWithinDist3d(m_targets.GetDstPos(), min_range))
5869 return SPELL_FAILED_TOO_CLOSE;
5870 }
5871
5872 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5873}
5874
5875SpellCastResult Spell::CheckPower()
5876{
5877 // item cast not used power
5878 if (m_CastItem)
5879 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5880
5881 for (SpellInfo::CostData const& cost : m_powerCost)
5882 {
5883 // health as power used - need check health amount
5884 if (cost.Power == POWER_HEALTH)
5885 {
5886 if (int32(m_caster->GetHealth()) <= cost.Amount)
5887 return SPELL_FAILED_CASTER_AURASTATE;
5888 continue;
5889 }
5890 // Check valid power type
5891 if (cost.Power >= MAX_POWERS)
5892 {
5893 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "Spell::CheckPower: Unknown power type '%d'", cost.Power);
5894 return SPELL_FAILED_UNKNOWN;
5895 }
5896
5897 //check rune cost only if a spell has PowerType == POWER_RUNES
5898 if (cost.Power == POWER_RUNES)
5899 {
5900 SpellCastResult failReason = CheckRuneCost(m_spellInfo->RuneCostID);
5901 if (failReason != SPELL_CAST_OK)
5902 return failReason;
5903 }
5904
5905 // Check power amount
5906 if (int32(m_caster->GetPower(cost.Power)) < cost.Amount)
5907 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_POWER;
5908 }
5909
5910 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5911}
5912
5913SpellCastResult Spell::CheckItems()
5914{
5915 Player* player = m_caster->ToPlayer();
5916 if (!player)
5917 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
5918
5919 if (!m_CastItem)
5920 {
5921 if (!m_castItemGUID.IsEmpty())
5922 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_NOT_READY;
5923 }
5924 else
5925 {
5926 uint32 itemid = m_CastItem->GetEntry();
5927 if (!player->HasItemCount(itemid))
5928 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_NOT_READY;
5929
5930 ItemTemplate const* proto = m_CastItem->GetTemplate();
5931 if (!proto)
5932 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_NOT_READY;
5933
5934 for (uint8 i = 0; i < proto->Effects.size() && i < 5; ++i)
5935 if (proto->Effects[i]->Charges)
5936 if (m_CastItem->GetSpellCharges(i) == 0)
5937 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_CHARGES_REMAIN;
5938
5939 // consumable cast item checks
5940 if (proto->GetClass() == ITEM_CLASS_CONSUMABLE && m_targets.GetUnitTarget())
5941 {
5942 // such items should only fail if there is no suitable effect at all - see Rejuvenation Potions for example
5943 SpellCastResult failReason = SPELL_CAST_OK;
5944 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
5945 {
5946 // skip check, pet not required like checks, and for TARGET_UNIT_PET m_targets.GetUnitTarget() is not the real target but the caster
5947 if (!effect || effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_PET)
5948 continue;
5949
5950 if (effect->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_HEAL)
5951 {
5952 if (m_targets.GetUnitTarget()->IsFullHealth())
5953 {
5954 failReason = SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_AT_FULL_HEALTH;
5955 continue;
5956 }
5957 else
5958 {
5959 failReason = SPELL_CAST_OK;
5960 break;
5961 }
5962 }
5963
5964 // Mana Potion, Rage Potion, Thistle Tea(Rogue), ...
5965 if (effect->Effect == SPELL_EFFECT_ENERGIZE)
5966 {
5967 if (effect->MiscValue < 0 || effect->MiscValue >= int8(MAX_POWERS))
5968 {
5969 failReason = SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_AT_FULL_POWER;
5970 continue;
5971 }
5972
5973 Powers power = Powers(effect->MiscValue);
5974 if (m_targets.GetUnitTarget()->GetPower(power) == m_targets.GetUnitTarget()->GetMaxPower(power))
5975 {
5976 failReason = SPELL_FAILED_ALREADY_AT_FULL_POWER;
5977 continue;
5978 }
5979 else
5980 {
5981 failReason = SPELL_CAST_OK;
5982 break;
5983 }
5984 }
5985 }
5986 if (failReason != SPELL_CAST_OK)
5987 return failReason;
5988 }
5989 }
5990
5991 // check target item
5992 if (!m_targets.GetItemTargetGUID().IsEmpty())
5993 {
5994 if (!m_targets.GetItemTarget())
5995 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_GONE;
5996
5997 if (!m_targets.GetItemTarget()->IsFitToSpellRequirements(m_spellInfo))
5998 return SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM_CLASS;
5999 }
6000 // if not item target then required item must be equipped
6001 else
6002 {
6003 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_EQUIPPED_ITEM_REQUIREMENT))
6004 if (!player->HasItemFitToSpellRequirements(m_spellInfo))
6005 return SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM_CLASS;
6006 }
6007
6008 // do not take reagents for these item casts
6009 if (!(m_CastItem && m_CastItem->GetTemplate()->GetFlags() & ITEM_FLAG_TRIGGERED_CAST))
6010 {
6011 bool checkReagents = !(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_POWER_AND_REAGENT_COST) && !player->CanNoReagentCast(m_spellInfo);
6012 // Not own traded item (in trader trade slot) requires reagents even if triggered spell
6013 if (!checkReagents)
6014 if (Item* targetItem = m_targets.GetItemTarget())
6015 if (targetItem->GetOwnerGUID() != m_caster->GetGUID())
6016 checkReagents = true;
6017
6018 // check reagents (ignore triggered spells with reagents processed by original spell) and special reagent ignore case.
6019 if (checkReagents)
6020 {
6021 for (uint32 i = 0; i < MAX_SPELL_REAGENTS; i++)
6022 {
6023 if (m_spellInfo->Reagent[i] <= 0)
6024 continue;
6025
6026 uint32 itemid = m_spellInfo->Reagent[i];
6027 uint32 itemcount = m_spellInfo->ReagentCount[i];
6028
6029 // if CastItem is also spell reagent
6030 if (m_CastItem && m_CastItem->GetEntry() == itemid)
6031 {
6032 ItemTemplate const* proto = m_CastItem->GetTemplate();
6033 if (!proto)
6034 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_NOT_READY;
6035 for (uint8 s = 0; s < proto->Effects.size() && s < 5; ++s)
6036 {
6037 // CastItem will be used up and does not count as reagent
6038 int32 charges = m_CastItem->GetSpellCharges(s);
6039 if (proto->Effects[s]->Charges < 0 && abs(charges) < 2)
6040 {
6041 ++itemcount;
6042 break;
6043 }
6044 }
6045 }
6046 if (!player->HasItemCount(itemid, itemcount))
6047 return SPELL_FAILED_REAGENTS;
6048 }
6049 }
6050
6051 // check totem-item requirements (items presence in inventory)
6052 uint32 totems = 2;
6053 for (uint8 i = 0; i < 2; ++i)
6054 {
6055 if (m_spellInfo->Totem[i] != 0)
6056 {
6057 if (player->HasItemCount(m_spellInfo->Totem[i]))
6058 {
6059 totems -= 1;
6060 continue;
6061 }
6062 }
6063 else
6064 totems -= 1;
6065 }
6066
6067 if (totems != 0)
6068 return SPELL_FAILED_TOTEMS;
6069
6070 // Check items for TotemCategory (items presence in inventory)
6071 uint32 totemCategory = 2;
6072 for (uint8 i = 0; i < 2; ++i)
6073 {
6074 if (m_spellInfo->TotemCategory[i] != 0)
6075 {
6076 if (player->HasItemTotemCategory(m_spellInfo->TotemCategory[i]))
6077 {
6078 totemCategory -= 1;
6079 continue;
6080 }
6081 }
6082 else
6083 totemCategory -= 1;
6084 }
6085
6086 if (totemCategory != 0)
6087 return SPELL_FAILED_TOTEM_CATEGORY;
6088 }
6089
6090 // special checks for spell effects
6091 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
6092 {
6093 if (!effect)
6094 continue;
6095
6096 switch (effect->Effect)
6097 {
6098 case SPELL_EFFECT_CREATE_ITEM:
6099 case SPELL_EFFECT_CREATE_ITEM_2:
6100 {
6101 if (!IsTriggered() && effect->ItemType)
6102 {
6103 ItemPosCountVec dest;
6104 InventoryResult msg = player->CanStoreNewItem(NULL_BAG, NULL_SLOT, dest, effect->ItemType, 1);
6105 if (msg != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
6106 {
6107 ItemTemplate const* pProto = sObjectMgr->GetItemTemplate(effect->ItemType);
6108 /// @todo Needs review
6109 if (pProto && !(pProto->GetItemLimitCategory()))
6110 {
6111 player->SendEquipError(msg, NULL, NULL, effect->ItemType);
6112 return SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
6113 }
6114 else
6115 {
6116 if (!(m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName == SPELLFAMILY_MAGE && (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x40000000)))
6117 return SPELL_FAILED_TOO_MANY_OF_ITEM;
6118 else if (!(player->HasItemCount(effect->ItemType)))
6119 return SPELL_FAILED_TOO_MANY_OF_ITEM;
6120 else if (SpellEffectInfo const* efi = GetEffect(EFFECT_1))
6121 player->CastSpell(m_caster, efi->CalcValue(), false); // move this to anywhere
6122 return SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
6123 }
6124 }
6125 }
6126 break;
6127 }
6128 case SPELL_EFFECT_ENCHANT_ITEM:
6129 if (effect->ItemType && m_targets.GetItemTarget()
6130 && (m_targets.GetItemTarget()->IsVellum()))
6131 {
6132 // cannot enchant vellum for other player
6133 if (m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetOwner() != m_caster)
6134 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_TRADEABLE;
6135 // do not allow to enchant vellum from scroll made by vellum-prevent exploit
6136 if (m_CastItem && m_CastItem->GetTemplate()->GetFlags() & ITEM_FLAG_TRIGGERED_CAST)
6137 return SPELL_FAILED_TOTEM_CATEGORY;
6138 ItemPosCountVec dest;
6139 InventoryResult msg = player->CanStoreNewItem(NULL_BAG, NULL_SLOT, dest, effect->ItemType, 1);
6140 if (msg != EQUIP_ERR_OK)
6141 {
6142 player->SendEquipError(msg, NULL, NULL, effect->ItemType);
6143 return SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT;
6144 }
6145 }
6146 // no break
6147 case SPELL_EFFECT_ENCHANT_ITEM_PRISMATIC:
6148 {
6149 Item* targetItem = m_targets.GetItemTarget();
6150 if (!targetItem)
6151 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_NOT_FOUND;
6152
6153 if (targetItem->GetTemplate()->GetBaseItemLevel() < m_spellInfo->BaseLevel)
6154 return SPELL_FAILED_LOWLEVEL;
6155
6156 bool isItemUsable = false;
6157 ItemTemplate const* proto = targetItem->GetTemplate();
6158 for (uint8 e = 0; e < proto->Effects.size(); ++e)
6159 {
6160 if (proto->Effects[e]->SpellID && (
6161 proto->Effects[e]->Trigger == ITEM_SPELLTRIGGER_ON_USE ||
6162 proto->Effects[e]->Trigger == ITEM_SPELLTRIGGER_ON_NO_DELAY_USE))
6163 {
6164 isItemUsable = true;
6165 break;
6166 }
6167 }
6168
6169 SpellItemEnchantmentEntry const* enchantEntry = sSpellItemEnchantmentStore.LookupEntry(effect->MiscValue);
6170 // do not allow adding usable enchantments to items that have use effect already
6171 if (enchantEntry)
6172 {
6173 for (uint8 s = 0; s < MAX_ITEM_ENCHANTMENT_EFFECTS; ++s)
6174 {
6175 switch (enchantEntry->Effect[s])
6176 {
6177 case ITEM_ENCHANTMENT_TYPE_USE_SPELL:
6178 if (isItemUsable)
6179 return SPELL_FAILED_ON_USE_ENCHANT;
6180 break;
6181 case ITEM_ENCHANTMENT_TYPE_PRISMATIC_SOCKET:
6182 {
6183 uint32 numSockets = 0;
6184 for (uint32 socket = 0; socket < MAX_ITEM_PROTO_SOCKETS; ++socket)
6185 if (targetItem->GetSocketColor(socket))
6186 ++numSockets;
6187
6188 if (numSockets == MAX_ITEM_PROTO_SOCKETS || targetItem->GetEnchantmentId(PRISMATIC_ENCHANTMENT_SLOT))
6189 return SPELL_FAILED_MAX_SOCKETS;
6190 break;
6191 }
6192 }
6193 }
6194 }
6195
6196 // Not allow enchant in trade slot for some enchant type
6197 if (targetItem->GetOwner() != m_caster)
6198 {
6199 if (!enchantEntry)
6200 return SPELL_FAILED_ERROR;
6201 if (enchantEntry->Flags & ENCHANTMENT_CAN_SOULBOUND)
6202 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_TRADEABLE;
6203 }
6204 break;
6205 }
6206 case SPELL_EFFECT_ENCHANT_ITEM_TEMPORARY:
6207 {
6208 Item* item = m_targets.GetItemTarget();
6209 if (!item)
6210 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_NOT_FOUND;
6211 // Not allow enchant in trade slot for some enchant type
6212 if (item->GetOwner() != m_caster)
6213 {
6214 uint32 enchant_id = effect->MiscValue;
6215 SpellItemEnchantmentEntry const* pEnchant = sSpellItemEnchantmentStore.LookupEntry(enchant_id);
6216 if (!pEnchant)
6217 return SPELL_FAILED_ERROR;
6218 if (pEnchant->Flags & ENCHANTMENT_CAN_SOULBOUND)
6219 return SPELL_FAILED_NOT_TRADEABLE;
6220 }
6221 break;
6222 }
6223 case SPELL_EFFECT_ENCHANT_HELD_ITEM:
6224 // check item existence in effect code (not output errors at offhand hold item effect to main hand for example
6225 break;
6226 case SPELL_EFFECT_DISENCHANT:
6227 {
6228 if (!m_targets.GetItemTarget())
6229 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_DISENCHANTED;
6230
6231 // prevent disenchanting in trade slot
6232 if (m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetOwnerGUID() != m_caster->GetGUID())
6233 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_DISENCHANTED;
6234
6235 ItemTemplate const* itemProto = m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetTemplate();
6236 if (!itemProto)
6237 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_DISENCHANTED;
6238
6239 uint32 item_quality = itemProto->GetQuality();
6240 // 2.0.x addon: Check player enchanting level against the item disenchanting requirements
6241 uint32 item_disenchantskilllevel = itemProto->RequiredDisenchantSkill;
6242 if (item_disenchantskilllevel == uint32(-1))
6243 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_DISENCHANTED;
6244 if (item_disenchantskilllevel > player->GetSkillValue(SKILL_ENCHANTING))
6245 return SPELL_FAILED_LOW_CASTLEVEL;
6246 if (item_quality > 4 || item_quality < 2)
6247 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_DISENCHANTED;
6248 if (itemProto->GetClass() != ITEM_CLASS_WEAPON && itemProto->GetClass() != ITEM_CLASS_ARMOR)
6249 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_DISENCHANTED;
6250 if (!itemProto->DisenchantID)
6251 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_DISENCHANTED;
6252 break;
6253 }
6254 case SPELL_EFFECT_PROSPECTING:
6255 {
6256 if (!m_targets.GetItemTarget())
6257 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_PROSPECTED;
6258 //ensure item is a prospectable ore
6259 if (!(m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetTemplate()->GetFlags() & ITEM_FLAG_PROSPECTABLE))
6260 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_PROSPECTED;
6261 //prevent prospecting in trade slot
6262 if (m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetOwnerGUID() != m_caster->GetGUID())
6263 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_PROSPECTED;
6264 //Check for enough skill in jewelcrafting
6265 uint32 item_prospectingskilllevel = m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetTemplate()->GetRequiredSkillRank();
6266 if (item_prospectingskilllevel >player->GetSkillValue(SKILL_JEWELCRAFTING))
6267 return SPELL_FAILED_LOW_CASTLEVEL;
6268 //make sure the player has the required ores in inventory
6269 if (m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetCount() < 5)
6270 return SPELL_FAILED_NEED_MORE_ITEMS;
6271
6272 if (!LootTemplates_Prospecting.HaveLootFor(m_targets.GetItemTargetEntry()))
6273 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_PROSPECTED;
6274
6275 break;
6276 }
6277 case SPELL_EFFECT_MILLING:
6278 {
6279 if (!m_targets.GetItemTarget())
6280 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_MILLED;
6281 //ensure item is a millable herb
6282 if (!(m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetTemplate()->GetFlags() & ITEM_FLAG_MILLABLE))
6283 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_MILLED;
6284 //prevent milling in trade slot
6285 if (m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetOwnerGUID() != m_caster->GetGUID())
6286 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_MILLED;
6287 //Check for enough skill in inscription
6288 uint32 item_millingskilllevel = m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetTemplate()->GetRequiredSkillRank();
6289 if (item_millingskilllevel > player->GetSkillValue(SKILL_INSCRIPTION))
6290 return SPELL_FAILED_LOW_CASTLEVEL;
6291 //make sure the player has the required herbs in inventory
6292 if (m_targets.GetItemTarget()->GetCount() < 5)
6293 return SPELL_FAILED_NEED_MORE_ITEMS;
6294
6295 if (!LootTemplates_Milling.HaveLootFor(m_targets.GetItemTargetEntry()))
6296 return SPELL_FAILED_CANT_BE_MILLED;
6297
6298 break;
6299 }
6300 case SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_DAMAGE:
6301 case SPELL_EFFECT_WEAPON_DAMAGE_NOSCHOOL:
6302 {
6303 if (m_attackType != RANGED_ATTACK)
6304 break;
6305
6306 Item* pItem = player->GetWeaponForAttack(m_attackType);
6307 if (!pItem || pItem->IsBroken())
6308 return SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM;
6309
6310 switch (pItem->GetTemplate()->GetSubClass())
6311 {
6312 case ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_THROWN:
6313 {
6314 uint32 ammo = pItem->GetEntry();
6315 if (!player->HasItemCount(ammo))
6316 return SPELL_FAILED_NO_AMMO;
6317 break;
6318 }
6319 case ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_GUN:
6320 case ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_BOW:
6321 case ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_CROSSBOW:
6322 case ITEM_SUBCLASS_WEAPON_WAND:
6323 break;
6324 default:
6325 break;
6326 }
6327 break;
6328 }
6329 case SPELL_EFFECT_CREATE_MANA_GEM:
6330 {
6331 uint32 item_id = effect->ItemType;
6332 ItemTemplate const* pProto = sObjectMgr->GetItemTemplate(item_id);
6333
6334 if (!pProto)
6335 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_AT_MAX_CHARGES;
6336
6337 if (Item* pitem = player->GetItemByEntry(item_id))
6338 {
6339 for (uint8 x = 0; x < pProto->Effects.size() && x < 5; ++x)
6340 if (pProto->Effects[x]->Charges != 0 && pitem->GetSpellCharges(x) == pProto->Effects[x]->Charges)
6341 return SPELL_FAILED_ITEM_AT_MAX_CHARGES;
6342 }
6343 break;
6344 }
6345 default:
6346 break;
6347 }
6348 }
6349
6350 // check weapon presence in slots for main/offhand weapons
6351 if (!(_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_IGNORE_EQUIPPED_ITEM_REQUIREMENT) && m_spellInfo->EquippedItemClass >=0)
6352 {
6353 // main hand weapon required
6354 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_MAIN_HAND))
6355 {
6356 Item* item = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetWeaponForAttack(BASE_ATTACK);
6357
6358 // skip spell if no weapon in slot or broken
6359 if (!item || item->IsBroken())
6360 return (_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DONT_REPORT_CAST_ERROR) ? SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT : SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM_CLASS;
6361
6362 // skip spell if weapon not fit to triggered spell
6363 if (!item->IsFitToSpellRequirements(m_spellInfo))
6364 return (_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DONT_REPORT_CAST_ERROR) ? SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT : SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM_CLASS;
6365 }
6366
6367 // offhand hand weapon required
6368 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR3_REQ_OFFHAND))
6369 {
6370 Item* item = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetWeaponForAttack(OFF_ATTACK);
6371
6372 // skip spell if no weapon in slot or broken
6373 if (!item || item->IsBroken())
6374 return (_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DONT_REPORT_CAST_ERROR) ? SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT : SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM_CLASS;
6375
6376 // skip spell if weapon not fit to triggered spell
6377 if (!item->IsFitToSpellRequirements(m_spellInfo))
6378 return (_triggeredCastFlags & TRIGGERED_DONT_REPORT_CAST_ERROR) ? SPELL_FAILED_DONT_REPORT : SPELL_FAILED_EQUIPPED_ITEM_CLASS;
6379 }
6380 }
6381
6382 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
6383}
6384
6385void Spell::Delayed() // only called in DealDamage()
6386{
6387 if (!m_caster)// || m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
6388 return;
6389
6390 //if (m_spellState == SPELL_STATE_DELAYED)
6391 // return; // spell is active and can't be time-backed
6392
6393 if (isDelayableNoMore()) // Spells may only be delayed twice
6394 return;
6395
6396 // spells not loosing casting time (slam, dynamites, bombs..)
6397 //if (!(m_spellInfo->InterruptFlags & SPELL_INTERRUPT_FLAG_DAMAGE))
6398 // return;
6399
6400 //check pushback reduce
6401 int32 delaytime = 500; // spellcasting delay is normally 500ms
6402 int32 delayReduce = 100; // must be initialized to 100 for percent modifiers
6403 m_caster->ToPlayer()->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_NOT_LOSE_CASTING_TIME, delayReduce, this);
6404 delayReduce += m_caster->GetTotalAuraModifier(SPELL_AURA_REDUCE_PUSHBACK) - 100;
6405 if (delayReduce >= 100)
6406 return;
6407
6408 AddPct(delaytime, -delayReduce);
6409
6410 if (m_timer + delaytime > m_casttime)
6411 {
6412 delaytime = m_casttime - m_timer;
6413 m_timer = m_casttime;
6414 }
6415 else
6416 m_timer += delaytime;
6417
6418 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell %u partially interrupted for (%d) ms at damage", m_spellInfo->Id, delaytime);
6419
6420 WorldPackets::Spells::SpellDelayed spellDelayed;
6421 spellDelayed.Caster = m_caster->GetGUID();
6422 spellDelayed.ActualDelay = delaytime;
6423
6424 m_caster->SendMessageToSet(spellDelayed.Write(), true);
6425}
6426
6427void Spell::DelayedChannel()
6428{
6429 if (!m_caster || m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER || getState() != SPELL_STATE_CASTING)
6430 return;
6431
6432 if (isDelayableNoMore()) // Spells may only be delayed twice
6433 return;
6434
6435 //check pushback reduce
6436 // should be affected by modifiers, not take the dbc duration.
6437 int32 duration = ((m_channeledDuration > 0) ? m_channeledDuration : m_spellInfo->GetDuration());
6438
6439 int32 delaytime = CalculatePct(duration, 25); // channeling delay is normally 25% of its time per hit
6440 int32 delayReduce = 100; // must be initialized to 100 for percent modifiers
6441 m_caster->ToPlayer()->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_NOT_LOSE_CASTING_TIME, delayReduce, this);
6442 delayReduce += m_caster->GetTotalAuraModifier(SPELL_AURA_REDUCE_PUSHBACK) - 100;
6443 if (delayReduce >= 100)
6444 return;
6445
6446 AddPct(delaytime, -delayReduce);
6447
6448 if (m_timer <= delaytime)
6449 {
6450 delaytime = m_timer;
6451 m_timer = 0;
6452 }
6453 else
6454 m_timer -= delaytime;
6455
6456 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell %u partially interrupted for %i ms, new duration: %u ms", m_spellInfo->Id, delaytime, m_timer);
6457
6458 for (std::vector<TargetInfo>::const_iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
6459 if ((*ihit).missCondition == SPELL_MISS_NONE)
6460 if (Unit* unit = (m_caster->GetGUID() == ihit->targetGUID) ? m_caster : ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, ihit->targetGUID))
6461 unit->DelayOwnedAuras(m_spellInfo->Id, m_originalCasterGUID, delaytime);
6462
6463 // partially interrupt persistent area auras
6464 if (DynamicObject* dynObj = m_caster->GetDynObject(m_spellInfo->Id))
6465 dynObj->Delay(delaytime);
6466
6467 SendChannelUpdate(m_timer);
6468}
6469
6470bool Spell::UpdatePointers()
6471{
6472 if (m_originalCasterGUID == m_caster->GetGUID())
6473 m_originalCaster = m_caster;
6474 else
6475 {
6476 m_originalCaster = ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, m_originalCasterGUID);
6477 if (m_originalCaster && !m_originalCaster->IsInWorld())
6478 m_originalCaster = NULL;
6479 }
6480
6481 if (!m_castItemGUID.IsEmpty() && m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
6482 {
6483 m_CastItem = m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetItemByGuid(m_castItemGUID);
6484 m_castItemLevel = -1;
6485 // cast item not found, somehow the item is no longer where we expected
6486 if (!m_CastItem)
6487 return false;
6488
6489 // check if the item is really the same, in case it has been wrapped for example
6490 if (m_castItemEntry != m_CastItem->GetEntry())
6491 return false;
6492
6493 m_castItemLevel = int32(m_CastItem->GetItemLevel(m_caster->ToPlayer()));
6494 }
6495
6496 m_targets.Update(m_caster);
6497
6498 // further actions done only for dest targets
6499 if (!m_targets.HasDst())
6500 return true;
6501
6502 // cache last transport
6503 WorldObject* transport = NULL;
6504
6505 // update effect destinations (in case of moved transport dest target)
6506 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
6507 {
6508 if (!effect)
6509 continue;
6510
6511 SpellDestination& dest = m_destTargets[effect->EffectIndex];
6512 if (!dest._transportGUID)
6513 continue;
6514
6515 if (!transport || transport->GetGUID() != dest._transportGUID)
6516 transport = ObjectAccessor::GetWorldObject(*m_caster, dest._transportGUID);
6517
6518 if (transport)
6519 {
6520 dest._position.Relocate(transport);
6521 dest._position.RelocateOffset(dest._transportOffset);
6522 }
6523 }
6524
6525 return true;
6526}
6527
6528CurrentSpellTypes Spell::GetCurrentContainer() const
6529{
6530 if (IsNextMeleeSwingSpell())
6531 return(CURRENT_MELEE_SPELL);
6532 else if (IsAutoRepeat())
6533 return(CURRENT_AUTOREPEAT_SPELL);
6534 else if (m_spellInfo->IsChanneled())
6535 return(CURRENT_CHANNELED_SPELL);
6536 else
6537 return(CURRENT_GENERIC_SPELL);
6538}
6539
6540bool Spell::CheckEffectTarget(Unit const* target, SpellEffectInfo const* effect, Position const* losPosition) const
6541{
6542 if (!effect->IsEffect())
6543 return false;
6544
6545 switch (effect->ApplyAuraName)
6546 {
6547 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_POSSESS:
6548 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_CHARM:
6549 case SPELL_AURA_MOD_POSSESS_PET:
6550 case SPELL_AURA_AOE_CHARM:
6551 if (target->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_UNIT && target->IsVehicle())
6552 return false;
6553 if (target->IsMounted())
6554 return false;
6555 if (!target->GetCharmerGUID().IsEmpty())
6556 return false;
6557 if (int32 value = CalculateDamage(effect->EffectIndex, target))
6558 if ((int32)target->getLevel() > value)
6559 return false;
6560 break;
6561 default:
6562 break;
6563 }
6564
6565 // check for ignore LOS on the effect itself
6566 if (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_CAN_TARGET_NOT_IN_LOS) || DisableMgr::IsDisabledFor(DISABLE_TYPE_SPELL, m_spellInfo->Id, NULL, SPELL_DISABLE_LOS))
6567 return true;
6568
6569 // if spell is triggered, need to check for LOS disable on the aura triggering it and inherit that behaviour
6570 if (IsTriggered() && m_triggeredByAuraSpell && (m_triggeredByAuraSpell->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR2_CAN_TARGET_NOT_IN_LOS) || DisableMgr::IsDisabledFor(DISABLE_TYPE_SPELL, m_triggeredByAuraSpell->Id, NULL, SPELL_DISABLE_LOS)))
6571 return true;
6572
6573 /// @todo shit below shouldn't be here, but it's temporary
6574 //Check targets for LOS visibility (except spells without range limitations)
6575 switch (effect->Effect)
6576 {
6577 case SPELL_EFFECT_RESURRECT_NEW:
6578 // player far away, maybe his corpse near?
6579 if (target != m_caster && !target->IsWithinLOSInMap(m_caster))
6580 {
6581 if (!m_targets.GetCorpseTargetGUID())
6582 return false;
6583
6584 Corpse* corpse = ObjectAccessor::GetCorpse(*m_caster, m_targets.GetCorpseTargetGUID());
6585 if (!corpse)
6586 return false;
6587
6588 if (target->GetGUID() != corpse->GetOwnerGUID())
6589 return false;
6590
6591 if (!corpse->IsWithinLOSInMap(m_caster))
6592 return false;
6593 }
6594
6595 // all ok by some way or another, skip normal check
6596 break;
6597 default: // normal case
6598 {
6599 if (losPosition)
6600 return target->IsWithinLOS(losPosition->GetPositionX(), losPosition->GetPositionY(), losPosition->GetPositionZ());
6601 else
6602 {
6603 // Get GO cast coordinates if original caster -> GO
6604 WorldObject* caster = NULL;
6605 if (m_originalCasterGUID.IsGameObject())
6606 caster = m_caster->GetMap()->GetGameObject(m_originalCasterGUID);
6607 if (!caster)
6608 caster = m_caster;
6609 if (target != m_caster && !target->IsWithinLOSInMap(caster))
6610 return false;
6611 }
6612 break;
6613 }
6614 }
6615
6616 return true;
6617}
6618
6619bool Spell::CheckEffectTarget(GameObject const* target, SpellEffectInfo const* effect) const
6620{
6621 if (!effect->IsEffect())
6622 return false;
6623
6624 switch (effect->Effect)
6625 {
6626 case SPELL_EFFECT_GAMEOBJECT_DAMAGE:
6627 case SPELL_EFFECT_GAMEOBJECT_REPAIR:
6628 case SPELL_EFFECT_GAMEOBJECT_SET_DESTRUCTION_STATE:
6629 if (target->GetGoType() != GAMEOBJECT_TYPE_DESTRUCTIBLE_BUILDING)
6630 return false;
6631 break;
6632 default:
6633 break;
6634 }
6635
6636 return true;
6637}

6640{
6641 if (!effect->IsEffect())
6642 return false;
6643
6644 return true;
6645}

6661 (m_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR8_AURA_SEND_AMOUNT)) || m_spellInfo->Speed > 0.0f || (!m_triggeredByAuraSpell && !IsTriggered());

6663
6664bool Spell::HaveTargetsForEffect(uint8 effect) const
6665{
6666 for (std::vector<TargetInfo>::const_iterator itr = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); itr != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++itr)
6667 if (itr->effectMask & (1 << effect))
6668 return true;
6669
6670 for (std::vector<GOTargetInfo>::const_iterator itr = m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.begin(); itr != m_UniqueGOTargetInfo.end(); ++itr)
6671 if (itr->effectMask & (1 << effect))
6672 return true;
6673
6674 for (std::vector<ItemTargetInfo>::const_iterator itr = m_UniqueItemInfo.begin(); itr != m_UniqueItemInfo.end(); ++itr)
6675 if (itr->effectMask & (1 << effect))
6676 return true;
6677
6678 return false;
6679}

6681SpellEvent::SpellEvent(Spell* spell) : BasicEvent()
6682{
6683 m_Spell = spell;
6684}
6685
6686SpellEvent::~SpellEvent()
6687{
6688 if (m_Spell->getState() != SPELL_STATE_FINISHED)
6689 m_Spell->cancel();
6690
6691 if (m_Spell->IsDeletable())
6692 {
6693 delete m_Spell;
6694 }
6695 else
6696 {
6697 TC_LOG_ERROR("spells", "~SpellEvent: %s %s tried to delete non-deletable spell %u. Was not deleted, causes memory leak.",
6698 (m_Spell->GetCaster()->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER ? "Player" : "Creature"), m_Spell->GetCaster()->GetGUID().ToString().c_str(), m_Spell->m_spellInfo->Id);
6699 ABORT();
6700 }
6701}
6702
6703bool SpellEvent::Execute(uint64 e_time, uint32 p_time)
6704{
6705 // update spell if it is not finished
6706 if (m_Spell->getState() != SPELL_STATE_FINISHED)
6707 m_Spell->update(p_time);
6708
6709 // check spell state to process
6710 switch (m_Spell->getState())
6711 {
6712 case SPELL_STATE_FINISHED:
6713 {
6714 // spell was finished, check deletable state
6715 if (m_Spell->IsDeletable())
6716 {
6717 // check, if we do have unfinished triggered spells
6718 return true; // spell is deletable, finish event
6719 }
6720 // event will be re-added automatically at the end of routine)
6721 } break;
6722
6723 case SPELL_STATE_DELAYED:
6724 {
6725 // first, check, if we have just started
6726 if (m_Spell->GetDelayStart() != 0)
6727 {
6728 // no, we aren't, do the typical update
6729 // check, if we have channeled spell on our hands
6730 /*
6731 if (m_Spell->m_spellInfo->IsChanneled())
6732 {
6733 // evented channeled spell is processed separately, cast once after delay, and not destroyed till finish
6734 // check, if we have casting anything else except this channeled spell and autorepeat
6735 if (m_Spell->GetCaster()->IsNonMeleeSpellCast(false, true, true))
6736 {
6737 // another non-melee non-delayed spell is cast now, abort
6738 m_Spell->cancel();
6739 }
6740 else
6741 {
6742 // Set last not triggered spell for apply spellmods
6743 ((Player*)m_Spell->GetCaster())->SetSpellModTakingSpell(m_Spell, true);
6744 // do the action (pass spell to channeling state)
6745 m_Spell->handle_immediate();
6746
6747 // And remove after effect handling
6748 ((Player*)m_Spell->GetCaster())->SetSpellModTakingSpell(m_Spell, false);
6749 }
6750 // event will be re-added automatically at the end of routine)
6751 }
6752 else
6753 */
6754 {
6755 // run the spell handler and think about what we can do next
6756 uint64 t_offset = e_time - m_Spell->GetDelayStart();
6757 uint64 n_offset = m_Spell->handle_delayed(t_offset);
6758 if (n_offset)
6759 {
6760 // re-add us to the queue
6761 m_Spell->GetCaster()->m_Events.AddEvent(this, m_Spell->GetDelayStart() + n_offset, false);
6762 return false; // event not complete
6763 }
6764 // event complete
6765 // finish update event will be re-added automatically at the end of routine)
6766 }
6767 }
6768 else
6769 {
6770 // delaying had just started, record the moment
6771 m_Spell->SetDelayStart(e_time);
6772 // re-plan the event for the delay moment
6773 m_Spell->GetCaster()->m_Events.AddEvent(this, e_time + m_Spell->GetDelayMoment(), false);
6774 return false; // event not complete
6775 }
6776 } break;
6777
6778 default:
6779 {
6780 // all other states
6781 // event will be re-added automatically at the end of routine)
6782 } break;
6783 }
6784
6785 // spell processing not complete, plan event on the next update interval
6786 m_Spell->GetCaster()->m_Events.AddEvent(this, e_time + 1, false);
6787 return false; // event not complete
6788}
6789
6790void SpellEvent::Abort(uint64 /*e_time*/)
6791{
6792 // oops, the spell we try to do is aborted
6793 if (m_Spell->getState() != SPELL_STATE_FINISHED)
6794 m_Spell->cancel();
6795}

6800}
6801
6802bool Spell::IsValidDeadOrAliveTarget(Unit const* target) const
6803{
6804 if (target->IsAlive())

6806 if (m_spellInfo->IsAllowingDeadTarget())
