6810
6811void Spell::HandleLaunchPhase()
6812{
6813 // handle effects with SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_LAUNCH mode
6814 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
6815 {
6816 // don't do anything for empty effect
6817 if (!effect || !effect->IsEffect())
6818 continue;
6819
6820 HandleEffects(NULL, NULL, NULL, effect->EffectIndex, SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_LAUNCH);
6821 }
6822
6823 float multiplier[MAX_SPELL_EFFECTS];
6824 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
6825 if (effect && (m_applyMultiplierMask & (1 << effect->EffectIndex)))
6826 multiplier[effect->EffectIndex] = effect->CalcDamageMultiplier(m_originalCaster, this);
6827
6828 for (std::vector<TargetInfo>::iterator ihit = m_UniqueTargetInfo.begin(); ihit != m_UniqueTargetInfo.end(); ++ihit)
6829 {
6830 TargetInfo& target = *ihit;
6831
6832 uint32 mask = target.effectMask;
6833 if (!mask)
6834 continue;
6835
6836 DoAllEffectOnLaunchTarget(target, multiplier);
6837 }
6838}
6839
6840void Spell::DoAllEffectOnLaunchTarget(TargetInfo& targetInfo, float* multiplier)
6841{
6842 Unit* unit = NULL;
6843 // In case spell hit target, do all effect on that target
6844 if (targetInfo.missCondition == SPELL_MISS_NONE)
6845 unit = m_caster->GetGUID() == targetInfo.targetGUID ? m_caster : ObjectAccessor::GetUnit(*m_caster, targetInfo.targetGUID);
6846 // In case spell reflect from target, do all effect on caster (if hit)
6847 else if (targetInfo.missCondition == SPELL_MISS_REFLECT && targetInfo.reflectResult == SPELL_MISS_NONE)
6848 unit = m_caster;
6849 if (!unit)
6850 return;
6851
6852 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
6853 {
6854 if (effect && (targetInfo.effectMask & (1<<effect->EffectIndex)))
6855 {
6856 m_damage = 0;
6857 m_healing = 0;
6858
6859 HandleEffects(unit, NULL, NULL, effect->EffectIndex, SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_LAUNCH_TARGET);
6860
6861 if (m_damage > 0)
6862 {
6863 if (effect->IsTargetingArea() || effect->IsAreaAuraEffect() || effect->IsEffect(SPELL_EFFECT_PERSISTENT_AREA_AURA))
6864 {
6865 m_damage = int32(float(m_damage) * unit->GetTotalAuraMultiplierByMiscMask(SPELL_AURA_MOD_AOE_DAMAGE_AVOIDANCE, m_spellInfo->SchoolMask));
6866 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER)
6867 m_damage = int32(float(m_damage) * unit->GetTotalAuraMultiplierByMiscMask(SPELL_AURA_MOD_CREATURE_AOE_DAMAGE_AVOIDANCE, m_spellInfo->SchoolMask));
6868
6869 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
6870 {
6871 uint32 targetAmount = m_UniqueTargetInfo.size();
6872 if (targetAmount > 10)
6873 m_damage = m_damage * 10/targetAmount;
6874 }
6875 }
6876 }
6877
6878 if (m_applyMultiplierMask & (1 << effect->EffectIndex))
6879 {
6880 m_damage = int32(m_damage * m_damageMultipliers[effect->EffectIndex]);
6881 m_damageMultipliers[effect->EffectIndex] *= multiplier[effect->EffectIndex];
6882 }
6883 targetInfo.damage += m_damage;
6884 }
6885 }
6886
6887 targetInfo.crit = m_caster->IsSpellCrit(unit, m_spellInfo, m_spellSchoolMask, m_attackType);
6888}
6889
6890SpellCastResult Spell::CanOpenLock(uint32 effIndex, uint32 lockId, SkillType& skillId, int32& reqSkillValue, int32& skillValue)
6891{
6892 if (!lockId) // possible case for GO and maybe for items.
6893 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
6894
6895 // Get LockInfo
6896 LockEntry const* lockInfo = sLockStore.LookupEntry(lockId);
6897
6898 if (!lockInfo)
6899 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
6900
6901 SpellEffectInfo const* effect = GetEffect(effIndex);
6902 if (!effect)
6903 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS; // no idea about correct error
6904
6905 bool reqKey = false; // some locks not have reqs
6906
6907 for (int j = 0; j < MAX_LOCK_CASE; ++j)
6908 {
6909 switch (lockInfo->Type[j])
6910 {
6911 // check key item (many fit cases can be)
6912 case LOCK_KEY_ITEM:
6913 if (lockInfo->Index[j] && m_CastItem && m_CastItem->GetEntry() == lockInfo->Index[j])
6914 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
6915 reqKey = true;
6916 break;
6917 // check key skill (only single first fit case can be)
6918 case LOCK_KEY_SKILL:
6919 {
6920 reqKey = true;
6921
6922 // wrong locktype, skip
6923 if (uint32(effect->MiscValue) != lockInfo->Index[j])
6924 continue;
6925
6926 skillId = SkillByLockType(LockType(lockInfo->Index[j]));
6927
6928 if (skillId != SKILL_NONE)
6929 {
6930 reqSkillValue = lockInfo->Skill[j];
6931
6932 // castitem check: rogue using skeleton keys. the skill values should not be added in this case.
6933 skillValue = m_CastItem || m_caster->GetTypeId()!= TYPEID_PLAYER ?
6934 0 : m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetSkillValue(skillId);
6935
6936 // skill bonus provided by casting spell (mostly item spells)
6937 // add the effect base points modifier from the spell cast (cheat lock / skeleton key etc.)
6938 if (effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM_TARGET || effect->TargetB.GetTarget() == TARGET_GAMEOBJECT_ITEM_TARGET)
6939 skillValue += effect->CalcValue();
6940
6941 if (skillValue < reqSkillValue)
6942 return SPELL_FAILED_LOW_CASTLEVEL;
6943 }
6944
6945 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
6946 }
6947 }
6948 }
6949
6950 if (reqKey)
6951 return SPELL_FAILED_BAD_TARGETS;
6952
6953 return SPELL_CAST_OK;
6954}
6955
6956void Spell::SetSpellValue(SpellValueMod mod, int32 value)
6957{
6958 if (mod < SPELLVALUE_BASE_POINT_END)
6959 {
6960 if (SpellEffectInfo const* effect = GetEffect(mod))
6961 m_spellValue->EffectBasePoints[mod] = effect->CalcBaseValue(value);
6962 return;
6963 }
6964
6965 switch (mod)
6966 {
6967 case SPELLVALUE_RADIUS_MOD:
6968 m_spellValue->RadiusMod = (float)value / 10000;
6969 break;
6970 case SPELLVALUE_MAX_TARGETS:
6971 m_spellValue->MaxAffectedTargets = (uint32)value;
6972 break;
6973 case SPELLVALUE_AURA_STACK:
6974 m_spellValue->AuraStackAmount = uint8(value);
6975 break;
6976 default:
6977 break;
6978 }
6979}

6989
6990void Spell::LoadScripts()
6991{
6992 sScriptMgr->CreateSpellScripts(m_spellInfo->Id, m_loadedScripts);
6993 for (std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator itr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); itr != m_loadedScripts.end();)
6994 {
6995 if (!(*itr)->_Load(this))
6996 {
6997 std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator bitr = itr;
6998 ++itr;
6999 delete (*bitr);
7000 m_loadedScripts.erase(bitr);
7001 continue;
7002 }
7003 TC_LOG_DEBUG("spells", "Spell::LoadScripts: Script `%s` for spell `%u` is loaded now", (*itr)->_GetScriptName()->c_str(), m_spellInfo->Id);
7004 (*itr)->Register();
7005 ++itr;
7006 }
7007}
7008
7009void Spell::CallScriptBeforeCastHandlers()
7010{
7011 for (std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator scritr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); scritr != m_loadedScripts.end(); ++scritr)
7012 {
7013 (*scritr)->_PrepareScriptCall(SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_BEFORE_CAST);
7014 std::list<SpellScript::CastHandler>::iterator hookItrEnd = (*scritr)->BeforeCast.end(), hookItr = (*scritr)->BeforeCast.begin();
7015 for (; hookItr != hookItrEnd; ++hookItr)
7016 (*hookItr).Call(*scritr);
7017
7018 (*scritr)->_FinishScriptCall();
7019 }
7020}

7022void Spell::CallScriptOnCastHandlers()
7023{
7024 for (std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator scritr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); scritr != m_loadedScripts.end(); ++scritr)
7025 {
7026 (*scritr)->_PrepareScriptCall(SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_ON_CAST);
7027 std::list<SpellScript::CastHandler>::iterator hookItrEnd = (*scritr)->OnCast.end(), hookItr = (*scritr)->OnCast.begin();
7028 for (; hookItr != hookItrEnd; ++hookItr)
7029 (*hookItr).Call(*scritr);
7030
7031 (*scritr)->_FinishScriptCall();
7032 }
7033}

7035void Spell::CallScriptAfterCastHandlers()

7038 {
7039 (*scritr)->_PrepareScriptCall(SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_AFTER_CAST);
7040 std::list<SpellScript::CastHandler>::iterator hookItrEnd = (*scritr)->AfterCast.end(), hookItr = (*scritr)->AfterCast.begin();
7041 for (; hookItr != hookItrEnd; ++hookItr)
7042 (*hookItr).Call(*scritr);

7047
7048SpellCastResult Spell::CallScriptCheckCastHandlers()
7049{
7050 SpellCastResult retVal = SPELL_CAST_OK;
7051 for (std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator scritr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); scritr != m_loadedScripts.end(); ++scritr)
7052 {
7053 (*scritr)->_PrepareScriptCall(SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_CHECK_CAST);
7054 std::list<SpellScript::CheckCastHandler>::iterator hookItrEnd = (*scritr)->OnCheckCast.end(), hookItr = (*scritr)->OnCheckCast.begin();
7055 for (; hookItr != hookItrEnd; ++hookItr)
7056 {
7057 SpellCastResult tempResult = (*hookItr).Call(*scritr);
7058 if (retVal == SPELL_CAST_OK)
7059 retVal = tempResult;
7060 }
7061
7062 (*scritr)->_FinishScriptCall();
7063 }
7064 return retVal;
7065}
7066
7067void Spell::PrepareScriptHitHandlers()
7068{
7069 for (std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator scritr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); scritr != m_loadedScripts.end(); ++scritr)
7070 (*scritr)->_InitHit();
7071}
7072
7073bool Spell::CallScriptEffectHandlers(SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellEffectHandleMode mode)
7074{
7075 // execute script effect handler hooks and check if effects was prevented
7076 bool preventDefault = false;
7077 for (std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator scritr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); scritr != m_loadedScripts.end(); ++scritr)
7078 {
7079 std::list<SpellScript::EffectHandler>::iterator effItr, effEndItr;
7080 SpellScriptHookType hookType;
7081 switch (mode)
7082 {
7083 case SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_LAUNCH:
7084 effItr = (*scritr)->OnEffectLaunch.begin();
7085 effEndItr = (*scritr)->OnEffectLaunch.end();
7086 hookType = SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_EFFECT_LAUNCH;
7087 break;
7088 case SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_LAUNCH_TARGET:
7089 effItr = (*scritr)->OnEffectLaunchTarget.begin();
7090 effEndItr = (*scritr)->OnEffectLaunchTarget.end();
7091 hookType = SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_EFFECT_LAUNCH_TARGET;
7092 break;
7093 case SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_HIT:
7094 effItr = (*scritr)->OnEffectHit.begin();
7095 effEndItr = (*scritr)->OnEffectHit.end();
7096 hookType = SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_EFFECT_HIT;
7097 break;
7098 case SPELL_EFFECT_HANDLE_HIT_TARGET:
7099 effItr = (*scritr)->OnEffectHitTarget.begin();
7100 effEndItr = (*scritr)->OnEffectHitTarget.end();
7101 hookType = SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_EFFECT_HIT_TARGET;
7102 break;
7103 default:
7104 ABORT();
7105 return false;
7106 }
7107 (*scritr)->_PrepareScriptCall(hookType);
7108 for (; effItr != effEndItr; ++effItr)
7109 // effect execution can be prevented
7110 if (!(*scritr)->_IsEffectPrevented(effIndex) && (*effItr).IsEffectAffected(m_spellInfo, effIndex))
7111 (*effItr).Call(*scritr, effIndex);
7112
7113 if (!preventDefault)
7114 preventDefault = (*scritr)->_IsDefaultEffectPrevented(effIndex);
7115
7116 (*scritr)->_FinishScriptCall();
7117 }
7118 return preventDefault;
7119}
7120
7121void Spell::CallScriptSuccessfulDispel(SpellEffIndex effIndex)
7122{
7123 for (std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator scritr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); scritr != m_loadedScripts.end(); ++scritr)
7124 {
7125 (*scritr)->_PrepareScriptCall(SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_EFFECT_SUCCESSFUL_DISPEL);
7126 std::list<SpellScript::EffectHandler>::iterator hookItrEnd = (*scritr)->OnEffectSuccessfulDispel.end(), hookItr = (*scritr)->OnEffectSuccessfulDispel.begin();
7127 for (; hookItr != hookItrEnd; ++hookItr)
7128 hookItr->Call(*scritr, effIndex);
7129
7130 (*scritr)->_FinishScriptCall();
7131 }
7132}
7133
7134void Spell::CallScriptBeforeHitHandlers()
7135{
7136 for (std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator scritr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); scritr != m_loadedScripts.end(); ++scritr)
7137 {
7138 (*scritr)->_PrepareScriptCall(SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_BEFORE_HIT);
7139 std::list<SpellScript::HitHandler>::iterator hookItrEnd = (*scritr)->BeforeHit.end(), hookItr = (*scritr)->BeforeHit.begin();
7140 for (; hookItr != hookItrEnd; ++hookItr)
7141 (*hookItr).Call(*scritr);
7142
7143 (*scritr)->_FinishScriptCall();
7144 }
7145}
7146

7150 {
7151 (*scritr)->_PrepareScriptCall(SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_HIT);
7152 std::list<SpellScript::HitHandler>::iterator hookItrEnd = (*scritr)->OnHit.end(), hookItr = (*scritr)->OnHit.begin();
7153 for (; hookItr != hookItrEnd; ++hookItr)
7154 (*hookItr).Call(*scritr);
7155
7156 (*scritr)->_FinishScriptCall();
7157 }
7158}

7173void Spell::CallScriptObjectAreaTargetSelectHandlers(std::list<WorldObject*>& targets, SpellEffIndex effIndex, SpellImplicitTargetInfo const& targetType)
7174{
7175 for (std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator scritr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); scritr != m_loadedScripts.end(); ++scritr)
7176 {
7177 (*scritr)->_PrepareScriptCall(SPELL_SCRIPT_HOOK_OBJECT_AREA_TARGET_SELECT);
7178 std::list<SpellScript::ObjectAreaTargetSelectHandler>::iterator hookItrEnd = (*scritr)->OnObjectAreaTargetSelect.end(), hookItr = (*scritr)->OnObjectAreaTargetSelect.begin();
7179 for (; hookItr != hookItrEnd; ++hookItr)
7180 if (hookItr->IsEffectAffected(m_spellInfo, effIndex) && targetType.GetTarget() == hookItr->GetTarget())
7181 hookItr->Call(*scritr, targets);
7182
7183 (*scritr)->_FinishScriptCall();
7184 }
7185}

7214
7215bool Spell::CheckScriptEffectImplicitTargets(uint32 effIndex, uint32 effIndexToCheck)
7216{
7217 // Skip if there are not any script
7218 if (m_loadedScripts.empty())
7219 return true;
7220
7221 for (std::list<SpellScript*>::iterator itr = m_loadedScripts.begin(); itr != m_loadedScripts.end(); ++itr)
7222 {
7223 std::list<SpellScript::ObjectTargetSelectHandler>::iterator targetSelectHookEnd = (*itr)->OnObjectTargetSelect.end(), targetSelectHookItr = (*itr)->OnObjectTargetSelect.begin();
7224 for (; targetSelectHookItr != targetSelectHookEnd; ++targetSelectHookItr)
7225 if (((*targetSelectHookItr).IsEffectAffected(m_spellInfo, effIndex) && !(*targetSelectHookItr).IsEffectAffected(m_spellInfo, effIndexToCheck)) ||
7226 (!(*targetSelectHookItr).IsEffectAffected(m_spellInfo, effIndex) && (*targetSelectHookItr).IsEffectAffected(m_spellInfo, effIndexToCheck)))
7227 return false;
7228
7229 std::list<SpellScript::ObjectAreaTargetSelectHandler>::iterator areaTargetSelectHookEnd = (*itr)->OnObjectAreaTargetSelect.end(), areaTargetSelectHookItr = (*itr)->OnObjectAreaTargetSelect.begin();
7230 for (; areaTargetSelectHookItr != areaTargetSelectHookEnd; ++areaTargetSelectHookItr)
7231 if (((*areaTargetSelectHookItr).IsEffectAffected(m_spellInfo, effIndex) && !(*areaTargetSelectHookItr).IsEffectAffected(m_spellInfo, effIndexToCheck)) ||
7232 (!(*areaTargetSelectHookItr).IsEffectAffected(m_spellInfo, effIndex) && (*areaTargetSelectHookItr).IsEffectAffected(m_spellInfo, effIndexToCheck)))
7233 return false;
7234 }
7235 return true;
7236}
7237
7238bool Spell::CanExecuteTriggersOnHit(uint8 effMask, SpellInfo const* triggeredByAura) const
7239{
7240 bool only_on_caster = (triggeredByAura && (triggeredByAura->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR4_PROC_ONLY_ON_CASTER)));
7241 // If triggeredByAura has SPELL_ATTR4_PROC_ONLY_ON_CASTER then it can only proc on a cast spell with TARGET_UNIT_CASTER
7242 for (SpellEffectInfo const* effect : GetEffects())
7243 {
7244 if (effect && ((effMask & (1 << effect->EffectIndex)) && (!only_on_caster || (effect->TargetA.GetTarget() == TARGET_UNIT_CASTER))))
7245 return true;
7246 }
7247 return false;
7248}
7249
7250void Spell::PrepareTriggersExecutedOnHit()
7251{
7252 /// @todo move this to scripts
7253 if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName)
7254 {
7255 SpellInfo const* excludeCasterSpellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(m_spellInfo->ExcludeCasterAuraSpell);
7256 if (excludeCasterSpellInfo && !excludeCasterSpellInfo->IsPositive())
7257 m_preCastSpell = m_spellInfo->ExcludeCasterAuraSpell;
7258 SpellInfo const* excludeTargetSpellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(m_spellInfo->ExcludeTargetAuraSpell);
7259 if (excludeTargetSpellInfo && !excludeTargetSpellInfo->IsPositive())
7260 m_preCastSpell = m_spellInfo->ExcludeTargetAuraSpell;
7261 }
7262
7263 /// @todo move this to scripts
7264 switch (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyName)
7265 {
7266 case SPELLFAMILY_MAGE:
7267 {
7268 // Permafrost
7269 if (m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags[1] & 0x00001000 || m_spellInfo->SpellFamilyFlags[0] & 0x00100220)
7270 m_preCastSpell = 68391;
7271 break;
7272 }
7273 }
7274
7275 // handle SPELL_AURA_ADD_TARGET_TRIGGER auras:
7276 // save auras which were present on spell caster on cast, to prevent triggered auras from affecting caster
7277 // and to correctly calculate proc chance when combopoints are present
7278 Unit::AuraEffectList const& targetTriggers = m_caster->GetAuraEffectsByType(SPELL_AURA_ADD_TARGET_TRIGGER);
7279 for (Unit::AuraEffectList::const_iterator i = targetTriggers.begin(); i != targetTriggers.end(); ++i)
7280 {
7281 if (!(*i)->IsAffectingSpell(m_spellInfo))
7282 continue;
7283 SpellInfo const* auraSpellInfo = (*i)->GetSpellInfo();
7284 uint32 auraSpellIdx = (*i)->GetEffIndex();
7285 // todo 6.x
7286 if (SpellEffectInfo const* auraEffect = auraSpellInfo->GetEffect(m_caster->GetMap()->GetDifficultyID(), auraSpellIdx))
7287 {
7288 if (SpellInfo const* spellInfo = sSpellMgr->GetSpellInfo(auraEffect->TriggerSpell))
7289 {
7290 // calculate the chance using spell base amount, because aura amount is not updated on combo-points change
7291 // this possibly needs fixing
7292 int32 auraBaseAmount = (*i)->GetBaseAmount();
7293 // proc chance is stored in effect amount
7294 int32 chance = m_caster->CalculateSpellDamage(NULL, auraSpellInfo, auraSpellIdx, &auraBaseAmount);
7295 // build trigger and add to the list
7296 HitTriggerSpell spellTriggerInfo;
7297 spellTriggerInfo.triggeredSpell = spellInfo;
7298 spellTriggerInfo.triggeredByAura = auraSpellInfo;
7299 spellTriggerInfo.chance = chance * (*i)->GetBase()->GetStackAmount();
7300 m_hitTriggerSpells.push_back(spellTriggerInfo);
7301 }
7302 }
7303 }
7304}
7305
7306// Global cooldowns management
7307enum GCDLimits
7308{
7309 MIN_GCD = 1000,
7310 MAX_GCD = 1500
7311};
7312
7313bool Spell::HasGlobalCooldown() const
7314{
7315 // Only players or controlled units have global cooldown
7316 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER && !m_caster->GetCharmInfo())
7317 return false;
7318
7319 return m_caster->GetSpellHistory()->HasGlobalCooldown(m_spellInfo);
7320}
7321
7322void Spell::TriggerGlobalCooldown()
7323{
7324 int32 gcd = m_spellInfo->StartRecoveryTime;
7325 if (!gcd)
7326 return;
7327
7328 // Only players or controlled units have global cooldown
7329 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER && !m_caster->GetCharmInfo())
7330 return;
7331
7332 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
7333 if (m_caster->ToPlayer()->GetCommandStatus(CHEAT_COOLDOWN))
7334 return;
7335
7336 // Global cooldown can't leave range 1..1.5 secs
7337 // There are some spells (mostly not cast directly by player) that have < 1 sec and > 1.5 sec global cooldowns
7338 // but as tests show are not affected by any spell mods.
7339 if (m_spellInfo->StartRecoveryTime >= MIN_GCD && m_spellInfo->StartRecoveryTime <= MAX_GCD)
7340 {
7341 // gcd modifier auras are applied only to own spells and only players have such mods
7342 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() == TYPEID_PLAYER)
7343 m_caster->ToPlayer()->ApplySpellMod(m_spellInfo->Id, SPELLMOD_GLOBAL_COOLDOWN, gcd, this);
7344
7345 // Apply haste rating
7346 gcd = int32(float(gcd) * m_caster->GetFloatValue(UNIT_MOD_CAST_SPEED));
7347 if (gcd < MIN_GCD)
7348 gcd = MIN_GCD;
7349 else if (gcd > MAX_GCD)
7350 gcd = MAX_GCD;
7351 }
7352
7353 m_caster->GetSpellHistory()->AddGlobalCooldown(m_spellInfo, gcd);
7354}
7355
7356void Spell::CancelGlobalCooldown()
7357{
7358 if (!m_spellInfo->StartRecoveryTime)
7359 return;
7360
7361 // Cancel global cooldown when interrupting current cast
7362 if (m_caster->GetCurrentSpell(CURRENT_GENERIC_SPELL) != this)
7363 return;
7364
7365 // Only players or controlled units have global cooldown
7366 if (m_caster->GetTypeId() != TYPEID_PLAYER && !m_caster->GetCharmInfo())
7367 return;
7368
7369 m_caster->GetSpellHistory()->CancelGlobalCooldown(m_spellInfo);
7370}
7371
7372bool Spell::HasEffect(SpellEffectName effect) const
7373{
7374 for (SpellEffectInfo const* eff : GetEffects())
7375 {
7376 if (eff && eff->IsEffect(effect))
7377 return true;
7378 }
7379 return false;
7380}

7384
7385WorldObjectSpellTargetCheck::WorldObjectSpellTargetCheck(Unit* caster, Unit* referer, SpellInfo const* spellInfo,
7386 SpellTargetCheckTypes selectionType, ConditionContainer* condList) : _caster(caster), _referer(referer), _spellInfo(spellInfo),
7387 _targetSelectionType(selectionType), _condList(condList)
7388{
7389 if (condList)
7390 _condSrcInfo = new ConditionSourceInfo(NULL, caster);
7391 else
7392 _condSrcInfo = NULL;
7393}
7394
7395WorldObjectSpellTargetCheck::~WorldObjectSpellTargetCheck()
7396{
7397 delete _condSrcInfo;
7398}
7399
7400bool WorldObjectSpellTargetCheck::operator()(WorldObject* target)
7401{
7402 if (_spellInfo->CheckTarget(_caster, target, true) != SPELL_CAST_OK)
7403 return false;
7404 Unit* unitTarget = target->ToUnit();
7405 if (Corpse* corpseTarget = target->ToCorpse())
7406 {
7407 // use ofter for party/assistance checks
7408 if (Player* owner = ObjectAccessor::FindPlayer(corpseTarget->GetOwnerGUID()))
7409 unitTarget = owner;
7410 else
7411 return false;
7412 }
7413 if (unitTarget)
7414 {
7415 switch (_targetSelectionType)
7416 {
7417 case TARGET_CHECK_ENEMY:
7418 if (unitTarget->IsTotem())
7419 return false;
7420 if (!_caster->_IsValidAttackTarget(unitTarget, _spellInfo))
7421 return false;
7422 break;
7423 case TARGET_CHECK_ALLY:
7424 if (unitTarget->IsTotem())
7425 return false;
7426 if (!_caster->_IsValidAssistTarget(unitTarget, _spellInfo))
7427 return false;
7428 break;
7429 case TARGET_CHECK_PARTY:
7430 if (unitTarget->IsTotem())
7431 return false;
7432 if (!_caster->_IsValidAssistTarget(unitTarget, _spellInfo))
7433 return false;
7434 if (!_referer->IsInPartyWith(unitTarget))
7435 return false;
7436 break;
7437 case TARGET_CHECK_RAID_CLASS:
7438 if (_referer->getClass() != unitTarget->getClass())
7439 return false;
7440 // nobreak;
7441 case TARGET_CHECK_RAID:
7442 if (unitTarget->IsTotem())
7443 return false;
7444 if (!_caster->_IsValidAssistTarget(unitTarget, _spellInfo))
7445 return false;
7446 if (!_referer->IsInRaidWith(unitTarget))
7447 return false;
7448 break;
7449 default:
7450 break;
7451 }
7452 }
7453 if (!_condSrcInfo)
7454 return true;
7455 _condSrcInfo->mConditionTargets[0] = target;
7456 return sConditionMgr->IsObjectMeetToConditions(*_condSrcInfo, *_condList);
7457}
7458
7459WorldObjectSpellNearbyTargetCheck::WorldObjectSpellNearbyTargetCheck(float range, Unit* caster, SpellInfo const* spellInfo,
7460 SpellTargetCheckTypes selectionType, ConditionContainer* condList)
7461 : WorldObjectSpellTargetCheck(caster, caster, spellInfo, selectionType, condList), _range(range), _position(caster) { }
7462
7463bool WorldObjectSpellNearbyTargetCheck::operator()(WorldObject* target)
7464{
7465 float dist = target->GetDistance(*_position);
7466 if (dist < _range && WorldObjectSpellTargetCheck::operator ()(target))
7467 {
7468 _range = dist;
7469 return true;
7470 }
7471 return false;
7472}
7473
7474WorldObjectSpellAreaTargetCheck::WorldObjectSpellAreaTargetCheck(float range, Position const* position, Unit* caster,
7475 Unit* referer, SpellInfo const* spellInfo, SpellTargetCheckTypes selectionType, ConditionContainer* condList)
7476 : WorldObjectSpellTargetCheck(caster, referer, spellInfo, selectionType, condList), _range(range), _position(position) { }
7477
7478bool WorldObjectSpellAreaTargetCheck::operator()(WorldObject* target)
7479{
7480 if (!target->IsWithinDist3d(_position, _range) && !(target->ToGameObject() && target->ToGameObject()->IsInRange(_position->GetPositionX(), _position->GetPositionY(), _position->GetPositionZ(), _range)))
7481 return false;
7482 return WorldObjectSpellTargetCheck::operator ()(target);
7483}
7484
7485WorldObjectSpellConeTargetCheck::WorldObjectSpellConeTargetCheck(float coneAngle, float range, Unit* caster,
7486 SpellInfo const* spellInfo, SpellTargetCheckTypes selectionType, ConditionContainer* condList)
7487 : WorldObjectSpellAreaTargetCheck(range, caster, caster, caster, spellInfo, selectionType, condList), _coneAngle(coneAngle) { }
7488
7489bool WorldObjectSpellConeTargetCheck::operator()(WorldObject* target)
7490{
7491 if (_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CU_CONE_BACK))
7492 {
7493 if (!_caster->isInBack(target, _coneAngle))
7494 return false;
7495 }
7496 else if (_spellInfo->HasAttribute(SPELL_ATTR0_CU_CONE_LINE))
7497 {
7498 if (!_caster->HasInLine(target, _caster->GetObjectSize() + target->GetObjectSize()))
7499 return false;
7500 }
7501 else
7502 {
7503 if (!_caster->isInFront(target, _coneAngle))
7504 return false;
7505 }
7506 return WorldObjectSpellAreaTargetCheck::operator ()(target);
7507}
7508
7509WorldObjectSpellTrajTargetCheck::WorldObjectSpellTrajTargetCheck(float range, Position const* position, Unit* caster, SpellInfo const* spellInfo)
7510 : WorldObjectSpellAreaTargetCheck(range, position, caster, caster, spellInfo, TARGET_CHECK_DEFAULT, NULL) { }
7511
7512bool WorldObjectSpellTrajTargetCheck::operator()(WorldObject* target)
7513{
7514 // return all targets on missile trajectory (0 - size of a missile)
7515 if (!_caster->HasInLine(target, target->GetObjectSize()))
7516 return false;
7517 return WorldObjectSpellAreaTargetCheck::operator ()(target);
7518}
